title: fig 'n almond bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9-inch loaf pan. Finely grind 3/4 cup of almonds.
Chop remaining almonds.

Combine ground almonds, flour, dry milk, baking powder, cinnamon and salt. In another bowl, combine sugar, eggs, butter, zest and juice. Stir into flour mixture alternately with milk until combined. Stir in chopped almonds and figs.
Transfer to pan.
Bake until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean, 1 hour and 50 minutes.
Shield top of bread with foil halfway through baking. Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely on rack.

title: cole slaw
directions: Cut or grate cabbage, pepper and onion.
Mix vinegar and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Cool.
Pour over slaw.

title: delicious skillet dinner
directions: Melt shortening in a frying pan.
Put beef, onion and parsley in a frying pan and brown.
Combine tomato paste and water; pour in pan with sugar, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes. Add noodles and cook until tender.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil together.
Add the eggs; mix well.
Add cinnamon, salt, soda and flour.
Add carrots.
Bake in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Cook and mash potatoes; add butter, onion, mushroom soup and milk to potatoes.
Cube Velveeta and add to mixture.
Spray casserole with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: onion popcorn
directions: Place margarine in a 4-cup glass measuring cup.
Cover and microwave on High for 45 seconds or until melted.
Remove from oven and stir in soup mix.
Place popcorn in a large bowl.
Pour butter mixture on top and mix well.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except Cool Whip.
Mix by hand until thoroughly mixed.
Mix in the Cool Whip and stir to mix well.
Spoon into graham cracker crust.
Chill for several hours before serving.
Makes 2 pies.

title: easy caramel corn
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
In a heavy saucepan, combine the butter, brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and add baking soda.
Stir well.
Place popcorn in large roasting pan and pour caramel sauce over the popcorn.
Stir.
Bake 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: chicken dijon
directions: In skillet, in 1 tablespoon oil, cook chicken and onions until chicken is brown.
Remove to paper towels and pat dry.
Wipe oil from skillet and add soup, milk, mustard and parsley.
Heat to boiling.
Add chicken and onions.
Cover and simmer 5 to 10 minutes or until chicken is completely done and tender.
Serve over brown rice with asparagus and French bread.
Serves 4.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Grease 9-inch pie pan and cover bottom with crumbled bacon and shredded cheese.
Blend all remaining ingredients in blender for one minute.
Pour into pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: hush puppies
directions: In large bowl, sift together dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until blended.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into deep hot fat (375°).
Fry golden brown.

title: halloween spiders
directions: Mix together the melted chocolate, Rice Krispies and coconut. Drop approximately 1 teaspoon on wax paper.
Use the chow mein noodles as "legs" for the spiders and work them in quickly as the chocolate hardens quickly!
Do a single batch at a time because the chocolate does harden so fast.
This is a fun recipe for kids to join in.
It's creepy.
Enjoy.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream softened cream cheese; add mayonnaise.
Add broken dried beef and salts.
Mix together and form into a ball.
Roll in nuts. Refrigerate until needed.

title: deer pot roast
directions: Salt, pepper and flour roast.
Put roast in large browning bag.
Mix all the soups together with water.
Place vegetables around roast and pour soups over roast.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
tags: Campbell's golden cream of mushroom soup

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Beat eggs and margarine; mix other ingredients.
Cook in iron skillet about 30 minutes in 400° oven or until golden brown.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix sugar, butter, salt and flavoring; add eggs, then milk. Pour into pastry shell; cook 15 minutes in 450° oven.
Sprinkle top of pie with nutmeg.
Reduce heat and bake at 350° for 25 minutes more.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts.
Make a ball.
Roll in nuts until well covered.
Chill.

title: chicken casserole #1
directions: Boil chicken.
Tear meat off the bone.
Use broth to boil noodles.
When finished boiling noodles, replace meat in broth with the noodles.
Add soups, mixing well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with torn up pieces of bread.
Now top with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: expresso truffles
directions: Break chocolate into pieces and melt double-boiler fashion. Make sure steam and water do not get in chocolate.
Bring milk and cream to boil.
Stir in corn syrup and butter.
Add ground coffee beans and let set for 20 minutes.
Strain mixture through cheesecloth and pour over melted chocolate.
Mix slowly and gently.
The mixture should be glossy and smooth.
Refrigerate for 1 hour and make a 1-inch diameter ball by rubbing between palms of your hands.
Roll ball in cocoa powder.
Makes about 40 truffles.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Make a white sauce with butter, flour and milk.
Add cheese, cook until melted.
Add chicken soup, carrot and broccoli.
Mix bouillon cube and water and add it to the cheese soup with Worcestershire sauce and onion.
Cook on low.

title: glazed turkey roast
directions: Prepare turkey as directed on package.
Heat cranberry sauce, corn syrup, lemon peel and lemon juice over low heat.
Stir constantly.
Twenty minutes before roast is done, remove from oven.
Spoon off drippings.
Pour cranberry glaze over turkey. Roast uncovered 20 minutes, spooning glaze over turkey.
Place roast on warm platter.
Spoon glaze over top.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken shrimp supreme
directions: In saucepan, melt butter; add mushrooms and onion, saute for 5 minutes.
Add soup; gradually stir in sherry and half and half. Add cheese and heat over low heat, stirring occasionally, until cheese is melted.
Add chicken and shrimp; do not boil.
Stir in parsley and serve over rice.
This may be served in a chafing dish.
May be prepared, covered and refrigerated and reheated just before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken potato soup
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Debone.
Skim fat off remaining broth.
Add to broth the onion, carrots, celery and bouillon cubes.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 45 minutes.
Add potatoes and evaporated milk.
Simmer on low heat for 20 minutes.

title: frozen banana punch
directions: Combine all ingredients except ginger ale and freeze.
Remove from freezer 45 minutes before serving.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and serve from a large punch bowl.

title: french strawberry pie
directions: Spread cream cheese (that has been blended with enough milk to soften) over bottom of cooled crust.
Wash berries and drain well. Place half of the choicest berries in cheese.
Coat shell, standing in regular rows.
Mash remaining berries.
Stir in sugar and cornstarch, mixed.
Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes, stirring often.
Cool and pour over berries in the shell.
Place in refrigerator until cold.
Spread with sweetened whipped cream and chill again.

title: caramel apple squares
directions: Arrange crackers in bottom of 12 x 8-inch baking dish, cutting crackers to fit, if necessary.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Put cranberries, orange and nuts through food processor. Dissolve Jell-O in water, add sugar.
When thick add berries, nuts and orange.
Place in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: friendship cake(thirty day fruit cake)
directions: Combine
starter,
peaches
with juice and 2 cups sugar and stir
every day for 10 days. Combine pineapple with juice and 2 cups
sugar.
Add
to mixture and stir every day for 10 days. Combine
cherries

and 2 cups sugar.
Add to mixture and
stir

day
for
10 days.
At the end of 30 days, drain
overnight, saving the liquid (this is the starter).
Fruit makes 3 cakes.

title: hot beef
directions: Combine.
Bake for 5 hours at 275°.
Break apart and return to juice.
Heat 6 to 8 hours in crock-pot.

title: yogurt corn muffins
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, honey, baking powder and salt.
Add yogurt, egg, oil and water, mixing just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill 12 oiled or paper-lined muffin cups 3/4 full. Bake at 425° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Cream together shortening, sugars, egg yolks, flour, water, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle chocolate chips and chopped nuts over top of batter. Press down lightly.

title: huckleberry cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add lemon juice, rind and egg and beat until well blended.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Add milk.
Stir in carrot and huckleberries.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until done.
Yields about 4 dozen.

title: deb's cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add sugar gradually.
Add salt and blend in milk, vanilla and lemon juice.
Add Cool Whip. Prepare and bake crust.
Cool.
Spoon mixture into cooled crust. Let set 3 hours.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed. Drop a teaspoon of batter onto greased pan and bake at 350° for 9 to 12 minutes or until done.

title: pineapple sandwich spread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour and undrained pineapple.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Cool and store in refrigerator.
Keeps well in a jar.

title: elbow salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions and drain.
Mix dressing, milk, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add all ingredients together.

title: bubble batter #1
directions: Measure 10 cups water into a clean pail or bucket.
Add the Dawn or Joy dish soap.
Add the glycerine (it makes the bubbles more durable by reducing evaporation).
Stir, but not too much. Skim off any from on top.

title: chocolate icebox pie
directions: Melt chocolate.
Soften gelatin in cold water and stir into the hot mixture.
Add egg yolks (beaten light) with 1/2 cup sugar.
Add salt and vanilla.
Cool.
Beat remaining 1/2 cup sugar into egg whites and fold into chocolate mixture.
Pour into cooled pie shell.

title: easy spaghetti sauce
directions: In skillet, brown meat and drain.
Mix onion, garlic, chili powder and green pepper.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add soup, sauce and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add garlic and onion powder.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: pineapple bake
directions: Melt butter; soak bread in it until absorbed.
Set aside.
Sift sugar and flour together.
Mix with eggs and pineapple.
Put in 1 1/2-quart greased casserole.
Place buttered bread cubes on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Be sure to pour in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish that had been sprayed with Pam.
The last 5 to 10 minutes remove from oven and sprinkle on extra 1/2 to 3/4 cup stuffing mix on top.
Return to oven and bake the last 5 to 10 minutes.

title: apple spice snack cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 9 x 9-inch metal baking pan.

title: chicken salad with a twist
directions: Cook macaroni.
Mix chicken and Italian dressing with hot macaroni.
Cool pasta mixture.
Blend mayonnaise, lemon juice and mustard.
Stir in olives, zucchini, salt and pepper.
Add to pasta mixture.
Chill 2 or more hours.
Serve with lettuce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken wings
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chicken wings, and mix well. Add chicken wings and marinate for 1 hour, making sure to coat all thoroughly.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet for 1 hour at 350°.

title: coney island hot dog sauce
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Add flour, sugar and brown sugar; beat until well blended.
Blend in cooled, melted oleo.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve warm, topped with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: breakfast casserole(serves 8)
directions: Place in casserole.
Leave in refrigerator overnight.
Place in cold oven.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover last few minutes to brown.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars until light.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients; blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts, coconut and chocolate chips.
Drop from teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° about 10 minutes.
Cool cookies slightly before removing from pan.
Makes about 3 to 4 dozen.

title: biscuit ring-a-round
directions: Brown meat, pour off fat, add other ingredients and simmer until slightly thickened.
Put meat in center of platter. Surround with cheese biscuits.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix all.
Add more flour if needed and drop by spoonfuls in hot oil.

title: ham and broccoli bake
directions: Cook frozen broccoli according to package and drain.
Saute onion in butter or margarine.
In a large mixing bowl, stir together the soups, milk and shredded cheese.
Add the broccoli, ham, uncooked rice, onion and Worcestershire sauce and mix well. Pour into large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Microwave on High for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peanutty crisscrosses
directions: In medium
bowl, mix oatmeal, flour and soda.
In large bowl, mix butter,
peanut
butter
and
sugar
until light and fluffy. Add water,	egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and mix well. Chill

Shape
dough to form 1-inch balls.	Place on	ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with fork dipped in sugar to	form
crisscross
pattern.
Bake
9 to 10 minutes at 350°
or until
edges
are
golden
brown.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet. Remove to wire cooling rack.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: cocoa banana bars
directions: Combine oat bran, flour, granulated sugar and 1/3 cup cocoa. Add combined banana, 1/4 cup margarine, corn syrup, egg whites and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into a 9-inch microwavable pie plate. Microwave on High for 4 minutes and 30 seconds to 5 minutes or until edges are firm to the touch, rotating every 2 minutes.

title: grilled shrimp in the italian style
directions: Shell the shrimp but leave the last segment of the shell and the tail attached to each shrimp.
With a small sharp knife, devein the shrimp by making a shallow incision down the back and lifting out the intestinal vein with the point of the knife.
(If you wish, you may dispense with the deveining process altogether.) Wash the shrimp thoroughly under cold running water and pat them dry with paper toweling.

title: chiligetti
directions: Cook and stir ground meat and onions in a large skillet until meat is brown and onion is tender. Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, chili powder, salt, and beans. (Do not drain.) Heat to boiling; reduce heat and cook uncovered about 10 minutes. Cook spaghetti according to pkg. directions; drain. Pour spaghetti onto a large platter and top with hot chili mixture.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and cook 20 to 25 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: pasta salad
directions: *Suggestions:
Tomatoes, broccoli, carrots, celery, green and red peppers, cucumbers, onions and olives.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and milk. Add pudding mix. Beat well. Chill 5 minutes. Whip cream. Fold whipped cream and Cool Whip into pudding mixture. Spoon 1 cup mixture into 2 1/2-quart glass serving bowl. Top with 1/3 each of wafers, bananas and pudding, ending with pudding. Chill. Garnish as desired.

title: hamburger-zucchini casserole
directions: Steam squash with a little water in a covered saucepan until 1/2 cooked; drain well.
Place zucchini in a buttered casserole dish.
Cover with cooked hamburger.
Add rice and spread tomatoes and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, or microwave for 5 minutes on High.

title: country steak
directions: Trim excess fat from steak.
Sprinkle flour evenly on both sides of meat and pound with mallet.
Melt shortening in large Dutch oven.
Brown steak on both sides.
Combine remaining ingredients, stirring well, then pour over steak.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until tender, adding more water if needed.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Put Tater Tots in oven to brown at 350°.
In iron skillet, brown ground beef. Drain. Add all other ingredients; mix well. Take Tater Tots out of oven. Top ground beef mixture.
Return to oven (in iron skillet). Bake for 30 minutes.

title: bubble bread
directions: Mix sugar, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll biscuit quarters in sugar mixture.
Place biscuits in Bundt pan and pour melted margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: kahlua
directions: Put 6 cups water in pot; add 6 cups sugar and bring to a boil and boil 10 minutes.
In separate pan, boil 2 cups water; add the jar of instant coffee and dissolve.
Pour into simple syrup, stir well and set aside to cool.
Slice vanilla beans lengthwise and put into a gallon jar (glass jar with top that will seal).
After simple syrup and coffee cool completely, add to container and pour in the 2 fifths of vodka, mixing well.
Seal jar and let set 6 weeks before using.
Each week shake the jar.
When you are ready to serve, use a highball type glass, 1 or 3 ounces of Kahlua, several ice cubes and fill the glass with sweet milk.
Also, can be used over vanilla ice cream.

title: coconut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Generously grease (not oil) and lightly flour the bottom of
a
x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake approximately 35
minutes.
Frost with White Cloud Frosting;
sprinkle with coconut.

title: roasted garlic and brie soup
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In shallow baking dish, place the unpeeled garlic cloves and drizzle with 2 tablespoons of the olive oil. Cover dish with foil and bake until tender, approximately 30 minutes. When tender, remove dish to rack to cool.

title: lorine's transparent pie
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and flour together.
Add the eggs, milk and vanilla.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: salsa di vingole-white clam sauce
directions: Heat oil in heavy saucepan.
Add garlic, celery and green onion and cook at medium heat for 1 minute while stirring.
Add clam juice, clams, salt and pepper.
Simmer, covered, for 2 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add butter.
Stir.
Serve at once.
Makes 4 to 6 servings or 1 pound linguine.

title: helen's egg stuffed peppers
directions: Cut the top of each pepper.
Remove seeds and membranes; in a 3-quart saucepan.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugars.
Add pumpkin and milk.
Add flour, mixed with salt and spices.
Beat well.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a hot oven, 450°, for 10 minutes, then in a moderate oven, 325°, for 40 minutes.

title: honey bee cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, eggs, sugar, oil and sour cream and beat 10 minutes.
Pour 1/3 batter into well-greased tube pan, then 1/2 nut/sugar mixture, then 1/3 more of batter, remainder of nut/sugar mixture and rest of batter.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: venison chili
directions: Simmer tomatoes 5 minutes in their own juices.
Add onions, green peppers and cook until tender, stirring often.
Add garlic and parsley.
Melt butter in a large skillet and saute meat for 15 minutes.
Add meat to tomato mixture; stir in chili powder and cook 10 minutes.
Add beans and spices and water, if needed. Simmer covered 1 hour.
Cook uncovered for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pineapple cheese cake
directions: Use deep bake pan.
In a bowl, combine cream cheese, sugar, eggs, vanilla and milk until smooth and well blended.
Over a pie crust, spread evenly the crushed pineapple, then spread the cheese and egg mixture into the crust.
Bake in a 250° oven until well done.

title: bishop's delight
directions: Mix up night before.
Cover and refrigerate.
Scramble eggs. When cooked, add sour cream, cheese and meat.
Mix together and place in greased baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together ingredients.
This is great on chicken and pork chops.

title: good tasting chocolate frosting
directions: Combine melted shortening, cocoa and salt; then add milk and vanilla.
Mix in sugar in 3 parts with electric mixer until smooth and creamy.
Add more sugar to thicken or milk to thin, if needed for good spreading consistency.
Frosts two 8 or 9-inch layers or one 9 x 13-inch sheet cake.

title: quick and easy icebox fruit cake
directions: Chop cherries.
Mix all the ingredients.
Line a pan with wax paper.
Press very firmly into the lined pan.
Refrigerate.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar and flour.
Then add melted margarine and mix well.
Add buttermilk and flavoring.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 325° until custard is set and a little brown on top.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hickory stick
directions: Mix together well.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Take out 3 days in a row and mix well.
On the 4th day, make 3 rolls and bake in broiling pan for 8 hours at 180°.
Slice and serve.

title: lemon cheese pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese with electric mixer until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients individually, mixing well after each addition.
Pour mixture into vanilla wafer crust and bake at 350° for 10-15 minutes.
Remove from oven and refrigerate until chilled. Top with any flavor pie filling before or after chilling.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix all ingredients well and shape into loaf.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Cut into slices, 1/2 to 2-inch slices and dip in flour.
Brown slightly on both sides in small amount of hot oil.
Place slices in casserole dish.
Dilute 1 can mushroom soup with 1/2 can of water; pour into the skillet after all meat is browned.
Pour the mixture over the meat slices; cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: epicurean salad
directions: Place mixed greens on large plate, place crab meat on greens. Arrange shrimp on top of crab.
Add avocado wedges, tomato, ripe olives and egg slices.
Serve with cocktail sauce, lemon wedges and salad dressing.
Serves 1 to 2.

title: wassail
directions: Heat apple juice, orange juice, and lemon juice in a large pot.
Add cinnamon candies.
Heat until candy is melted.

title: italian broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli until very tender.
Drain and mash, leaving some bits of broccoli.
In large skillet, saute onion and garlic in oil; add broccoli.
Add bread crumbs and cheese and stir until blended.
Add egg; remove from heat and stir until blended.
Add seasonings.
Stir to blend.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook broccoli and sugar snap peas in a large pot of lightly salted boiling water for 2 minutes or until very crisp-tender. Remove with strainer and rinse under cold running water.

title: pig in a blanket
directions: Split hot dogs down middle on one side (not all the way through).
Spread mustard and insert cheese in split in hot dog. Wrap with crescent roll.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes, until roll is done.

title: millionaire shortbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a food processor, blend together the flour, sugar and 1/4 cup of the butter.
Press into a buttered 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden.
Cool.

title: si's salmon ball
directions: Remove large bones and skin from salmon.
Mix all ingredients together, use your hands!
Form it into a ball.
Mix pecans and parsley; roll salmon ball in nuts until completely coated.
Press gently with hands to set nut coating.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix together and bake in sheet pan at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: ritz cracker snacks
directions: Cook milk, dates and vanilla until thick.
Cool.
Spread a teaspoon of mix on each cracker.
Bake 5 minutes at 350°.
Cool. Frost each one with cheese, sugar and butter mixture.
They freeze very well.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Dice cheese in large pieces and place in crock-pot on high setting.
After cheese is melted, add tomatoes, chili and green chilies.
Mix well.
Reduce heat to low.
Serve over tortilla chips.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburg and onion, add taco seasoning mix.
Prepare according to package directions.
Cool slightly.
Mix all ingredients together, in a large bowl.
Add Doritos and mix well. Serve with salsa and sour cream to taste.

title: tacoritos
directions: Deep fry the flour tortillas and form in the shape of a rectangle taco shell.
(Fry both sides of tortilla and fold in half.)
Brown turkey meat in frying pan; when browned, add in beans and dry taco mix.
This mixture will be used for the filling of the tacorito.
Chop the tomatoes; shred the cheese and shred the lettuce.
Put these in separate bowls for garnishing the tacorito.
Also, put the olives in a separate bowl.
The tacorito can be topped with the ingredients, with guacamole and sour cream on the top.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cream together butter, shortening and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Add flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Mix well. Press dough into large jelly roll pan (12 x 17-inch) or into 2 pizza pans.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: mexican dressing for spinach salad
directions: Put all together in blender and blend thoroughly (omits chopping onion).
Refrigerate; keeps indefinitely.
Prepare at least 12 hours before using.
Makes enough dressing for 2 packages of spinach.

title: basic white sauce
directions: In medium saucepan, melt margarine.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook until mixture is smooth and bubbly; gradually add milk.
Heat until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly. Makes 2 cups.

title: fish chowder
directions: Fry salt pork in a deep kettle, being careful not to burn it. When crisp, remove pork and set aside.
Fry onions until soft, but not browned.
Add water and potatoes.
Cook for five to ten minutes; add fish, cut into two-inch pieces and simmer until all tender.
Add milk or cream; heat until just a simmer.
Add salt, pepper and a pinch of herbs to taste.
If using milk, add a tablespoon of butter and the crisp fried pork.
Cool, reheat and serve.
Do not boil.
Serves 6.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cut up potatoes and stir it up a little.
Put all the stuff in a bowl and mix it up.

title: refried beans(fat free)
directions: Place beans, onions and garlic in water; boil for 1 1/2 hours or
until soft.
Add salt and continue to cook for about 45 minutes.
Mash and use.
Freeze what you don't use.

title: steamed shrimp
directions: Combine all ingredients except shrimp in pan with lid.
Bring to boiling and add shrimp.
Stir to get seasoning all over the shrimp.
Bring to boiling.
Cover, lower heat and steam until tender.
Do not overcook.

title: angel balls
directions: Heat these 5 ingredients and cook slowly for 6 minutes stirring constantly.
Take off heat and add 4 cups rice crispies, 2 cups nuts chopped fine.
Make into balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze spinach until dry.
Stir spinach, sour cream, mayonnaise, soup mix and green onions until well blended.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Serve with crackers and veggies or hollow out center of loaf of bread and fill with dip.
Use center of bread cube and serve as dippers.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine 1 tablespoon flour and the salt and sprinkle over strips of beef.
Stir to coat beef strips.
Heat skillet, then add 2 tablespoons butter.
When melted, add beef strips and brown quickly, turning meat to brown all sides.
Add the mushroom slices, onion and garlic; cook 3 to 4 minutes or until onion is barely tender.
Remove meat and mushrooms from skillet.
Add 2 tablespoons butter to pan drippings; when melted, blend in 3 tablespoons flour. Add tomato paste.
Slowly pour in cold meat stock.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Return browned meat and mushrooms to skillet.
Stir in sour cream and sherry.
Heat briefly.
Do not allow to boil after sour cream is added.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: southern spoon bread
directions: Beat eggs (separate).
Melt butter in 3-quart saucepan.
Stir in meal.
Add boiling water, then milk, stirring constantly, until smooth.
Pour in egg yolks, then fold in egg whites to which has been added salt and baking powder.
When mixture begins to rise, pour in greased heated baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Put 1/4 to 1/2 cup flour over nuts and apples.
Mix first three ingredients by beating well.
Add flour and mix well.
Add vanilla and fold in apples and pecans.
Bake at 350° for about 55 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix and pour in greased pan.
Put about 1/3 cup oleo, sliced on top, and bake for 1 hour.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt (set aside).
Place in pan the water, oil, margarine and cocoa.
Bring mixture to a boil and remove from heat.
Pour mixture over dry ingredients.
Add eggs and beat.
Mix in soda, buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat for a minute.
Pour in greased pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate covered peanuts
directions: Melt chips and peanut butter over low heat.
Add 2 cups Spanish peanuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Let sit in refrigerator about 30 minutes.
Can store at room temperature.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix first three ingredients and put in pan.
Mix together last four ingredients.
Place half on top of other mixture and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Put other half of icing on top while hot.

title: bourrekas(cheese pastries)
directions: Crumble the Feta cheese with a fork.
Add the grated Parmesan and Swiss cheeses and stir with a fork until the cheeses are mixed.
Add 1 egg to the cheeses and blend everything together. Cut each of the two puff pastry sheets into squares.
Add the cheese mixture.
Close the filled pastries by folding the pastry into a triangular shape and decorating the edges with a small fork.
Brush the pastries with beaten egg and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Put the pastries on a baking tray and bake in a 350° oven for approximately 15 minutes, or until the pastries are a golden brown.

title: bite sized cheesecakes
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs, sugar, coconut and butter. Press into bottom of cups.
Melt 1 cup of the chocolate chips and set aside.
Beat cream cheese.
Add milk and chocolate chips.
Add egg and vanilla (and melted chips).
Beat until smooth.
Pour into petite four cups and bake 20 minutes at 300°.
Refrigerate.

title: strawberry poppy seed dressing
directions: In a blender, combine sugar, vinegar, onion juice and mustard. Add oil gradually; blend until smooth.
Beat in pureed strawberries.
Pour into quart jar or container.
Cover and chill. Serve over fruit or mixed greens.

title: pork with chinese flavor
directions: Cook noodles, drain and rinse.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in large skillet.
Tilt to coat evenly.
Add egg and tilt again.
When egg is set, remove.
Cut into strips.
Set aside.
In same skillet, cook pork in 2 more tablespoons oil until browned.
Add celery and onion; cook 2 minutes.
Add chicken broth.
Combine cornstarch, salt, pepper, ginger and soy sauce.
Stir into pork mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened and boil 1 minute.
Remove.

title: 24 hour vegetable salad
directions: Arrange layer of each vegetables as listed.
Cover with 1 layer of 1 1/2 cups of Miracle Whip and 1/2 pint sour cream (mixed together).
Cover this with mild grated cheese.
Cover and keep in refrigerator for 24 hours before serving.
(Best arranged in long rectangular shaped casserole about 12-inches.)

title: turkey loaf
directions: Fry Tender Bits in oil until brown.
Add all ingredients together.
Stir well.
Put into baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon into skillet and fry until crisp.

title: hamburger taco pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain and mix with taco seasoning. Add refried beans, water and barbecue sauce.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Make cornbread according to package directions; let it cool. Crumble cornbread into large bowl. Chop tomatoes and bell pepper, then mix with mayonnaise into the crumbled cornbread. Refrigerate.

title: yankee pot roast
directions: In Dutch oven, heat corn oil over medium heat.
Add roast; brown on all sides.
Remove.
Add onions; cook until lightly browned.
Remove.
Pour off excess fat.
Add bouillon or broth, tomatoes, salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Return roast to Dutch oven. Bring to boil over high heat.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until roast is almost tender.
Add potatoes, carrots, turnips and browned onions.
Cover and cook 20 to 30 minutes or until roast is tender and vegetables are cooked as desired.
Remove roast and vegetables to serving platter.
Keep warm.

title: pork tenderloin with peppercorns
directions: Press pepper into meat with fingers.
Heat butter in frying pan just large enough to hold pork, over medium-high heat.
Brown pork on all sides.
Reduce heat to low.
Pour brandy over pork.
Stir in remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cover and cook 20 to 25 minutes. Remove pork and cut into ???-inch slices.
Pour sauce over top. Makes 2 or 3 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries, apples, oranges and pineapple.
Add sugar. Dissolve jello and let set until it gets about half jelled, then add cranberry mixture and stir.
Add crushed pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: friendship cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until smooth and fluffy. Add flour and salt, blending to make a smooth dough. Carefully fold in 1 pinch of love. Press dough into ungreased cookie sheet pan. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350° or until lightly browned. Remove from oven and sprinkle with powdered sugar. Cut into wedges while warm. Yield: 8 large cookies or 18 small cookies.

title: frosted pineapple banana shake
directions: In a blender, puree the pineapple and the banana.
Add the ice milk, orange juice and lemon juice. Blend until smooth.
Pour into 2 tall glasses and garnish each glass with a pineapple wedge and a cherry. Serves 2.

title: hamburger-sour cream casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic in butter. Stir in all other ingredients except for sour cream, Parmesan and noodles.
Simmer 30 minutes. Fold in sour cream, Parmesan and noodles. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese, sugar, and peanut butter.
Stir in milk and fold in whipped topping.
Stir in chocolate chips. Pour filling into pie crusts.
Melt together the chocolate and shortening.
Then spread over tops of pies.
Place pies in freezer for 6-8 hours until firm.

title: cherry flip
directions: Melt margarine and add graham cracker crumbs.
Take half of crumb mixture and press in bottom of dish.
Beat together Dream Whip and milk, add in sugar and vanilla, beat again.
Add cream cheese and beat until smooth.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil for 5 minutes the brown sugar, oleo and white syrup. Remove from heat, add soda and vanilla; mix well.
Pour over corn, stirring as you pour.
Corn should be in 2 large deep pans.
Cook in preheated oven at 250° for 45 minutes, stirring every 9 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.
Will keep for months and are delicious.

title: guess again carrots
directions: Pare, slice and boil carrots until tender.
Mash carrots well. Add butter, onion and cheese. Place this mixture into 1-quart buttered casserole.
Sprinkle top with unflavored bread crumbs. Dot with butter.
Bake in a 350° oven covered for 40 minutes.

title: california blend vegetable salad
directions: Cook California Blend vegetables for 2 minutes; drain.
Add mushrooms, celery, green onions, black olives, green olives and tomatoes.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Freeze in ice cream freezer according to instructions.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: icebox cake
directions: Crush graham crackers very fine.
In a saucepan, stir butter and marshmallows until melted.
Remove from heat.

title: turkey chow mein
directions: Cut green pepper in thin strips; cook with celery slices in butter for 2 minutes.
Add broth.
Blend cornstarch with cold water and soy sauce.
Gradually stir into broth.
Add dry onion soup mix.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Add turkey, mushrooms, water chestnuts (drained and thinly sliced) and bean sprouts (drained).
Heat mixture and serve with chow mein noodles. Makes 6 servings.

title: corned beef hot dish
directions: Mix all together.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in an 8 x 11-inch greased pan.

title: pepper relish
directions: Put the first 4 ingredients through food chopper.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Seal.
Makes 8 pints.

title: west virginia bean soup
directions: Brown sausage and drain grease.
Put beans in pot.
Add all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on high for 4 hours.
I add a little hot sauce to it.
It doesn't take much.

title: german chocolate icing
directions: Pour first 5
ingredients in a saucepan and cook until thick, about 10 to 12 minutes.
When thick, add chopped pecans and coconut.
Beat until cooled.

title: potatoes and ham casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 1 hour or until potatoes are done.
Sprinkle with white and yellow cheeses.
Bake about 15 minutes or until cheeses are lightly browned.

title: hawaiian fruit cake
directions: Break up graham crackers and run through blender.
Add rest of ingredients except eggs.
Beat in eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Pour mixture into 3 (9-inch) greased and waxed paper-lined cake pans and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° or a tube pan, baking longer at 340°.

title: plum cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given in large bowl; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 4 x 8-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May be baked in 2 small loaf pans.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl and stir by hand.
Cook on hot griddle.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Combine refried beans and taco seasoning.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with sour cream.
Top sour cream with grated cheese.
If jalapeno peppers are desired, they can be diced and placed in bean mixture.
Place jalapeno slices on top of cheese for garnish.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Serve with tortilla chips and picante sauce, if desired.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Add pickle juice and relish to salad dressing, pour over cornbread.
Add rest of ingredients in order.
Let sit overnight and toss before serving.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add margarine, orange juice and egg.
Combine only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cantaloupe salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Makes 4 large servings.

title: hot spiced percolator punch
directions: Put pineapple juice and water in bottom of an 8-cup percolator.
Put the rest of the ingredients in the top.
Perk for 10 minutes.
Serve hot in mugs.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend together.
Serve with cut slices of fruit (favorites). Dip into dip.

title: corn chowderwaterford, michigan
directions: Prepare soup as directed on can.
Chop celery and add to soup.

title: ritz delight
directions: Make peanut butter and Ritz crackers by putting peanut butter on the crackers, then put together.
Melt chocolate pieces in a bowl in oven or microwave.
Dip peanut butter and crackers into the melted chocolate.

title: chocolate fudge sauce
directions: *I toast almonds in the oven; watch carefully, they will burn.

title: spicy cajun mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms; trim ends and cut in half.
In heavy saute or frypan, heat oil and butter.
Add chopped garlic and mushrooms. Saute mushrooms for 2 minutes; add Cajun Spice Blend.
Two minutes later, add remaining ingredients and saute for another 2 minutes. Serve hot.
Serves 4 people.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in oven on 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies no. 2
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in peanut butter.
Sift dry ingredients; stir into creamed mixture.
Shape dough into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with a fork dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: twin beef turnovers
directions: Make pastry with 2 1/2 cups of flour.
Melt butter in skillet. Add onion, green peppers and beef; brown lightly.
Add peas and carrots and sprinkle with salt, pepper and 3 tablespoons of flour. Stir well.
Divide pastry dough in half.
Roll each into a 12-inch circle.
Moisten edges of dough with water.
Fold pastry over filling like a giant turnover and press edges together to seal.
Cut open design for escape of steam.
Bake in a very hot oven (450°) for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to moderate (375°) and continue baking for 20 minutes.

title: mini reuben snacks
directions: Mix corned beef and dressing.
Place bread slices on broiler pan and divide corned beef mixture among bread slices.
Top with sauerkraut and cheese.
Broil 4-inches from heat 4 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini and onion until tender.
Melt stick of margarine; mix with the dry Stove Top and seasoning packet.
Put half of the mixture on bottom of casserole dish.
Drain squash and onion; mix in sour cream and soup.
Pour into dish and put rest of Stove Top mixture on top.
Bake for 20 minutes, uncovered, and then cover for another 10 to 15 minutes.
tags: Stove Top corn bread stuffing mix

title: taco soup
directions: Heat all of the ingredients until hot.
Dish up into soup bowls, top with grated cheese.
Serve with taco chips.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Brown meat; drain off fat.
Combine all ingredients and pour in 1 (9 or 10-inch)
pie shell. Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: granola(low-fat, 100% natural)
directions: Coat 3 large jelly roll pans with nonstick spray.
In a large bowl mix the oats with the wheat germ and dry milk.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix and sift cocoa and sugar.
Mix in flour and salt.
Add cream and stir.
Add vanilla and cook over low heat and stir constantly until consistency of hot gravy.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Stir yeast in water until dissolved; add brown sugar, salt, margarine, eggs and 2 cups whole wheat flour.
Stir until mixed. Add 8 to 9 more cups flour; knead until mixed.
Put in big Tupperware bowl and seal with lid.
Wait 30 minutes.
Divide into 4 parts.
Put in loaf pans, cover with towel and wait about 30 minutes until it has risen.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit dressing
directions: Combine sugar, flour and egg yolk; add fruit juice.
Cook in double boiler till thick.
Cool.
Fold in whipped cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Make dressing, mixing well. Pour over broccoli mixture, stirring to evenly coat.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.
Keeps well.

title: hamburger chili cornpone
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef and onions.
Drain well. Place on paper towels to absorb grease.
Add ingredients to ground beef and onions, except corn and kidney beans.
Return to skillet and simmer for 15 minutes, covered.
Drain kidney beans and corn. Layer beans and corn on bottom of casserole dish.
Put ground beef mixture over corn and beans.
Make 1 cup of cornbread mixture. Pour cornbread mixture on top of casserole.
Bake in a 425° oven for 20 minutes or until cornbread is baked.

title: tomato, artichoke, mushroom and olive salad
directions: Drain tomatoes, artichoke hearts (rinse with cold water and slice in half), olives and mushrooms.
Gently mix well, drained vegetables in a large bowl.
In a jar, place remaining ingredients and shake until well blended.
Toss dressing with vegetables. Cover salad lightly and leave at room temperature for at least 1 hour or several hours.
Stir gently occasionally.
Refrigerate.

title: white fluffy icing
directions: Boil sugar and water without stirring until mixture spins 6 to 8-inch thread.
Keep pan covered first 3 minutes of cooking to prevent crystals forming on sides of pan.
Beat egg whites until stiff enough to hold a peak.
Pour hot syrup very slowly into egg whites, beating constantly; add flavoring.
Be sure icing is cool before adding fruits, nuts, etc.

title: crusty baked potatoes
directions: Brush potatoes with butter.
Place cut side down on baking sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: veal rollettes
directions: Mix garlic, Parmesan cheese, parsley, salt and pepper. Set aside.
Cut veal into 4 x 3-inch pieces.

Put 1 slice of Mozzarella cheese on each piece of meat. Top each with 1 teaspoon garlic-cheese mixture. Roll each piece of meat to enclose mixture. Tie with string or fasten with wooden picks or skewers.
Heat oil in a skillet. Add meat rolls and brown slowly on all sides.
Put meat into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Mix butter and water. Pour over meat.
Cover casserole. Bake at 300° for about 1 hour or until meat is tender. Remove fasteners and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix Karo syrup, eggs, sugar, butter, vanilla and flour together, then add chopped pecans.
Add to mixer.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: tuna fish casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain. Add macaroni, celery soup, tuna fish, peas, onions and 1/2 cup of shredded cheese in a 2-quart casserole dish along with milk. On top, add remaining 1/2 cup cheese then slice butter on top of cheese then sprinkle bread crumbs on last. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Mix
1/2 Oreos and margarine.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding as directed on box, then mix it with cream
cheese
and spread over crumbs.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle remaining crumbs on top and chill.

title: orange pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time; beat, alternate with orange juice and flour.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add the beans, tomatoes, salt and pepper to taste and chili powder.
Heat together.
Dip the tortillas in the sauce, then fill and add some onion and cheese.
Roll up and put side by side in a casserole.
Cover with rest of the sauce.
Top with onion and cheese.
Bake until bubbly.
Serve with lettuce, tomatoes and hot sauce.

title: azuki coffee dessert
directions: In a small bowl, soften gelatin in water.
In a large bowl, dissolve instant coffee in boiling water; add gelatin.
Stir well. Add tsubushi-an and condensed milk.
Mix.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill approximately 6 hours.

title: shrimp stew
directions: Brown flour in oil.
Add onions, garlic and tomato paste, stirring until paste browns.
Add water slowly, stirring to be sure of smoothness.
Add salt, pepper, sugar, bay leaf, Tabasco sauce and lemon juice.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Add shrimp and simmer for 20 minutes or until shrimp are cooked.
Add more water if gravy becomes too thick.
Serve over rice.

title: dessert squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and put into greased and floured pan. (Mixture will be dry.)
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over cake mix mixture. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: buttermilk candy
directions: Combine buttermilk and soda in 3-quart saucepan; let stand for 20 minutes.
Add sugar and corn syrup; bring to a boil, stirring, until sugar dissolves.
When boiling, add margarine and cook to soft ball stage (236°).
It will be a medium brown in color.
Cool until lukewarm; beat until mixture loses gloss and thickens.
Stir in pecans.
Makes 36 pieces.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Mix all other ingredients together. Pour 1/2 of mixture in heavy iron 10-inch skillet, then pour meat, then rest of batter.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour until golden brown.

title: pudding cake
directions: Mix altogether; grease and flour pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken in casserole dish.
Mix in Pet milk.
Pour cream of chicken soup over mixture.
Pour stuffing mixed with broth over ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, oleo and Karo until smooth.
Add flour, salt and eggs.
Beat slightly.
Add vanilla and pecans.	Pour into pie shell.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Lower heat and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Pie is done when top starts to crack.
Do not overbake.

title: taco pie
directions: In pie pan, spread cream cheese on bottom and sides.
Add can of beans and flatten to top of cream cheese.
Pour jar of salsa on top of beans.
Spread shredded cheese on top of salsa.
Sprinkle sliced olives on top of cheese.

title: jamaican curried goat
directions: Clean and wash goat meat.
Add all seasoning to meat and mix together.
Cover in pan for 1 hour.
Pour 4 tablespoons cooking oil in pot on low heat.
Pour meat and seasoning in pot and cover. Will cook itself.
Add a little water occasionally and stir until cooked.

title: peach bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs and mix thoroughly.
Add peaches and dry ingredients.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Bake in 2 loaf pans (floured and greased) at 325° for 1 hour.
Can be made in advance and frozen.

title: apricot delight(salad or dessert)
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, water and jello.
Boil 2 to 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Put in freezer to cool.
When cool, add baby food and pineapple.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Sift together milk powder and sugar.
Stir in syrup and peanut butter.
When mixture gets stiff, knead like dough until it is the color of peanut butter.
Press into a pan and refrigerate.

title: caramel brownies
directions: In a bowl, mix cake mix, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and butter. In double boiler, melt caramels and add 1/3 cup evaporated milk (or cook in microwave 2 minutes on High, let stand 1 to 2 minutes and cook additional 2 minutes on Medium).
Spread half of cake mixture in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 6 minutes.
Spread chocolate chips over baked cake.
Spread melted caramel mixture on top of chips.
Dot rest of cake mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until cake is done.

title: sugar crisps
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Sift together flour and salt and set aside.
Cream butter and shortening together.
Add dry ingredients gradually with eggs, sour cream, vanilla and softened yeast.
Cover.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: pea casserole
directions: Simmer margarine, onion, celery and pepper.
Cook frozen peas or drain canned peas.
Mix with onion, celery and pepper mixture; add chestnuts, soup and pimento.
Pour into casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with potato chips or Ritz cracker crumbs.

title: rich orange loaf cakes
directions: Generously grease two loaf pans.
Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, beat all ingredients but nuts at low speed to mix, then medium speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.

title: old fashioned two-egg cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together; add eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk, then add flavorings.
Mix until smooth and creamy.
Pour batter into 2 (9-inch) greased and floured cake pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from pans.

title: sweet-n-sour meatballs with sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients except Sweet-And-Sour Sauce.
Shape mixture by tablespoons into 1 1/4-inch balls.

(For ease in shaping meatballs, wet hands occasionally with cold water.) Arrange meatballs in rectangular dish, 11 x 7 x 1 1/2 inches. Cover loosely and microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes, rearranging meatballs after 5 minutes, until no longer pink inside.
Let stand, covered, 3 minutes; drain.
Prepare Sweet-And-Sour Sauce. Stir meatballs gently into sauce until coated.
Cover tightly and microwave 4 to 6 minutes or until hot.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: boil cake
directions: Add dry ingredients.
Add milk and shortening after bringing to a boil.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: crab and cheese quiche
directions: Combine mayonnaise, flour, eggs and milk; mix thoroughly. Stir in crabmeat, cheese and onion.
Spoon into baked, pricked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until firm in center; garnish with parsley.
Yield: 1 (9-inch) quiche.

title: carrot bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and pour into ungreased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients until they adhere in a large bowl. Make into bite-size balls and bake 15 minutes at 375°.
May be cooled and frozen.
Makes 48 balls.

title: easy stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in casserole pan.
Cook for 3 hours at 325°.
Serve over noodles.

title: make ahead coleslaw
directions: Combine cabbage, onion, celery, carrots, green pepper and cucumber.
Mix well and set aside.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries; add sugar and let stand until sugar is dissolved.
Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup hot water; pour all together and mix well.
Let stand until firm.

title: soft molasses jumbos
directions: Cream butter and 1 cup sugar until well blended. Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in remaining ingredients; then chill.
When firm enough to roll, roll on lightly floured board to 1/4 inch thickness.
Sprinkle with sugar and roll lightly to make sugar stick.
Cut with a floured 3-inch cutter.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.

title: peachy chicken
directions: Pour melted butter over chicken that's in a baking pan.
Place 1/4 to 1/2 cup stuffing on each breast.
Roll breast and place seam side down.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Sift
flour;
blend
in shortening until crumbs are the size of	peas.
Beat
egg;
add	vinegar, salt and water.
Mix with fork
until mixture leaves side of bowl and forms a ball. Makes enough for 2 fruit pies.

title: pay day candy
directions: Combine and bring to a boil the sugar and honey.
Add peanut butter.
Mix and pour over
Cheerios and nuts.
Stir together. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool before cutting.

title: wilted lamb's quarter
directions: Saute onion in vegetable oil over medium heat in a skillet. Add vinegar, salt, pepper and greens, then stir-fry until lamb's quarter is limp.

title: broccoli au gratin
directions: Heat 1-inch salted water (1/2 teaspoon salt to 1 cup water) to boiling.
Add broccoli.
Cover and heat to boiling.
Cook until stems are tender, 12 to 15 minutes.
Drain.
Arrange broccoli in ungreased oblong pan, 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inches.

title: ginger ale salad
directions: Heat ginger ale; add to jello.
Let stand until slightly thick, then add remainder of ingredients and refrigerate.

title: memi's alaska rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and set aside.
Warm eggs to room temperature.
Heat flour in microwave for 20 seconds.

title: cajun beans
directions: Cook meat well done-fine texture; drain liquid off bacon.
Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: greek chicken
directions: Boil rice as per package instructions.
Thaw spinach in 1/4 cup water in 2-quart saucepan.
Add grating of nutmeg and dash of salt.
Toast pinenuts 6 to 7 minutes in 350° toaster oven.
Pound breasts and rub in smashed garlic.
When spinach is thawed, add lemon juice; dissolve cornstarch in small amount of broth and combine broth and thickener with spinach.
Bring to a boil while stirring.
Turn off burner under spinach.
Place breasts in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle with pepper; add wine.
Cover dish completely with plastic wrap and microwave for 4 minutes.
Crumble cheese over breasts, then layer spinach and rice; finally sprinkle pinenuts on top.
Cover dish completely with plastic wrap and microwave for 1 minute and 20 seconds.

title: orange cool whip salad
directions: Mix cool whip with orange jello. Add cottage cheese and mix well. Fold in pineapple,
oranges, and pecans. Let chill in the refrigerator
before serving.

title: banana-nut cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour and soda together.
Combine buttermilk to mashed bananas. Add alternately to egg mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts, sprinkled in a little flour.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: quiche
directions: Place all ingredients, except ham and cheese, in blender. Blend well.
Pour into 9-inch or 10-inch greased pie pan. Sprinkle ham and cheese evenly over top, pushing gently below surface.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: cheese-stuffed meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine beef, crumbs, pepper, tomato sauce and 1 egg.
In small bowl, combine 1 egg, Ricotta and Parmesan cheeses and parsley.
Press 1/3 of beef mixture into 9 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Make shallow well in center. Spoon cheese mixture into well.
Cover with remaining beef mixture. Pat firmly at sides to seal. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: egg and sausage bake
directions: Mix together eggs, milk, salt, dry mustard and pepper.
Brown sausage.
Combine all ingredients and cover.
Put into refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, uncovered.

title: venison marinade
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour over meat.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours.
Can marinate for 3 to 4 days.
Broil or barbecue.

title: amish barbecue pork chops
directions: Pour mixture over pork chops and bake for 2 hours at 375°.

title: clam appetizer dip
directions: Rub bowl with halved garlic clove.
Cream the cream cheese with spoon until smooth.
Gradually add remaining ingredients; blend well.
Serve with crackers or raw cauliflower pieces.
If too thick, add more clam juice.
Makes 1 pint.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces. Mix flour, salt and pepper; pound into steak. Brown steak in oil on both sides. Mix remaining ingredients; heat to boiling. Pour sauce over steak. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Yields 4 servings.

title: refrigerator oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream butter and sugars together.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Add oatmeal and nut meats. Shape in rolls.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill thoroughly or overnight.
Slice 1/4 inch thick, bake on lightly buttered cookie sheets for 10 minutes in 350° preheated oven.
Yields 10 to 12 dozen.

title: corn pudding
directions: Heat oven to 325° for 1 hour and 15
minutes.
Grease a casserole
dish.
Beat eggs in large bowl.
Stir
in
butter, flour, sugar, salt, pepper and nutmeg until
blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into prepared dish.
Insert knife in center to check if it is done.
Can be
prepared in advance and refrigerated until ready.

title: hot artichoke and crab dip(appetizer)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray baking dish with cooking oil.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, and garlic.
Drain and chop artichoke and crabmeat.
Mix all ingredients together and bake 25 - 30 minutes.
Garnish with green onion and red pepper.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Wrap chicken in rolls; set aside. Combine soup, milk and cheese.
Melt and pour over chicken rolls. Bake at 350° for 20-40 minutes or until rolls are done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix golden mushroom soup, milk and onion soup mix together.
Put the rice in casserole dish on top of chicken and then pour soup mixture over the top of rice and chicken.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: drop doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add milk, oil and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to egg mixture and mix well.
Drop by small teaspoonfuls into hot oil.
Cook until brown and roll in sugar while hot.
Children like to help by rolling them in sugar.

title: merry jack-o'-lanterns
directions: Place puffed rice in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Pour into large greased bowl.
Melt butter and marshmallows in double boiler over boiling water, stirring until smooth.
Stir in orange extract and food colorings.
Stir mixture into puffed rice until evenly coated.
Shape into 8 balls with greased hands.
Let stand for several hours or until firm.
Fasten green gumdrops on top of each ball with frosting for stem.
Cut each black gumdrop into triangles; arrange triangles on each ball for nose and eyes.
Add black string licorice for mouth.
Let stand until frosting is set.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt 4 tablespoons butter; add flour and salt.
Add milk slowly; cook until sauce thickens.
Add sliced potatoes; bring to a boil.
Put into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish and dot with remaining butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Makes 15 servings.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and softened butter. Press firmly in bottom and sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
In a large bowl, beat cheese until soft and smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar, mixing well.
Stir in 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Pour carefully into spring-form pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/4 hours or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Let cool for 10 minutes.

title: peter piper's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, sweetener and whipped topping together.
Place 1/2 of mixture in the bottom of the pie crust. Blend pudding and milk.
Add pumpkin and spices.
Pudding will be thick.
Spread over whipped topping in pie crust and cover with the remaining whipped topping mixture.
Refrigerate.
Chill for 4 hours.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix oats, flour and brown sugar.
Add nuts.
Cut in oleo until crumbly.
Place 1/2 mixture in greased pan.
Cover with uncooked rhubarb mixed with remaining ingredients.
Top with other half of oat mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cabbage roll casserole
directions: Sear ground chuck, onions, salt and pepper until brown.
Add rice and simmer 2 minutes.
Add soup and water and mix well.
Stir in cabbage and place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: In a deep saucepan, brown the ground meat; drain. Mix in the next 8 ingredients and set aside.

title: cream cheese blueberry delight
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, pecans and butter.
Put in baking dish and bake for 15 minutes at 325°.
Cool well.

title: "lady baltimore" cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs together.
Dissolve soda in water and add.
Mix and sift flour, salt and spices; add to the first mixture.
Add raisins and nuts; mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 or 20 minutes.
This receipt makes about 70 cookies.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown the hamburger in a skillet and drain the grease.
Mix in the seasoning.
Cook the refried beans.
Crumble the taco shells in a bowl (you can also use nacho cheese tortilla chips).
Mix in the remaining ingredients and add salsa to taste.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine egg whites, milk, coloring, sugar, salt, vanilla, raisins and cinnamon.
Mix and blend well.
Add rice and pour into shallow quart casserole.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until a knife comes out clean when tested in the middle.
Serve warm.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Scald milk to boiling point after adding cocoa, 2 cups sugar and salt.
Pour into an ice cream freezer (8-quart).
Add cream and remaining ingredients.
Add additional milk as needed to fill freezer and set freezer into motion.
Freeze until hard with ice and rock salt around outside of freezer can.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Place beans in a baking dish; add soup.
Sprinkle with water chestnuts and almonds.
Top with cheese.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, oil, vanilla, cinnamon, salt, baking soda, baking powder and cream cheese.
Add zucchini and mix well.
Add flour, beat with mixer 2 minutes.
Fold in nuts.
Turn into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
In small bowl, combine soup and milk. Beat with a whisk until smooth.
Stir all ingredients together. Turn into a 2-quart casserole.
If desired, top with 1/2 cup toasted, slivered almonds.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes at 425°.
Serves 6.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Fry tortillas in skillet with grease; set aside.
Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Add Ranch Style beans, Ro-Tel and cream of mushroom soup.
Stir and heat.
Layer casserole dish as follows:
tortillas, meat mixture and Velveeta cheese.
Top with Velveeta and cook in oven long enough for cheese to melt.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: Put all ingredients into crock-pot.
Cook on high all day until carrots are tender.

title: boiled egg custard
directions: Mix
sugar,
flour and eggs together.
Beat well.
Heat milk to	scalding.
Gradually
pour egg mixture into milk and cook until it coats a spoon.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: holiday fruit cookies
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar and eggs; add sour cream.
Sift flour, soda and salt; stir in nuts, cherries and dates.
Chill.
Drop with spoon on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: antipasto salad
directions: In large bowl, combine vegetable oil, vinegar, garlic, basil, salt and red pepper.
Add warm pasta and Parmesan cheese; toss to coat well.
Stir in broccoli, tomatoes, pepperoni and Mozzarella cheese.
Cover; chill 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: mashed potato filling
directions: Cook celery in butter with salt, pepper, parsley and saffron until soft, about 10 minutes.
Lightly mix with potatoes, eggs, bread cubes and milk.
Spoon into a well buttered casserole.
Dot top with butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: breakfast bubble ring
directions: Grease 12 cup Bundt pan.
Mix granola, sugar and cinnamon. Cut each biscuit (uncooked) in half and dip in butter.
Roll in granola mixture, pressing into dough.
Layer in pan.
Sprinkle with remaining mixture and butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Turn out at once onto plate.
Serve warm.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, milk, and garlic powder.
Spread thin on pizza pan or cookie sheet.
Cover with shrimp cocktail sauce. Cover with shrimp or crab meat.
Sprinkle with parmesan cheese and parsley flakes.
Serve with crackers.

title: baked stuffing and chicken
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine over low heat. When tender, add some bread cubes to soak up margarine. Turn everything into a bowl. Add remaining bread cubes and spices. Toss well. Add chicken broth until stuffing is desired consistency. Place cooked chicken in the bottom of a baking dish. Pack stuffing on top of chicken. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until stuffing is lightly browned and dry enough for taste.

title: creamy marshmallow fudge
directions: Combine sugar, evaporated milk and salt.
Cook and stir until sugar melts.
When bubbles cover the entire surface, boil and stir over medium heat for 6 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Beat in peanut butter, chocolate pieces, marshmallows and vanilla.
Beat until everything is melted.
Spread into buttered 9-inch square pan. Chill until hard.
Keep refrigerated until ready to use.
Makes 64 squares.

title: 7 minute brown sugar frosting
directions: Combine brown sugar, water and egg whites in top of double boiler.
Place over boiling water.
Beat with rotary beater or electric mixer for 7 minutes.
Remove from boiling water.
Add vanilla; continue beating until mixture stands up in peaks when beater is lifted.
Spread on cake; sprinkle with toasted coconut, if desired.
Makes generous frosting for two 8 or 9-inch cake layers.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel and seed avocados.
In a large bowl, mash avocados with lime juice and salt.
Add onion, chilies and tomato.
Mix thoroughly.
Cover and chill.
Serve with corn chips or tortilla chips.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine margarine, flour and pecans. Mix well. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Cool.

title: funnel cake
directions: Beat egg and add milk.
Sift flour, salt, sugar, baking powder and baking soda together.
Add egg and milk to dry ingredients. Beat until smooth.
Heat oil in deep fryer to 375°.
Cover the opening of a 5/8-inch funnel with finger and pour small amount of batter into the funnel.
Slowly swirl funnel over hot oil, releasing the batter to make cakes about 6-inches in diameter. Fry until brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: soft batch chocolate chip cookies
directions: Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, then add rest all together.
Blend well by hand.
Grease pans (glass).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Let loaves set in pans a few minutes before setting on racks to cool. Makes 2 loaves.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease a 10-inch Bundt pan; sprinkle with 1 teaspoon basil. Set aside.
Position knife blade in food processor bowl; add 1 1/2 cups flour and next six ingredients to processor bowl.
Process two minutes.
Add enough remaining flour through food chute with processor running until dough begins to form a ball.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead 1 minute.
Roll dough to a 15 x 12-inch rectangle; brush with one-third of melted butter.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch diamond shaped pieces.
Layer half of pieces, buttered side down, in prepared pan.
Brush top with half of remaining butter and sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon basil.
Repeat procedure with remaining dough, butter and basil.
Cover and let rise in a warm place about 45 minutes or until double in bulk. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan 2 minutes; invert onto a wire rack to cool.
Yield:
1 loaf.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix together instant pudding and 2 1/2 cups of milk until slightly thickened. Add sweetened condensed milk and Cool Whip to pudding. Mix well. In a 9 x 13-inch dish, layer vanilla wafers and bananas and pour mixture over layers. Refrigerate before serving (at least 2 hours).

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, oil, vanilla, and salt.
Sift dry Ingredients together.
Add to egg mixture.
Add zucchini, nuts, and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb cherry pie
directions: In mixing bowl, combine the first 4 ingredients; let stand for 15 minutes.
Prepare pie crust and line pan.
Add filling and top with crust.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes or until crust is golden and filling is bubbling.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil
your
chicken until tender or done.
Take chicken out of	broth.	Set
aside to cool.
Add cream of chicken and poultry seasoning
to
your broth.	Heat broth until cream of chicken has blended in.
Add salt and pepper to your taste.

title: swiss green beans
directions: Melt butter or margarine; blend in flour, salt, pepper, sugar and onion.
Add sour cream.
Stir constantly while cooking at low temperature until mixture thickens.
Add drained green beans.
Mix with grated cheese.
Place in 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: truly different cupcakes
directions: Melt chips and butter; add nuts and stir until nuts are covered.
Set aside.
Combine sugar, flour, eggs and vanilla.
Mix only until blended; do not beat.
Add chocolate chip mixture, mixing carefully.
Pour into muffin tins that are lined with foil cup liners.
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Makes approximately 24.

title: chicken breast supreme
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with bacon and beef.
Layer in baking dish.
Mix together soup and sour cream.
Spread evenly over chicken.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.

title: chicken devine
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Do not cook broccoli ahead.
Make a sauce by combining soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Layer 1/2 of the sauce mixture, mushrooms, chicken, broccoli and 1/2 of cheese.
Repeat.
Brown bread in small amount of butter and sprinkle on top of mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: funny cake
directions: Mix and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: choose a fruit or vegetable bread
directions: Combine flours, oats and soda; set aside.
In a large mixer bowl, beat butter or margarine with an electric mixer on medium speed for 30 seconds.
Add sugar; beat until fluffy, scraping sides of bowl often.
Add eggs, milk, vanilla and lemon peel; beat well.
Stir in vegetable or fruit.
Add flour mixture, a third at a time, beating on low speed until combined.
Stir in walnuts. Spread batter in a greased 5 1/2-cup ring mold or 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 50 minutes for ring mold or for 55 to 60 minutes for loaf pan, or until a wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cover with foil the last 10 minutes of baking; cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool on wire rack.
Wrap and store overnight for easier slicing.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix all 3 ingredients and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: tuna cashew casserole
directions: Set aside 1/2 cup noodles.
Combine remaining ingredients. Transfer into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup noodles over top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage and potato casserole
directions: Slice potatoes anyway you want to.
Slice onion same way as potatoes.
Cook potatoes and onion in a deep skillet until almost done.
Add smoked sausage; cover with lid and cook slowly until done.
Cover potatoes, onion and sausage with cheese.
Put lid back on and let the cheese melt.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and lay in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan, ungreased.
Bake at 350° until a very light brown.
Take out and completely cool.

title: corn oysters
directions: Mix well, stirring the corn kernels in last.
Heat oil in nonstick skillet on medium heat.
Drop rounded tablespoonful of batter into skillet. Cook until golden and crisp on bottom. Turn and brown on the other side.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil, then let simmer until used.

title: egg noodles
directions: Break egg into 1 1/2-quart bowl; add milk and salt and beat up.
Add 1 cup flour and blend real good.
Add more flour until you have workable dough.
Turn out on heavily floured pastry cloth.
Roll and turn; add in flour as you roll very thin.
Let dry for 2 hours.
Cut in very narrow strips.
Put in chicken broth and cook until done.

title: cantaloupe chiffon pie
directions: Prepare a 9-inch crust and bake until lightly brown.
Set aside to cool.

title: zucchini beef skillet
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add onion, green pepper, garlic, pepper and chili pepper, then add zucchini, tomatoes, corn, pimentos and parsley.
Simmer until done.

title: canned green beans
directions: Boil and sterilize jars.
Prepare jar lids.
In large pot, bring water, sugar, vinegar and salt to boil, stirring until sugar and salt have melted.
Add beans and bring back to a boil.
Cook 45 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal.
Makes about 7 to 8 quarts.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: You may use more butter and mayonnaise if you need too. I use this basic recipe and add if I think I need to.

title: rabbit or squirrel pot pie
directions: Mix well.
Roll out on floured surface paper thin.
Cut in strips, then cut diagonal squares about 1-inch in size.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix cocoa, flour and sugar together.
Add margarine, vanilla and eggs.
Beat until mixed.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: pickled cabbage
directions: Chop up cabbage.
(Can use food processor.)
Cook until tender. Add turmeric to desired color.
Grind up green tomatoes and pepper with sausage grinder, mix with cabbage, and squeeze out water.
In large stainless steel pot add vinegar, sugar & water.
Dissolve sugar.
Place spices in cheese cloth.
Secure tightly.
Place in pot.
Add cabbage mixture.
Cook about 30 minutes.
Pack in hot sterilized jars.
Seal.
This is very good as a side dish with hamburgers.

title: apple custard pie
directions: Bake pastry shell at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: apple chow chow
directions: Put apples, peppers and onions through food chopper.
Add other ingredients and boil.
Boil for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Put mixture into sterilized jars and seal.
Yields approximately 8 pints.

title: soft tacos
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain fat.
Add chopped cheese and beans.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Serve on tortillas.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini.
Mix lightly, but well.
Add flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Mix well; add nuts.
Pour into 2 floured and greased loaf pans.
Bake at 250° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.

title: lentil soup
directions: Combine all; cook 1 1/2 hours.

title: crunchy veggie dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight. Serve with crackers or veggies.

title: deviled eggs and cheese
directions: Boil eggs and slice eggs when cool.
Mix all ingredients together.
Fill each egg half.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Chill and serve.

title: potato tot casserole
directions: Fry and drain the hamburger. Add 1/4 cup of water, the
cube, and the Cream of Mushroom Soup. Mix together.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Drain vegetables and combine with celery, onion and pimento. Pour marinade over all and refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: You will need a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add berries, egg and milk and stir to moisten.
Add melted shortening and mix in.
Pour into round or square cake pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and dot with butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes, depending on pan size (longer time for larger pan).
When tester comes out clean, cake is done.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Melt the butter in microwave-safe 2-quart glass casserole with a lid, about 1 minute.
Stir in cabbage, apple, onion, vinegar, brown sugar, golden raisins, salt and allspice.
Cover and microwave on High power for 8 to 10 minutes, stirring 4 times until the cabbage is very soft.
Let stand, covered, for 2 minutes.
Add freshly ground pepper; taste and adjust seasonings.
Serve hot or warm.
Serves 4. Preparation time:
10 minutes.
Cooking time:
11 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: This is for the microwave.

title: pumpkin bread
