directions: Mix first 9 ingredients well. Bake at 350°, small loaf pan for 30 minutes, or large loaf pan for 35 minutes.

title: ritz bits snacks
directions: Melt almond bark.
Dip Ritz Bits to cover.
Use food coloring in almond bark for desired color (very festive).
Let cool on wax paper.

title: hot fruit compote
directions: Drain fruit and save juice.
Cook orange in juice a little while and drain.
Mix all fruits and put in large casserole dish.

title: lentil soup
directions: Cook lentils for 20
minutes.
Add
the
rest of ingredients and simmer until vegetables are soft;
30 minutes or so.
Our family enjoys this.

title: chocolate delight balls
directions: Melt chocolate; stir in cream cheese and vanilla.
Cool to room temperature.
Fold in nuts and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Make walnut-size balls and roll in coconut.
Keep in refrigerator for storage.

title: brownies
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until light and fluffy.
Melt chocolate and butter together.
Add egg mixture to chocolate mixture. Combine flour, baking powder and nuts.
Add flour mixture to chocolate.
Mix until smooth.
Pour batter into greased 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool and cut into squares. Makes about 20 brownies.

title: raisin sandwich spread
directions: Stir ingredients together in saucepan.
Bring to a boil over low heat.
Cook until mixture forms a string from the spoon.
Add 1/2 to 1 pound ground raisins and 1/2 cup of mayonnaise.
Add nuts, if desired.
Mix well and spread on the bread of your choice.

title: layer cookies
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, melt the oleo.
Add the rest of the ingredients in the order listed, one on top of the other. Sprinkle graham crumbs over melted oleo, then nuts, chips and coconut.
Pour the can of Eagle Brand milk over all the layers and bake at 350° for 25 minutes, until brown on top.
Cool before cutting.

title: buttermilk cookies
directions: Cream together the sugar and shortening.
Add the egg, salt and vanilla.
Sift together the dry ingredients.
Add the dry ingredients and buttermilk alternately to the creamed mixture.
Be sure to start and end with the dry ingredients and mix well after each addition.
Drop onto a greased baking sheet; bake in a 350° oven for approximately 10 minutes.
These are a nice soft cookie and taste very good with a frosting.

title: lower fat chocolate chip cookies(heart healthy)
directions: Option:
One half cup whole wheat flour may be substituted for 1/2 cup white flour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, soups, mushrooms and chicken stock.
When ready to bake, add Chinese noodles and pour into casserole.
Top with water chestnuts (these can be omitted).
Bake 20 minutes at 350° uncovered.
Sprinkle remaining noodles over top and bake for 10 more minutes.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Mix all together.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Spread on crackers.

title: fudge chocolate cake
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Mix margarine, cocoa and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture and stir until well mixed.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 14 pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Add dry ingredients.
Mix together.
Set aside.
Cream the sugar and
oleo. Add egg, water and vanilla.

title: pie crust
directions: Put the flour in a bowl and make a hole in the middle of the flour.
Mix in the oil, water and salt.
As you mix the ingredients, use as much of the flour as necessary to form a ball of dough that can be easy to handle, not sticky.
Roll out dough between two pieces of waxed paper, large enough for your pan. Flute the edge of the crust.
Use foil on the edge of the crust to keep it from getting too brown.

title: french toast
directions: Mix egg, sugar, milk and cinnamon.
Dip sliced bread in mixture.
Fry in a well-greased iron frying pan on medium heat. Brown on both sides.
Top with your favorite syrup or fruits or sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: peanut butter 'n chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together the margarine, sugar, brown sugar, peanut butter, eggs and vanilla until creamy smooth. Add (and stir after each ingredient) the baking soda, salt and flour, until well mixed.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: one dish meal
directions: Cut up green salad in oblong dish. Make as to your desire (lettuce, tomatoes, etc.). Brown ground chuck with onion and bell pepper. Drain well.

title: carrot nut bread
directions: Beat together the sugar, eggs and margarine.
Add the dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in the carrots and walnuts.
Pour equal amounts into two (2) no-stick loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool.
Remove from pan.
Slice and serve.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix jello in boiling water.
Add partially thawed strawberries, drained crushed pineapple and pecans.
Turn 1/2 into pan and let set, keeping remaining half at room temperature.
When set, put sour cream on top and add remaining jello mixture.
Let set.
Chill.

title: easy chicken cacciatore
directions: Cut up onion, pepper and garlic.
Put on top of chicken.
Add oregano, salt and pepper.
Pour tomatoes over.
Do not add water!

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Saute onions in 1
tablespoon
margarine
in Dutch oven lid. Place an inverted pie plate inside a 12-inch Dutch oven. Put
the uncooked pie shell in
a
second
pie
plate
on
the inverted plate.
Layer with ham
and onions.
Add eggs, cream, dry mustard, nutmeg, salt and
pepper.
Bake
for
minutes with 12 coals on top and 12	coals
on
the	bottom.
Allow to cool for 10 to 15 minutes before cutting and serving.

title: mexican popcorn
directions: Microwave popcorn, then toss with taco seasoning mix.
Store in airtight container.

title: lori's easy peach cobbler
directions: Grease 9 x 13 pan.
Layer in order peaches and jello (sprinkle over peaches); spread cake mix next.
Pour water over cake mix; melt butter and pour over everything.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until golden brown.
Easy and delicious!

title: mary's squash casserole
directions: Mash squash.
Add all other ingredients.
Place in greased casserole and top with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: greek quickie apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients listed in order.
Pour into a lightly buttered or spray-coated 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°, or until lightly brown.

title: green pepper casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Boil 2 cups water and add bouillon cubes.
Add 1 cup rice to 9 x 13-inch pan and pour hot broth over rice.
Put pepper slices over the rice.
Cover with foil and bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, brown ground beef with onions and seasonings.
Drain fat.
Add tomato sauce and mushrooms. Spread this mixture over rice in pan.
Cover and bake another 15 minutes.
Add grated cheese to top and return to oven for 5 minutes, uncovered.
Use any cheese or combination of your choice: Cheddar, Monterey Jack, Co-Jack or Mozzarella.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: texas spiced pecans
directions: Combine sugar, cinnamon, cloves and salt in a large saucepan. Add evaporated milk and vanilla. Cook, stirring constantly, to soft ball stage (234°).
Remove from heat and stir in pecans. Spread out on waxed paper to cool.
Separate when cool.

title: pot roast
directions: Shake flour in a cooking bag; place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Put tomato sauce, salt, pepper and mushroom soup in. Close bag; shake gently to mix.
Trim fat from roast; place in bag.
Peel and quarter potatoes, carrots and
onions; put in bag. Tie bag with nylon tie.
Make six 1/2-inch slits in top of bag. Bake at 350° for 2 3/4 hours.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add frozen strawberries, stir until strawberries are
melted.
Add
mashed
bananas and drained pineapple.
Pour 1/2
mixture in mold and refrigerate. When Jell-O sets, spread sour
cream
on top and add remaining half of mixture.
Let jell in refrigerator.

title: catfish soup
directions: Fry the bacon until crisp, remove and drain on a paper towel. Saute onion in the fat.
In a cooking pot, cover the fish with water; add parsley, salt and pepper.
Simmer until fish pieces are tender.
Melt the butter in a saucepan, stir in the flour and cook for about 1 minute.
Remove this from heat, stir in the milk and add this to the fish soup.
Beat the egg yolks and add 2 tablespoons hot liquid to them and stir into the soup.
Simmer a few minutes, add the bacon and serve.

title: play dough
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heat over medium heat and stir until mixture forms a soft ball.
Put on wax paper and knead.

title: gourmet chicken bake
directions: Place chicken breasts in flat greased baking dish.
Cover chicken pieces with Swiss cheese.
Mix soup and milk and spread over cheese.
Mix oleo and Pepperidge dressing and spread over soup.
Cover with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown beef, onions and pepper; then drain fat off beef.
Boil noodles until tender; drain off water. In pan mix tomato paste and spaghetti sauce until good and thick. Add a dash of garlic salt and oregano to mixture.
In a baking dish, layer in order.
Use a small amount of sauce in bottom of dishes so noodles won't stick.
Next, put a layer of noodles, then sauce, beef mixture and cheese.
Then start all over again until you have used all the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: After dipping chicken pieces in milk, roll in dry ingredients. Place in shallow baking dish.
Drizzle 1/3 cup melted butter or margarine over chicken.
Bake in 375° oven, uncovered, for 50 minutes or until tender.

title: spice cake
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Then add and mix together egg, molasses and milk.
Sift together all dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Serve warm, topped with Cool Whip or sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: good sandwiches
directions: Beat together until well mixed.
Spread on bread.

title: creamy coconut cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Beat well after each addition.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Cut bread into 1/2-inch cubes; set aside.
In a bowl, mix together sugar, eggs, butter and milk.
Add bread cubes.
Pour into a 2-quart baking dish.
Pour the can of pineapple on top. Spread around on top.
Bake at 350° until center is firm and a knife inserted comes out clean, about 1 hour.
Delicious!

title: blueberry dump cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 inch pan. Make a layer of blueberries. Make another layer of the crushed pineapple. Pour dry cake mix over top. Add pecans. pour melted margarine over the top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: "wacky" cake
directions: Combine all the ingredients and sift into ungreased 8-inch square pan.
Make 3 holes in dry ingredients.
In #1 hole, put 1 tablespoon vanilla; in #2 hole, put 1/3 cup oil and in #3 hole, put 1 tablespoon vinegar.
Pour 1 cup of cold water over all.
Mix well with scraper.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp paste
directions: Boil shrimp with bay leaf, salt, pepper and celery.
Grind shrimp and mix with catsup, Worcestershire sauce and enough mayonnaise to make paste.
Good for sandwiches or dip.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix together and bake in greased 9 x 11-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a slight boil. Let simmer 10 minutes.
Pour over chicken, pork, etc.

title: party ham loaf
directions: Combine veal, ham and dry milk.
Blend dry mustard and water. Add to meat mixture with onion, beaten egg, peach juice or syrup from can of peaches, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and ground cloves. Shape in loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fake baked steak
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix together ground beef, eggs, onion, salt, and pepper.
Press meat mixture into 10 by 15-inch cookie sheet with side (jelly roll pan).
Cut meat into serving sized portions.
Dip meat in cracker crumbs, brown in shortening. Place meat in baking dish and pour soup, diluted with water or milk over the meat portions.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Pour into a measuring cup the juice and grated rind of one orange and shortening and add enough hot water to make 3/4 cup liquid.
Add this all to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour for a bread pan and 40 minutes for 2 smaller pans.

title: pretzel dessert
directions: Melt the butter.
Add the crushed pretzels and sugar; mix thoroughly.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: mama's mini cheesecakes
directions: You will need cupcake papers.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix 1/2 cup powdered sugar and the butter. Stir in baking mix, nuts and almond extract.
Mix in enough water to moisten dough.

title: whole wheat bagels
directions: In mixing bowl, mix eggs, salt, honey and melted butter.
Add yeast and warm water.
Mix wheat germ and flours and add to liquid mixture until soft dough is formed.
Turn dough out on floured board, cover with towel and let rest 10 minutes.
Knead dough until smooth and elastic, about 6 to 8 minutes.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover; let rise until doubled in bulk.
Punch dough down. Divide into 12 to 14 equal pieces.
Roll each into a ball and punch hole in center.
Enlarge to form bagel shape.
Cover with towel and let rise again for 30 minutes.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar to water and bring to boil.
Drop bagels in a few at a time.
They will rise to the surface.
Turn over once.
Simmer for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove and pat dry.
Place on greased baking sheet. Brush with glaze made of 1 egg yolk beaten with 1 tablespoon water.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 20 to 25 minutes until golden.

title: aunt jo's no name candy
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in heavy saucepan and cook until 300° on candy thermometer, stirring constantly.
Do not rush boiling and be careful not to burn.
Immediately take off heat and add vanilla.
Quickly pour into buttered 9 x 9 pan.
Lay chocolate bar on top and spread over all as it melts.
Sprinkle nuts on top. Cool until set.
Break into serving size pieces.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy; add sugar, vanilla, oil and zucchini. Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in pineapple, raisins and nuts.
Put in one loaf pan or 2 small loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Remove when brown.

title: great-grandma's tea cakes
directions: Cream eggs, Crisco, sugar and flavoring together.
Add milk. Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet and sprinkle with sugar.
Or may be rolled and cut out as thick or thin as you prefer.
But sprinkle rolled dough with sugar, then cut out.
Bake at 400° about 10 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and blend all ingredients together with a mixer.
Serve with fresh fruit (cantaloupe, honeydew melon, peaches, strawberries, bananas, nectarines and watermelon).

title: corn meal pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add margarine and 1/2 cup sugar.
Mix corn meal and remaining sugar.
Add to egg mixture, add vanilla.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 15 minutes; filling will thicken and crust will be brown.

title: west indies salad
directions: Divide onion in half.
Spread half over bottom of a large bowl.
Separate and spread crab meat over onion.
Spread rest of onion over crab meat.
Salt and pepper.
Pour the remaining ingredients (Wesson oil, vinegar and ice water) over top of onion layer.
Cover and place in refrigerator to marinate 12 to 24 hours.
Toss lightly before serving.
Do not stir.
Follow recipe precisely for best results.

title: pear crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine pears, raisins, 3 tablespoons brown sugar, cinnamon and vanilla in a medium bowl.
Mix gently. Transfer to a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Combine oats, remaining brown sugar, flour, margarine and honey in a bowl.
Mix with a fork until margarine is evenly distributed.
Mixture will be crumbly.
Spoon on top of pear mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes or until browned.
Allow to cool slightly before serving.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding enough whole milk to make mixture have the consistency of cake batter.
Bake at 350° until done in the center and golden brown on top.

title: hushpuppies i
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into balls of desired size and drop in very hot grease.

title: truffles
directions: Melt chocolate over low heat.
Scald whipping cream and let cool until same temperature as melted chocolate.
Melt butter and let cool to same temperature.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover.
Chill.
Makes about 5 1/2 cups.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lentil soup
directions: Dice carrots, celery and onion.
Cut potatoes into 1/2-inch pieces.
Mince garlic.
Heat oil in large pan and cook carrots, celery and onion until tender.
Add garlic and stir just until garlic begins to brown.
Stir in tomatoes with their liquid, chicken broth, potatoes and 3 cups of water.
Stir with spoon to break up tomatoes.
Heat to boil; reduce heat to low, cover and simmer for 50 minutes.
While soup is simmering, thinly slice escarole and stir into soup just before serving.
Cook until escarole wilts.
Serve with breadsticks, if desired.
Makes about five 2-cup servings.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown meat in shortening; add onions and celery.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper and bring to a boil. Place alternate layers of cabbage and meat mixture in buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs and bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
(May add Tabasco sauce.)

title: lacho
directions: Chop the onion.
Slice the meat.
Slice the peppers.
Dump in the cans.
Cook the stuff in a crock-pot on low for 5 to 7 hours or high 4 to 5 hours.

title: jello candy
directions: Pour into pans to chill; don't make thick.

title: italian casserole bread
directions: Dissolve yeast, salt and sugar in water; stir in flour.
Dough will be sticky.
Let rise until double in size.
Stir down and divide dough into 2 well-greased casserole dishes.
Sprinkle with garlic salt on top and let rise to top of dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 400°.

title: grandma ridley's baked beans (sticky beans)
directions: Put beans in a bowl.
Mix everything together except bacon. Pour out into a flat baking dish, slow cooker oven or crock-pot. Bake at 350° until juice is gone.

title: chocolate crinkle cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix oil, sugar and melted chocolate. Blend in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Mix in salt, flour and baking powder.
Chill several hours or overnight (covered). Roll 1 teaspoon dough into ball and roll in powdered sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until firm.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil noodles in chicken broth; salt to taste.
Put noodles in baking dish, then put a layer of noodles, layer chicken, French fried onions, celery and cheese.
Pour celery soup and mushroom soup over layers.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour, covered with tinfoil.

title: barbecue hamburgers
directions: Saute meat, stirring frequently until lightly brown.
Add other ingredients and simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes or longer. Stir occasionally.
Serves 25 people.

title: sugar-free peanut butter pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together in a large bowl. Beat until smooth. Gently fold in Cool Whip. Pour into pie shell and freeze. Take out of freezer 10 minutes before serving.

title: sugar-free ice cream
directions: Mix pudding and sugar substitute in a large mixing bowl. Add the canned milk and vanilla. Mix well. Continue adding skim milk. Stir well. Pour the mixture into freezer container and add milk until almost full. Freeze according to manufacturer's directions.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix together.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: baked cheese and onion spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until bubbly or spread on crackers and broil until bubbly. Variation:
Instead of onion, use bacon bits and horseradish.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Shape into a loaf in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Arrange in casserole in following order:
zucchini, meat mixture and grated cheese.
Pour can of soup over layers.
Sprinkle crumbs over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°; remove cover for last 15 minutes.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute green onions in margarine until tender; add chicken broth and chopped broccoli.
Boil 2 minutes or until done.
Add soups, milk, cheese and seasoned salt.
Heat; do not boil.

title: mulled wine spice mix
directions: Peel rind from oranges in 1/2-inch strips, cutting into white membrane as little as possible.
Reserve orange for another use. Place rind strips, outer side up, on a wire rack on baking sheet.

title: glorified chicken
directions: In skillet, brown chicken in shortening.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes or until done.

title: savory baked beans
directions: Stir all together and pour into a greased, covered casserole dish. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add water and bring to a boil.
Add jello and red food coloring.
Boil until it turns clear red.
Pour over strawberries.
Refrigerate.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale and freeze. Take out 4 to 6 hours before serving to allow some thawing. Add ginger ale and serve.

title: cabbage slaw(can be frozen)
directions: Shred cabbage; add salt and let set 1 hour.
Squeeze out all the liquid, then add the green pepper and carrot.
Combine and boil the vinegar, sugar and spices.
Allow the syrup to cool, then pour over the shredded cabbage and vegetables.
Place in a covered container with a tight lid.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Put ice cream in by spoonful. Add pineapple.
Stir several times before putting in molds.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Mix together. Reserve 1 cup. Pat remaining mixture lightly in an ungreased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in crock-pot (which has been greased with 2 tablespoons of butter).
Cut several thin slices of cheese and place on top of mixture.
Cook 3 1/2 hours on slow.

title: wasp nest cake
directions: Cook pudding as directed on box.
Add cake mix.
Batter will be thick.
Place batter in greased 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle chips on top and then pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: melody fruit and nut cake
directions: Cook fruit in 1 cup water.
Cool.
Mix ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Serve with your favorite topping or ice cream.

title: easy fruit dessert
directions: Pour large can of fruit of your choice in 13 x 9 x 3-inch pan. Remove crust from bread.
Cut bread into 5 strips and place over fruit in rows.
Mix topping and pour over bread. Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: cheese dip
directions: Pour can milk in pan with Velveeta cheese and melt.
Brown ground chuck and drain.
Then add meat and all other ingredients to melted cheese and mix.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients. Mix together the brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour cake batter in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over batter.
Take knife and swirl through cake.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Combine all ingredients in order listed, transfer mix to Bundt pan and bake for 1 hour.

title: apple fritters
directions: Beat egg, add milk.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add diced apples and stir to coat with batter.
Drop by tablespoons into hot oil in skillet.
Fry until brown and turn to brown other side.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve warm with dip of ice cream.

title: speedy spicy chili
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, over medium heat, cook hamburger, onion, garlic and chili powder until hamburger is browned and onion is tender, stirring to separate meat.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in beans, soup, chilies and water.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low. Let simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 4 cups or 4 servings.

title: pepper cheesecake
directions: Combine cream cheese, Cheddar cheese and taco seasoning; beat well (high speed if an electric mixer).
Add eggs (one at a time, beating well after each addition.) Stir in half of sour cream. Fold in chilies and red pepper.
Pour mixture into a greased 10-inch spring-form pan; bake at 350° for 35 minutes (or until set).
Combine remaining half of sour cream and salsa.
Spread mixture evenly over cheesecake.
Bake an additional 5 minutes; let cool in pan on a wire rack.
Cover and chill at least 8 hours.

title: chocolate rock
directions: Line a cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
In a double boiler, melt the semi-sweet and milk chocolates with the oil over hot, not simmering, water, stirring constantly until the chocolate is melted and smooth.
Remove the top part of the double boiler; let the chocolate cool to tepid.
The chocolate may thicken slightly as it cools.
Stir the pecans and chopped white chocolate into the cooled melted chocolate.
Pour the mixture out onto the prepared cookie sheet.
Spread to the desired thickness.
Refrigerate for 20 to 30 minutes, or until set.
Slide a metal spatula under the chocolate to loosen from the foil.
Break into uneven pieces.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crust:
Mix Oreos and melted margarine.
Pat all except 3/4 cup Oreo crumbs in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze for 1 hour.
Soften ice cream.
Spread on crust and freeze.

title: decorator's icing
directions: Place first 3 ingredients in mixer; blend until creamy.
Add confectioners sugar, water and salt. Tint if desired.
Keeps indefinitely in refrigerator.

title: marie's wheat bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water with sugar.
Add rest of ingredients and mix.
Let rise 10 minutes; knead.
Let rise in greased bowl again.
Place in 2 greased loaf pans and let rise.
Bake 45 minutes in 375° oven.

title: "sensational centennial souffle"(grits souffle)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter 2-quart casserole or souffle dish.
Bring water and milk to a boil in a medium saucepan.
Add salt.
Slowly dribble in grits, stirring constantly.
Reduce to simmer, stirring frequently, until mixture thickens.
Add butter and all ingredients except eggs.
Cover and remove from heat. Separate eggs.
Beat egg yolks lightly and add to mixture.
Beat whites until peaks form.
Beat approximately 1/3 of egg whites into mixture and fold in remaining 2/3.
Pour entire mixture into prepared dish and cook about 30 minutes until lightly brown on top.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix flour, soda and spices.
Cream butter, sugar and molasses. Add dry ingredients to butter.
Pour hot water over batter and mix.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes in a 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Cook sausage; drain.
Put sausage, cheese, onions, peppers and flour in a bowl and mix.
Pour into pie shell.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Pour over sausage mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: old fashion chili buns
directions: Mix all ingredients together, mashing hamburger up real good. Stir
and
cook
for
or 3 hours or until thick.
If there is too much grease on top, dip it off.
Can be served on hamburger or	hot
dog
buns	with
mustard,	onions, relish, shredded, Colby cheese or your choice of spread.

title: spinach parmesan and pasta
directions: Microwave frozen spinach until thawed.
Stir-fry spinach, diced onion and diced tomato in olive oil in skillet until hot. Dash with garlic powder and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, grated.

title: open face breakfast sandwiches
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients, mix well.
Spread butter or margarine on each muffin half.
Next, spread approximately 2 tablespoons mixture on each muffin half.
Broil 3 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: far east celery
directions: Cook the celery in a small amount of boiling water until crisp (about 8 minutes); drain.
Mix with the water chestnuts, soup and diced pimiento.
Place in a 1-quart casserole.
Top with the soft breadcrumbs, tossed with the slivered almonds and melted butter. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions, making 2 layers. Cool and slice layers to make 4 layers.

title: pasta fresca with basil
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions, omitting salt. While cooking pasta, prepare sauce.
Heat the olive oil in a large saucepan.
Saute onion and garlic until just tender.
Add tomatoes, parsley and basil; simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain pasta.
Mix with tomato sauce and cheese.
Toss until cheese is melted.
Sprinkle generously with freshly ground pepper.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: corned beef reuben casserole
directions: Mix kraut, onion and sour cream.
Put mixture in a greased 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Put corned beef over kraut mixture. Then layer the Swiss cheese and on top, the rye bread.
Drizzle with butter over bread.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cream blueberry muffins(makes 24)
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake at 375°.

title: oatmeal brownies
directions: Combine sugar, water, vegetable oil and vanilla in a medium bowl. Stir well. Add egg whites and stir well.
Combine flour and next 4 ingredients.
Add to sugar mixture, stirring well.
Pour batter into an 8-inch square baking pan coated with cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 23 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool. Sprinkle with sugar.
Yields 12 servings (about 126 calories per 2 1/2 x 2-inch bar).
Protein 2.4, fat 4.1, carbohydrate 20.1, cholesterol 0, iron 0.7, sodium 52 and calcium 19.

title: chocolate bark
directions: Place
chocolate
morsels
in glass bowl.
Microwave on High for
minutes.
Stir
in	nuts.
Spread on cookie sheet covered with
wax paper and place in refrigerator until hard, then break into chunks.
Keep in tin in refrigerator.	Time of preparation: 5 or 10 minutes.

title: easiest peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine peanut butter and sugar in bowl; mix well.
Mix in egg.
Drop by small spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Press lightly with fork in crisscross design.
Bake at 375° until light brown.
Yields 36 cookies.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Mix.
Bake on greased pans at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peach dupplings
directions: Peel and quarter peaches.
Roll peaches up in crescent rolls and put into baking dish.
Bring 1 cup of sugar, water and butter to boil.
Pour over peach rolls.
Sprinkle rolls with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: grandma jackie's cheese rolls
directions: Cut rolls in half lengthwise and remove most of the soft center bread from both top and bottom halves.
(Dry these crumbs and use in other cooking.)
Mix all other ingredients in a large bowl.
Fill centers of rolls with cheese mixture, replacing tops on bottoms.
Place roll in a wax paper sandwich bag and twist top of bag closed or wrap roll in waxed paper, twisting ends tightly to seal.
Do not use plastic bags or wrap.
Place as many as desired in a brown paper bag and heat in a 350° oven for about 20 minutes.
Store unused rolls in refrigerator or freezer.
When wanted, just place in a brown bag for oven.
No defrosting required.
Do not heat in microwave; it makes them soft instead of crunchy.

title: cover-up watergate cake
directions: Mix together and beat.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: italian chicken wings
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine oil and chili powder in jelly roll pan.
Heat for 5 minutes.
Combine other ingredients and put in pan.
Place wings in hot pan.
Bake 1 hour or until tender, turning once or twice.
Serves 4.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix together and put in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients plus pepper and garlic and form into balls.
In large skillet, combine remaining ingredients. Simmer until smooth.
Add meatballs to skillet.
Do not brown meatballs before adding.
Simmer 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.

title: garden vegetable sauce
directions: Half squash lengthwise and slice thin.
Cut asparagus in 1-inch pieces (1 cup).
Combine in a large saucepan with undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, mint and sugar.
Bring to boiling and reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 5 to 7 minutes, more or less, until squash and asparagus are tender.
Serve over hot fettuccine pasta.

title: dilly casserole bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Warm the cheese and add the sugar, onion, butter, dill, salt, soda, egg and yeast.
Mix.
Add the flour to make a stiff dough, beating well after each addition. Cover.
Let rise in a warm place until light and double in size (50 to 60 minutes).
Stir down dough.

title: venison ribswaterford, michigan
directions: Marinate ribs in dressing overnight.
Drain ribs and put in crock pot.
Add 1/4 c. marinate back into ribs and cover with saurkraut.
Cook on low all day.

title: coffee cake
directions: Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle with flour mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Bake at 300° for 3 hours or cook on stove top on medium, then simmer. Stir often.

title: delicious strawberry cake
directions: Beat egg whites; set aside.
Mix all other ingredients well. Fold in egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 2 (9-inch) pans.
Let cool and split in half to make 4 layers.

title: grandma westermeyer's krummel cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cinnamon and shortening. Reserve one cup of mixture for crumb topping.
Add eggs, milk, baking soda and salt. Mix well.
Pour into 2
nine inch round cake pans. Sprinkle crumb mixture on top.
Bake in a 350 degree oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until knife or toothpick comes out clean.

title: baked beans
directions: Drain beans; put in pot.
Combine in a cup:
molasses, brown sugar and dry mustard.
Fill the cup with water and mix well. Pour on top of beans.
Add a small onion and salt pork to bean pot and then fill with water 1 inch over the beans.
Bake at 375° for 4 hours.

title: creamy cheesecake
directions: Beat eggs and combine with softened cream cheese.
Add the rest of the ingredients to the mixture.
Beat together.
Spread mixture evenly on greased glass pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Mix everything together, except sour cream, to layer between tortillas. Put small layer of sour cream under top layer of tortilla and cover top of tortillas with shredded cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cut like a pizza and serve.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and dice.
Add all other ingredients and fold together.
Top with sliced egg and paprika.
Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.

title: pan toasted garlic bread
directions: In 10-inch skillet, melt butter until sizzling.
Stir in pepper and garlic.
Dip both sides of each bread slice in melted butter; place in same skillet.
Cook over medium heat, watching closely, until bread is lightly browned, 2 to 3 minutes.
Reduce heat to low.
Turn bread slices over and sprinkle each with about 1 teaspoon cheese.
Cover.
Continue cooking until cheese is melted, 1 to 2 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Place sherbet in punch bowl.
Pour cranberry juice over as needed.

title: not fried-fried chicken wings
directions: Set oven to 375° to preheat.
Spray baking sheet (cookie sheet size) with no-fat vegetable cooking spray graciously (pass over 2 to 3 times).
Set aside.

title: sin
directions: Cool cake.
In large bowl, crumble 1/2 of cake.
Sprinkle with Kahlua to taste.
Spread 1/2 of pudding on top of cake.
Spoon 1/2 of whipped cream on top of pudding.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of crushed candy.
Repeat layers.
Refrigerate.
Best if refrigerated overnight before serving.

title: grandmother's jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add eggs and cream well.
Blend in jam.
Sift	together flour, salt and spices.
Add the soda to buttermilk.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with the buttermilk, ending with dry mixture.
Fold in pecans
and raisins; pour into 4 cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash with onion in salted boiling water until tender. Drain off water and mash squash.
Add soup, garlic powder, black pepper, egg, Parmesan cheese and crushed crackers.
Mix well and pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish which has been sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with cheese and onion rings.
Return to oven for 5 minutes to melt cheese.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
In large baking dish, place chicken and vegetables.
In bowl, mix chicken broth and soups.
Pour over chicken.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Spray pan lightly with Pam or butter.
Layer chicken, cheese, soups (with 1/2 can water) and Pepperidge Farm dressing (approximately 2 cups).
Melt butter, pour over and bake at 375°, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: carousel salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; do not chill. While still hot, drizzle with oil and vinegar.
Add onion and seasoning; toss well.
Gently mix in peas and remaining ingredients.
Eat while warm or chill and serve cold.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all together and let stand overnight or 4 hours.
(For raw vegetables, one bunch.)

title: old fashioned pot roast
directions: In Dutch oven, brown beef; add soup mix blended with water. Simmer, covered, turning occasionally 2 1/2 hours or until beef is tender.
If desired, thicken gravy.

title: blender coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend at low speed for 1 minute.
Pour into buttered pie pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix well and bake in a shallow 9 x 13 pan, greased. Cover with Streusel Topping before putting in oven. Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown and drain hamburger; add garlic powder, salt, pepper and tomato sauce and simmer for 15 to 30 minutes.
Heat tortillas in microwave, put 2 tablespoons meat mixture in each tortilla.
Add some Longhorn cheese, onion and refried beans (heated).
Roll each tortilla up and hold together with a toothpick.
After tortillas are prepared, pour enchilada sauce over all and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until it starts to bubble.
You can also add sour cream and black olives.

title: peanut butter tandy cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a jelly roll cake pan (9 x 13-inch).
Beat together sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla. Slowly add flour, salt, baking powder and milk.
Bake for approximately 25 minutes. While cake is hot, spoon peanut butter, in small amounts, over cake.
Place cake in freezer until peanut butter has hardened.
Melt Hershey chocolate bar with Crisco in microwave.
Spread chocolate over cooled cake.
After chocolate has hardened, cut into squares.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix your flour and sugar in a bowl.
Mix Crisco oil, butter or margarine, cocoa and Coca-Cola together in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add flour and sugar mixture; beat very good.
Then add egg, baking soda, vanilla, marshmallows and buttermilk.
Beat very good.
Bake for 45 minutes in greased pan in the oven at 300°.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding as directed on box.
Add pineapple.
Add whipped cream topping.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Use pineapple juice, if needed.
You can add Philadelphia cream cheese for better flavor.

title: "sin" butter
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix with electric mixer very well. Put in airtight plastic container and store in the refrigerator. Yields 16 ounces.

title: chicken las vegas
directions: Salt and pepper chicken; place in a baking dish.
Mix up soup and sour cream.
Wrap bacon around each breast with ham "tucked" in underside of breast.
Pour soup mixture over.
Bake, uncovered, at 275° for 3 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry pound cake
directions: Put cake mix, jello, eggs, oil and strawberries in mixing bowl; mix well for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Cook in well-greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.
Let cake cool slightly, then turn out of pan.

title: chicken and spaghetti casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Pour in a greased casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring margarine, water and cocoa to a boil.
Pour in bowl and add flour, sugar and salt.	Beat well and add eggs, sour cream and baking soda.
Pour batter into greased and floured 12 x 18-inch cookie sheet (or other shallow pan) and bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: fried squash bread
directions: Stew squash and onion until done, mash well.
Stir in beaten eggs.
Add salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Add flour and meal. Add enough water to make into consistency to drop by tablespoonfuls into hot grease until browned.

title: peanut pattie candy
directions: Bring sugar, water and syrup to boil.
Add peanuts and coloring.
Cook over medium heat to 250° or hard-ball.
Remove from heat and add butter, salt and vanilla.
Beat until thick. Pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
Let cool and break into pieces.

title: pickled okra
directions: Pack okra in sterilized pint jars.
Heat water and vinegar. Bring to a boil.
Put seasoning over okra.
Pour vinegar and water mixture into jars.
Seal.
This takes 2 to 3 weeks to pickle properly.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Bring water, salt, butter and onion salt to boil.
Add potatoes, sour cream, cream cheese and milk.
Bake in buttered baking dish with grated Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake approximately 20 minutes at 325° until hot.
Add Cheddar cheese to top and broil until cheese is melted and slightly brown.
Serves 8 people.

title: irish beef stew
directions: Combine beef and gravy, peas, Worcestershire sauce and celery seed in saucepan or baking dish.
Heat thoroughly.
Put in large dish or platter.
Make a hole in the center and add cooked rice. Serve with cole slaw.
Makes a delicious meal. This can be prepared ahead of time and reheated.

title: roux
directions: Put oil in heavy iron pot over medium heat.
When oil is hot, stir flour in gradually.
Lower heat.
It is very important that you keep stirring constantly.
After all the flour has been combined with the oil, turn fire down very low and cook until golden brown, stirring constantly.
When roux is golden brown, pour the mixture into another container, until ready for use.
Roux will get too dark if it remains in the pot in which it was prepared.

title: sticky buns
directions: Grease 9
x
13-inch
pan.
Put pecans in bottom.
Tear dough into
walnut
size	pieces	and put in single layer over pecans. Mix rest of ingredients together and pour over dough. Refrigerate overnight.	Bake
in morning at 350° for 1/2 hour. Invert and serve warm.

title: tapioca dessert
directions: Mix puddings, jello and water, bring to boil.
Cook until mixture begins to thicken.
Cool.
Fold in Cool Whip and fruit. Chill. Any fruit and flavor of jello may be used.

title: cream cheese wontons
directions: In a large bowl, combine cream cheese, sugar and chives, mixing until well smooth.
Place a small spoonful of the mixture in the center of each wrapper (follow folding instructions on the wonton package).
Preheat peanut oil to 375° in a deep pan. Deep-fry wontons until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels. Serve hot.
Makes 48 wontons.

title: onions au gratin
directions: Cook sliced onions in salted water for 10 minutes.
Drain, reserving 1/4 c. liquid for the sauce.
Place onions in buttered baking dish.
Blend melted butter and flour in a saucepan.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in milk and onion liquid.
Continue to stir and cook on low heat until thick.
Remove from heat, add cheese, and stir until it is melted.
Pour over onions and with a fork help sauce to flow down through onions.
Top with crumbs and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
This may be made ahead and stored in refrigerator until baking time.

title: roasted potatoes with rosemary and garlic
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut potatoes in quarters.
Place them in a bowl and add 1 1/2 teaspoons fresh rosemary or 1/2 teaspoon dried.
Pour 2 1/2 teaspoons olive oil over them.
Toss them until they are well coated and the rosemary is well distributed.
Place them on a baking sheet in a single layer and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Roast for 15 minutes, turning every 5 minutes.

title: spinach roll-ups
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
Stir together first 6 ingredients. Evenly spread onto flour tortillas.
Roll up, jellyroll fashion, pressing edges to seal.
Wrap in plastic wrap.
Chill 4 to 6 hours.
Cut into 1/2-inch thick slices.

title: broiled fish steaks
directions: Preheat broiler.
Rinse fish and pat dry.
Lightly coat both sides of each fish piece with mayonnaise.
Place in a shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with half of the Lemon Herb Seasoning and paprika.
Broil 3 to 4 minutes.
Turn fish and sprinkle with remaining seasonings.
Broil for another 3 to 4 minutes or until fish flakes when tested with a fork or is no longer translucent. Garnish with lemon slices and a sprig of fresh parsley.
Serve immediately.

title: stir-fry deer meat
directions: Cut meat into 1/2-inch strips, 3 to 4 inches in length.
You may want to use a meat cleaver to tenderize.
Place meat in 1/2 cup oil.
Cook until done to avoid bitter taste.
Add pepper and onion; continue frying on medium heat until done.
It goes good with rice.

title: cheese-sausage balls
directions: Mix all 3 ingredients well into a large ball.
Pinch off into small balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 125 to 175 balls.
(Mix may be frozen before cooked and stored until needed.)

title: pumpkin pie(fat-free, sugar-free)
directions: Mix pudding mix and milk.
Add pumpkin and mix well.
Add spice and liquid sweetener and mix well.
Pour into baked shell and chill.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream
butter
and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour, soda,
vanilla, lemon juice and sour cream.
Mix well. Bake in Bundt
pan	at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Remove from Bundt pan to cool.

title: glorified rice
directions: Gently mix pineapple, marshmallows, sugar and rice.
Add vanilla to whipped topping.
Fold into rice mixture.
Chill. Serves 8.

title: peach or apple crunch
directions: Put apples or peaches and juice in buttered dish.
Mix sugar, flour and egg.
Sprinkle over fruit.
Melt the butter and pour over top.
Bake until brown at 350° to 375°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Soften ice cream slightly; stir in peanut butter and fold in whipped cream until well blended.
Spoon into a chilled unbaked 9-inch graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over top.
Freeze.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine, 1 egg and nuts until crumbly.
Pour into long 9x13-inch pan.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs until smooth.
Pour this over crumbly mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: barbecued beans
directions: Boil cabbage 10 minutes in salt and water.
Drain.
Put on butter, nutmeg, milk and pepper.

title: lipton pot roast
directions: In Dutch oven, brown roast.
Add soup mix blended with 2 cups water. Simmer, covered, turning occasionally, 2 hours.
Cut potatoes into 1-inch pieces and slice carrots thinly.
Add to roast and cook an additional 30 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Remove roast and vegetables.
Blend 1/2 cup water with flour. Stir into Dutch oven. Bring to a boil, then simmer, stirring constantly, until thickened, about 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour, salt, vanilla and sugar.
Grease and flour large stem pan. Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Slice the zucchini in apple size slices; toss them in lemon juice.
Add dash of cinnamon and a little salt.
Pile the mixture into an unbaked pie shell.
Top it with the margarine, flour, sugar and a sprinkling of cinnamon mixed together.
Bake as you would for ordinary apple pie at 425° for 40 minutes.
Cover the rims of your crust with aluminum foil if crust gets too brown.

title: funnel cake
directions: Use a glass pie plate or dull metal pie pan.
Shiny metal pans keep the crust from browning nicely and should be used only for crumb crusts that are not baked.

title: pineapple cream salad
directions: Mix pineapple, sugar and lemon juice; boil 2 minutes.
Mix jello in the 1/2 cup cold water.
Add to the cooked mixture. Blend in the cream cheese.
Place in refrigerator until partially set. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in dish and refrigerate overnight.

title: noodle bake
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain.
Add condensed tomato soup and water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add cheese.
Put in greased baking dish.
Add to cooked noodles.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chicken divan(350 calories per serving)
directions: Brown chicken in oil, stirring occasionally.
Add water, wine, broccoli and soup.
Bring to full boil, separating broccoli pieces.
Stir in rice.
Cover; remove from heat and let stand for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Pour popped corn into brown paper grocery bag.
Take butter, brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Mix together in a bowl.
Cook syrup mixture on High power for 2 minutes; stir.
Cook 2 minutes longer.
Stir in baking soda.
Pour mixture over popcorn.
Shake bag extremely well and microwave on High power for 1 1/2 minutes. Shake extremely well again.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes again. Repeat process once more.
Cool and enjoy.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Place the mixture in casserole dish.
Add the vegetable next, then cover with mashed potatoes. Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and cheese is browned.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Stir together.
Put in ice cream freezer; add milk to fill line.
Add salt (rock) and ice to freezer and crank, crank, crank.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa. Add milk and well beaten egg yolks. Cook until thick, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla. Pour into baked pie shell. Top with Meringue.

title: pecan pie
directions: This makes
a
crunchy pecan
pie.
If your desire more syrupy and gooey, then
just
add	1/4 more syrup and 1/4 more sugar to the same other ingredients.

title: extra large pound cake
directions: Cream oleo, Crisco and sugar until very smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Sift flour, salt and mace. Add alternately with milk and almond and lemon extract.
Cook in 325° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Do not open for entire time.

title: potato stretcher
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Slice potatoes thin.
Dip potatoes in batter and fry in medium-hot oil or grease until golden brown.

title: cavetelli con pomadoro
directions: Melt margarine in large pan.
Brown minced garlic in margarine. Remove from heat and stir in half and half, heat through.
Stir in Parmesan cheese and melt.
Stir in parsley.
Stir in tomato and heat through.
Stir in cooked and drained cavetelli.
Serve with a little parsley sprinkled on top for garnish.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, beat the brown sugar, sugar, margarine and shortening until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and egg; beat well.
Lightly spoon flour into mixture. Stir chocolate chips and nuts into mixture, then spoon onto cookie sheet.
Cook for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: tex-mex chicken
directions: Boil chicken and take meat off bones. Place taco chips in a 13x9x2 inch pan or baking dish. In a separate pot saute onions in butter until tender and add chili peppers, milk, mushroom and chicken soup until heated. Place chicken over the chips and then pour liquid over the chicken. Put grated cheese on top and place in oven until cheese melts.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix all ingredients (except chips and wax) together with spoon.
Form small balls on cookie sheet and chill in refrigerator until firm.

title: ground beef and dressings casserole
directions: In a buttered dish (2-quart size), place 1/2 of bread stuffing.
Add meat; season with salt and pepper and add mushroom soup, also milk, heated together.
Repeat these layers.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 350°.

title: english toffee
directions: Line 8 x 10-inch ungreased pan with almonds.
Cook together brown sugar and butter for 12 minutes.
After it comes to a slow rolling boil (not stirring), pour hot mixture over nuts.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top immediately.
Put cookie sheet on top of this until chocolate melts.
Then spread with knife.
Place in refrigerator until hard.
Cut in squares and store in refrigerator.

title: deviled almonds
directions: Melt margarine in a medium saucepan.
Stir in celery salt, chili powder and ground red pepper.
Add almonds, stirring until nuts are evenly coated.
Transfer nuts to a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until nuts are lightly toasted, stirring once.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Turn out onto paper towels to finish cooling.
Store tightly covered. Makes 2 cups.

title: pasta and peppers
directions: Cook the pasta according to package directions.
Drain, reserving some of the fluid.
Place in a large pasta bowl.
Set aside.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Brown the ground beef and mix with taco mix. Put refried beans in the bottom of an 11 x 7 pan, top with ground beef, then sour cream, then salsa and sprinkle cheese over all. Put in 350 degree oven until cheese melts.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and roll into small balls. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Roll in extra powdered sugar while hot and again when cool.

title: 4 layer dessert
directions: Mix together until like coarse meal.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Let cool.

title: crusty potato tidbits
directions: Scrub potatoes; cut into quarters.
Place in a large saucepan. Cover with 1/2-inch salted water; cover and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, about 20 minutes or until tender; peel potatoes and place in large bowl.
Mash with electric mixer, gradually beating in milk, butter, salt and pepper.
Add cheese and onion; blend well.
Shape potato mixture into 1-inch balls; dip balls in eggs, then roll in crushed cornflakes.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until balls are hot and crusty.
Makes about 70 balls.

title: aunt helen's broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Saute thawed broccoli and chopped onion in 1 tablespoon oil for 5 minutes.
Add soup and milk.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add cheese and allow to melt.
Add cooked rice.
Put in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with more cheese.
Heat in the oven until hot and bubbly around the edge.

title: caramel icing(good on angel food cake)
directions: Cook until it forms a soft ball in cold water.

title: potatoes in herbed sauce
directions: Slice potatoes in 1/2-inch thick slices and cook in salted water until slightly soft.
Melt butter in large skillet.
Add leek and onion; cook 1 minute.
Add finely chopped boiled ham and stir.
Lower heat.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Put the sugar, cinnamon, butter, water and nutmeg in saucepan and boil.
Keep hot to pour over wrapped apples just before baking.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Roll chicken pieces in flour, salt and pepper.
Fry in hot oil until brown.
Add soup and water.
Lay biscuits around the top of chicken.
Simmer for 1 hour, or until done

title: chicken divan
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, arrange broccoli spears horizontally in 2 rows, with stalks facing each other in center of dish.
Spoon chicken on top of stalk ends and top chicken with cheese and sliced mushrooms.
Set aside.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Partially thaw broccoli and combine with other ingredients, except Cheez Whiz.	Stir
well.
Place
in buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish and dot with Cheez Whiz.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs well; blend in other ingredients and mix well. Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes its own crusts.

title: chunky german potato salad
directions: Boil whole potatoes, drain and cool.
Fry bacon to crisp.
Cut in small pieces.
Dice onions and eggs.
Peel cooled potatoes and cube.
Add bacon, onions, eggs and mayonnaise.
Chill and serve.

title: plantation walnuts
directions: Cook until sugar thickens and slides off spoon.
Pour walnuts in.

title: grape cup(serves 4)
directions: Combine juice and liqueur.
Stir in fruits, except 4 small grape clusters.
Chill thoroughly.
Garnish each serving with small cluster of grapes.
Contains about 130 calories per serving.

title: microwave baked stuffed potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and pierce with a fork on both sides. Cook in microwave, uncovered, about 5 minutes on each side or until soft. Let stand 5 minutes.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix gelatin, pineapple and boiling water.
Refrigerate until it sets.
Top with can of filling.
Cover with Cool Whip.

title: kimpira gobo(fried burdock)
directions: Cut 1 pound gobo thin, like matchsticks.
Soak in water for 15 to 20
minutes;
drain.
Put 1 tablespoon oil in frying pan; saute gobo	for
5	to
minutes.
Add carrots, shoyu, sugar, shrimp and	aji.
Cook
until
sauce
is absorbed.	Add chili pepper if desired.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together. Dough will be stiff. Shape into balls. Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and place in casserole dish.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and onion and pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese, then stuffing on top.
Bake 30 minutes (or until heated through) at 350°.
Can be prepared the day before, refrigerate and bake an extra 15 minutes.

title: barb's chili
directions: In a Dutch oven, saute first four ingredients in hot oil until tender.
Add meat, 1 pound at a time, stirring until meat loses redness.
Drain.
Add water.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring after each addition.
Simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours, stirring frequently.
Season to taste with garlic, salt and pepper, if desired.

title: holiday confetti salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Chill until it begins to thicken.
Whip pineapple and cream cheese together until smooth and add with diced celery, nuts and cherries to gelatin mixture.
Whip cream and fold into gelatin mixture.
Chill.

title: cherokee
directions: You can also use any other vegetables that you think would suit!

title: chocolate peach flan
directions: Combine crumbs, butter, sugar, and almonds.
Press evenly into bottom and sides of a 9 inch pan or pie plate.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: roast lamb with orzo
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic in butter or oil.
When meat is brown, add wine and spices and cook about 20 minutes.
Transfer meat into baking pan with 1 cup of warm water.
Bake at 400° until meat is done.
Remove meat from pan and keep warm.

title: crab spread
directions: Use fork to mash it altogether.
Put in ovenproof bowl.
Bake at 375° for approximately 15 minutes.

title: pumpernickel rye bread
directions: Combine sugar, yeast and 1/2 cup warm water; set aside.
Over low heat, mix beer, butter and molasses until very warm.
Combine 3 cups rye flour, 1 cup white flour and salt.
With mixer on low, gradually add liquid to dry ingredients, increasing speed to medium and beating for 2 minutes.
With spoon, stir in yeast mixture, 4 cups white flour and caraway seed.
Dough will be sticky.

title: all purpose stew
directions: Brown meat in frying pan with onion until tender.
Take 2 cups of water and add carrots, potatoes, peas, green pepper and bay leaf.
Let simmer until vegetables start to get done.
Then add garlic, pepper, catsup and meat.
Let simmer, then mix 1 cup of water with a 1/2 cup of flour.
Add to stew and let cook until thickened.

title: pumpkin bread with glaze
directions: Combine pumpkin, eggs, oil and water.
Mix well.
Add orange peel and mix.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add nuts to pumpkin mixture and mix.
Add to dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 70 minutes or until done.
Bread springs back when lightly touched in the center.
Cool for 15 minutes in pans. Remove bread and cool on wire rack.
Glaze cooled loaves.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well.
Roll into small balls. Roll balls in chopped nuts or Rice Krispies.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Melt shortening; remove from heat and cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg; beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to first mixture; mix well.
Chill for an hour or more.

title: creme vichyssoise
directions: Slightly brown onions in butter.
Add potatoes, broth and salt.
Bring to boiling point, then cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Cool and puree in blender.
Add milk, heat to boiling point, remove from heat and add cream and other ingredients.
Mix well; chill.
Serve very cold and garnish with chopped chives.

title: putting on the ritz
directions: Mix seasonings and salad oil.
Toss with Ritz.
Dry on paper towels.

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: Prick pie shell thoroughly with fork.
Bake at 425° for about 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from oven.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Melt chocolate with butter in saucepan over very low heat, stirring constantly until smooth.
Cool slightly.
Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, salt, corn syrup, milk and vanilla.
Beat in chocolate, then pour into partially baked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until top puffs and begins to crack.
Cool.
Center of pie will fall slightly.
Just before serving, fill center with sweetened whipped cream.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat (1/2 sausage and 1/2 hamburger may be used).
Drain and add to tomatoes, tomato paste, salt, basil and garlic.
Simmer 15 minutes.
*Italian sauce may be used.
Cook 10 ounces lasagne noodles in boiling salted water.
Combine eggs, Ricotta, Parmesan, parsley, salt and pepper.
Spread 1 cup sauce in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Layer 1/3 of noodles over sauce.
Spread 1/2 of egg mixture, 1/2 pound grated Mozzarella cheese, 1/3 meat mixture.
Repeat layers, ending with layer of noodles, then sauce. Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and sprinkle with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese and bake for 10 to 15 more minutes.

title: dill pickles
directions: Place dill, grape leaf, red hot pepper, alum and garlic powder all in each jar.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix oil, vinegar, sugar, water, salt and pepper together. Pour over vegetables and mix.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cherry sauce for baked ham
directions: Drain cherries, reserving syrup.
Combine cherry syrup in saucepan with cornstarch, sugar, vinegar, water and spices.
Cook stirring constantly until thick and clear.
Add wine and cherries. Use part of sauce to glaze ham during baking.
Serve remaining sauce warm or chilled with ham.

title: chicken breasts with bacon
directions: Cream together the cheese and chopped onion, then form it into 6 walnut size balls. Wrap a chicken breast around each one, then wrap 2 slices of bacon around the bundle in such a way as to cover as much of the chicken as possible.
Secure each little bundle with a toothpick or two.
Broil them on a rack with a drip pan beneath the broiler unit.
Turn the chicken breasts occasionally, as needed. Broil them about 30 minutes or until the bacon is well done.

title: tarty cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften while chopping up chipped beef and green onions.
(You may use a blender.)
Set aside some chipped beef to roll the cheese ball in.
Mix all the ingredients by hand and roll into a ball.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: three-bean hot dish
directions: Brown bacon.
Brown hamburger and onion together.
Drain off fat.
Drain kidney beans and add kidney beans and butter beans. Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour, covered, and 1/2 hour uncovered.

title: lyn's strawberry applesauce bread
directions: Mix ingredients well in a large bowl.
Bake in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: gone-all-day stew
directions: Mix together tomato soup, water or wine and flour until smooth. Combine with remaining ingredients in covered roasting pan.
Bake at 275° for 4 to 5 hours.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Chill and serve on a bed of lettuce.

title: great garlic bread
directions: Preheat grill. Combine first 3 ingredients and spread between bread slices. Reassemble loaf and wrap in heavy-duty aluminum foil. Place on grill rack over medium-hot coals (350° to 400°). Cook 7 to 8 minutes on each side or until thoroughly heated. Makes 8 servings.

title: sunday beef bake
directions: Pour mushroom soup over beef in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, then onion soup mix.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours.
Serve over hot buttered noodles or rice.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into greased muffin pan or sheet pan.
Bake at 350.
If in muffin pan, bake for 30 minutes. If in sheet pan, bake for 1 hour.

title: bread
directions: Mix milk and oleo and warm.
Combine 2 cups of flour, sugar, salt and yeast; add warmed milk mixture. Mix well with mixer.
Add 1/2 cup flour at a time.
Beat with wooden spoon until mixture leaves the sides of the bowl.
Put mixture out on board and knead until elastic.
Let rise, punch down and form.
Let rise again. Bake at 325° for glass pans or 350° for metal, 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pickled fish
directions: Step 1:
Filet and skin salmon.
Cut into 1-inch cubes.
Soak in brine of 1 1/2 cups salt and 4 quarts water.
Refrigerate 48 hours.

title: italian fish
directions: Marinate fish in dressing overnight.
To cook, bake at 375° to 400°.
Place fish and some of the dressing in glass baking dish. Dot with butter.
Cover with foil.
Bake 15 to 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily.

title: rhubarb-raspberry crisp
directions: In large bowl, combine rhubarb, sugar, orange juice and peel. In another bowl combine flour, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in butter as for pastry.
Add oats and pecans; mix well.
Turn rhubarb mixture into an 8-inch square baking pan.
Sprinkle evenly with raspberries.
Cover with crumb topping.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 9 servings.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
No need to cook.
Absorb moisture. Mix all ingredients and refrigerate several hours before serving. Serve with chips or crackers.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together; pat into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: coconut balls
directions: Heat corn syrup and mix with coconut.
Put into refrigerator and let cool until cold enough to stick together.
Dip into chocolate and paraffin.

title: slaw
directions: Bring last 5 ingredients to a boil.
Cool completely and pour over cabbage mixture. This will keep several weeks in refrigerator.

title: california chicken salad
directions: Sprinkle lemon juice over chicken and apple, mixing lightly. Combine remaining ingredients, using only enough mayonnaise to moisten.
Add chicken and apples; toss together lightly.
Serve cold with mayonnaise.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown and drain hamburger, sausage, onion, green pepper and bacon.
Cook noodles and drain.
Mix together with remaining ingredients except cheese.
Put into casserole pan.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: marie's special italian ricotta cookies
directions: Allow butter to soften.
Blend in Ricotta until creamy.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Add sugar gradually, beating until well blended.
Add egg and mix well.
Slowly stir in dry ingredients and blend well.
Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch dish.
Layer vegetables in order.
Mix mayo and sugar, then spread over salad.
Add grated cheese on top of mayo. Slice eggs and put on top of cheese.
Chill.

title: cheese bread
directions: Mix cheese, mayo, onion and garlic powder; spread onto bread. Sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight or at least 6 to 8 hours.
Bake, uncovered, 15 to 30 minutes or until cheese melts and bubbles.

title: best zucchini bars
directions: Beat together sugar, oil and eggs in large bowl or food processor.
Beat in flour, cinnamon, salt, soda, baking powder and vanilla.
Beat 1 to 2 minutes until well mixed.
Fold in zucchini, carrots, oats and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin pecan cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts and beat for 5 minutes. Fold in chopped pecans.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: mexican chicken and rice
directions: Heat oil in skillet on medium to medium high heat.
Add chicken, onion, and bell pepper.
Cook and stir until chicken is cooked through.
Add corn, chicken broth, and salsa.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and cover.
Let stand 2 minutes till cheese melts.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Toast almonds and sesame seeds in oven at 350° for 3 to 4 minutes until slightly browned.

title: hot fruit compote
directions: Layer fruit in a sprayed (Pam) baking dish.
Mix together brown sugar, curry powder and melted butter.
Pour this mixture over the layered fruit.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Refrigerate overnight.
Reheat at 350° for 30 minutes before serving.
This is best made a day earlier than you expect to serve.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Pour off liquid; rinse pickles and dry. Cut in 1/3 to 1/4 inch slices. Mix sugar, vinegar, whole cloves, water, cinnamon sticks and bay leaves. Boil for 5 minutes. Pour over pickles (placed in jar). Replace lid. Turn upside down until cooled. Refrigerate.

title: puppy chow(good and easy!)
directions: Melt together.
Pour mixture over 1 medium box of Crispix. Place mixture in a paper bag with the powdered sugar and shake. Then eat.

title: sue's e. z. etouffee
directions: Saute onion in margarine until clear.
Add cream of celery soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Simmer for at least 1 hour, the longer, the better.
Add crawfish or shrimp; heat until ready.
Very e.z.

title: venison stew
directions: Place meat into an earthen jar.
Cover with vinegar, onions and bay leaves.
Allow to stand at least 2 days.
Remove meat from jar and wash it with cold water.
Place in pot.
Cover with boiling water; simmer slowly until tender.
Remove meat.
Mix flour with a little water; add to liquid in pot, stirring until thickened.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: scrambled egg bake
directions: Grease 9 x 13 pan. Tear up the slices of bread and set aside. Beat eggs with fork. Add milk. Brown and drain sausage (or can add sliced and sauteed mushrooms and green pepper). Add to eggs. Grate mild Cheddar cheese. Combine bread, milk, eggs, sausage and cheese and pour into pan. Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: corn
directions: In 6 to 8-quart pan, bring 4 quarts water to a boil over high heat.
Add corn; cover and cook until hot (2 to 3 minutes).
Drain and arrange in a 9 x 13-inch dish or rimmed serving platter.
In same pan, combine vinegar, onion, sugar, pimentos, mustard seeds, red pepper and salt.
Bring to a boil over high heat and cook, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
pour over corn; let stand until cool, spooning mixture over corn frequently.
If made ahead, cover and refrigerate for up to 6 hours.
Serve at room temperature as finger food.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: helen's country biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 475°.
In a bowl, rub flour and shortening together with hands until mixture looks like meal.
Add buttermilk and stir until it forms a ball.
Turn dough onto a floured surface. Knead lightly until dough is no longer sticky.
Roll out and cut into 16 biscuits.
Roll dough into 1/4-inch thick if biscuits are to be folded over.
Bake 8 minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain green beans and carrots.
Marinate overnight in vinegar, sugar and vegetable oil.
Onion may be sliced and placed on top or cut fine and added to mixture.
Next day, add drained peas, celery, bell pepper and mayonnaise to mix.
Place in refrigerator to cool for 1 hour before serving.

title: ham appetillas
directions: Remove tortillas from refrigerator.
Allow them to reach room temperature.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, onion and olives. Spread thin layer on tortilla.
Arrange 4 slices of ham over cheese.
Roll up tightly.
Wrap individually in plastic wrap. Chill 3 hours.
Slice 3/4-inch thick.
Serve.
Makes about 64.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix in blender. Fry thin.

title: napoleon bars
directions: In double boiler mix first 4 ingredients until melted.
Then add egg.
Cook until thick, about 1 minute.
Take off heat.
Stir in the last 2 ingredients.

title: herbed potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes and dice; cook in salted water until just tender.
Drain, then add the rest of ingredients.
Put in refrigerator several hours or overnight for flavors to blend. Makes 5 to 7 servings.

title: broccoli and cavatelli
directions: Cook the garlic in
the
oil until brown; take off heat about 5 minutes.	Add
tomatoes;	cook on medium heat; as they get hot crush or break
with
wooden spoon.
Cook for about 20 minutes. Add either fresh or dried basil, then add cavatelli, broccoli and black pepper to taste.

title: best, easy pea salad
directions: Combine cole slaw, peas and olives in a bowl. Mix sugar, vinegar and mayonnaise together. Add to pea mixture and mix well. Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Stir flour, sugar, oatmeal, baking powder, baking soda, and salt in a mixing bowl.
Then stir in lard, buttermilk, vanilla, eggs, peanut butter, and chocolate chips.
Bake till golden brown or until done.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook veggies as directed.
Drain and add celery, onions, cheese and mayonnaise.
Top with cracker crumbs that have melted with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Brown meat and onion; add taco seasoning and put in deep 10-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle on chilies.
Beat milk, Bisquick and eggs until smooth; pour over meat.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°; top with tomatoes and green pepper and sprinkle on Cheddar cheese. Bake 8 to 10 minutes more or until knife comes out clean.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a glass casserole dish.
In a bowl, mix together sugar, milk and flour.
Pour batter in dish on top of margarine.
Spread a can of your favorite canned fruit or pie filling on top of batter, leaving batter around edges.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375 degrees.

title: heavenly hash pie
directions: Prepare jello according to package directions; chill until firm.
Whip until fluffy; stir in pecans, fruit cocktail, coconut and marshmallows.
Fold in whipped cream; pour into crust. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: fried rice chicken casserole
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in large bowl.
Set aside.
In a large skillet, melt shortening and saute onion and rice until rice is yellow.
Add salt and water or broth.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes in large casserole.
Place half of rice, chicken mixture, then remaining rice.
Sprinkle with crushed chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: rolls
directions: Pour water over other ingredients and let stand until lukewarm.

title: corn dogs
directions: In bowl, mix cornmeal, flour, baking powder, salt, sugar, egg, paprika, dry mustard and pepper.
Pour mixture into a tall glass. Skewer hot dogs with wooden skewer.
Dip into mixture.
Deep fry at 375° until golden brown (about 2 minutes).
Drain on paper towel.
Yields 10 to 16 corn dogs.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix with fingers, butter, sugar, flour, spices and salt. Grease an 8 or 9-inch pan and spread apples on the bottom. Sprinkle crumb mixture over apples.
Pat lightly.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until the apples are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: orange pineapple cake
directions: Mix cake mix, mandarin oranges, oil and eggs well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Cool.
Split 2 layers to make 4. Let cool.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Mix lime jello per package instructions.
Let set.
In a double boiler, mix 1 cup hot water, lemon jello and marshmallows. Stir until dissolved.
Add 1 cup pineapple juice.
Remove from heat and add cream cheese and Miracle Whip.
Let cool, then fold in Cool Whip and 1 cup pineapple.
Let cool until thick.
Pour over lime jello.
Prepare cherry jello as directed.
When it starts to jell, pour over lime mixture.
Chill until firm and serve.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream all ingredients together.
May serve on strawberry pie.

title: french apple trifle
directions: Combine apples and caramel topping in large bowl stir gently. Place 1/2 of pound cake slices in a large glass serving bowl. Top with 1/2 of apple mixture then 1/2 of pudding repeat layers. Spoon whipped topping over pudding sprinkle with nuts. Garnish with cherries, if desired. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: shortcake dough for strawberries
directions: Mix and pour in greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Batter will be thick. Bake at 400° until brown all over top.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Sort and wash beans.
Place in a Dutch oven.
Cover beans with water 2-inches above beans and let soak overnight.
Drain beans and return to Dutch oven.
Add 1 1/2 quarts of water and the next 10 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cook beans, uncovered, stirring occasionally for 1 hour.
Add ham and 1 cup of water.
Cook, uncovered, an additional hour or until desired degree of doneness, stirring occasionally.
Discard bay leaf. Stir in hot sauce.
Serve over rice.
Yields 4 servings.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Cook ham
and
onion
in butter.
Combine eggs, pepper, nutmeg, cream and parsley for batter.
Spread ham and onion in pie shell.
Add
batter, then cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 1 pie.

title: dark chocolate cake
directions: Mix eggs and sour milk together.
