Melt together butter and cocoa.
Sift sugar, flour, salt and soda.
Mix with the rest. Whip and add boiling water and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt. In a large bowl, cream the butter and sugar.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Fold in flour mixture, milk, lemon juice and zest, mixing only enough to combine well.
Pour into an oiled and floured bread pan and bake until done, approximately 1 hour.
Unmold and dust top with confectioners sugar, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: dream pies
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip together.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Add all the other ingredients to mixture and mix well. Pour into pie shells and chill for at least 3 hours.

title: lemon pie squares
directions: Prepare lemon pie filling by combining lemon pudding and pie filling, 4 tablespoons sugar and 4 cups water.
Cook until thick. Cool.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt shortening over low heat. Remove from heat and add sugar, molasses and egg; mix well. Sift all dry ingredients and add to mixture. Mix thoroughly. Put in refrigerator and chill. Form into 1-inch balls; roll in sugar and place on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: best ever fruit cake
directions: After you skin and clean your possum, trim all the fat off the carcass.
Freeze if possible.
When you are ready to cook the varmint, place it in a roaster.
Place an onion and an apple inside the possum; then sprinkle it with salt, pepper and sage. (Other spices may be used to suit taste.)
Put enough water in roaster to keep meat from scorching.
Cover; place in oven at low heat and steam one hour (varying slightly with size of animal). Uncover; place sweet potatoes around possum; replace cover and cook until potatoes are tender.
Uncover and brown the possum.

title: indoor barbecue chicken
directions: Cook the chicken in water with the salt.
Mix together barbecue sauce, honey and brown sugar.
Brush onto cooked chicken. Place onto indoor barbecue grill.
Turn every 5 minutes, brushing barbecue sauce on each time you turn.
Cook on grill about 30 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Fill 9 or 10-inch pie plate with apples.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Pat firmly over apples and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Poke holes in bottom and sides of pie crust.
Pre-brown crust for a few minutes.
Remove crust from oven.
Drain (and squeeze) spinach to remove liquid.
Layer spinach on bottom of pie crust. Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Mix flour with 1/4 cup milk. Beat together eggs and remaining milk.
Beat flour/milk mixture into egg/milk mixture.
Pour mixture into pie crust.
Bake on cookie sheet in 350° oven for 45 minutes or in 375° oven for 1/2 hour.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes before cutting.

title: pork barbecue
directions: In a crockpot or pressure cooker, roast onion salt and pepper until very tender.
When meat is done, remove from pot and using a fork shred meat until very fine.
Return to crock pot and add remaining ingredients cook over night on low temperature.

title: peanut butter logs
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into small 1 1/2-inch long rolls. Melt in double boiler the chocolate chips and paraffin wax.
Dip logs in mixture and lay on wax paper.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Melt
margarine;
stir	in brown sugar, syrup and salt. Boil 5
minutes.
Remove
from
heat and stir in 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and
teaspoon	baking	soda.
Pour over popcorn, mixing it well to coat each piece.
Separate pieces of popcorn and place
a layer
in two large baking sheets.	Bake at 250° for 1
hour. Cool
completely.
It crisps on standing.
Store in airtight container.

title: heavenly jam(rhubarb-pineapple jam)
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients for 20 minutes.
Take off heat and add jello.
Seal with paraffin or keep in refrigerator. Heavenly.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix flour and corn meal into 1/2 cup sugar. Beat slightly. Add remaining ingredients. Pour into uncooked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: raw cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries, pineapple and sugar.
Let stand overnight.
Drain for 10 minutes or more and add grapes, nuts and marshmallows. Fold in the whipped cream.
Let stand in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Can be frozen. Serves 16 to 18.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well. Sift flour, baking powder, cocoa and salt.
Add
dry ingredients, alternating with milk. Add vanilla. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: chicken noodle soup with vegetables
directions: Heat all ingredients except noodles to boiling.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer until chicken is done, about 45 minutes.
Cook noodles.
Remove chicken from bones.
Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces.
Add chicken and noodles to broth.
Heat until hot, about 5 minutes.

title: nutmeg cookies
directions: Cream butter or shortening with sugar; mix until it is well creamed.
Beat eggs and add milk.
Add the liquid slowly to the sugar and butter mix and beat well.
Add a little at a time the sifted flour, baking powder, nutmeg and salt (which have been sifted together).
Take only part of the dough at a time and roll out thin or thick, as desired.
Cut with plain or fancy cutters which have been dipped in flour.
Place on a greased sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: helena's beau monde dip
directions: Mix well and let stand overnight.
Serve with all kinds of veggies. Makes 2 cups.
Enjoy!

title: deborah's broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli, drain and set aside.
In large skillet, saute onion until crisp-tender.
Add turkey breakfast sausage or ground beef and cook until brown.
Drain off fat.

title: baby reubens
directions: Split rolls.
Layer cheese and ham, then remaining cheese on bottom layer of rolls.
Top with top layer of rolls.
Boil together remaining ingredients and pour over rolls.
Let set 2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix all together with a large spoon.
Do not beat.
Grease and flour tube cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve as is or ice with butter cream icing.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Store in airtight containers.

title: sicilian stuffed artichokes
directions: Cut off 1-inch from the top and base of each artichoke.
Remove lower outer leaves.
If desired, snip off tips of remaining leaves. Cover with cold water and add 1 teaspoon salt.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Drain upside down.
Mix together bread crumbs, 1 clove garlic, cheese, 1 teaspoon parsley, salt and pepper.
Set aside. Spread leaves of drained artichokes open slightly.
Place 3 slices of garlic in each artichoke.
Sprinkle bread crumb mixture between leaves and over top of artichokes.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley. Place artichokes close together in a 10-inch skillet so they will remain upright during cooking.
Pour the boiling water in the skillet and sprinkle the artichokes with the olive oil.
Cook, covered, about 30 minutes or until artichoke leaves are tender. Makes 4 servings.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and vanilla.
Add 1 egg and
mix well.
Spread on bottom of deep, 9-inch, unbaked pastry shell.

title: baked potato balls
directions: Separate egg.
Add mashed potatoes with egg yolk.
Roll into ball.
Dip ball into egg white, roll in flavored bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: two-tone raspberry soup(excellent appetizer - fun to make)
directions: Sieve the raspberries to remove their seeds and combine with cranberry-raspberry juice.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: hot tamale balls
directions: Mix together ground meats, cornmeal, flour, tomatoes, chili powder, garlic and 2 tablespoons salt.
Form mixture into small balls the size of a large marble.
In a large roaster, pour in tomato juice and remaining salt.
Let simmer for 10 minutes.
Drop in tamale balls and let cook for 2 hours. Check sauce during cooking and add tomato juice or water, if needed.
Remove balls from sauce and serve.
Makes about 100 balls.

title: eggplant
directions: Peel and chop
eggplant.
Cook	in
water until tender. Salt to taste.
When
tender,
drain
off
water and mash with potato masher.
Add
onion
and tomatoes.	Add bacon drippings to season. Mix cornbread and most of grated cheese and add to eggplant mixture.
Sprinkle
remaining
grated
cheese
over mixture. Bake in greased dish at 350° about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: if i can do it, you can do it dip
directions: Chop chipped beef.
Beat all ingredients together until smooth.
Put mixture into a buttered casserole dish.
Top with 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 minutes. Serve warm with your favorite crackers.

title: salsa
directions: Blend all chopped ingredients along with juices in large (8 qt.) pan.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 15 minutes.
Can in water bath for 10 minutes.

title: pacific salmon loaf with cucumber sauce
directions: In medium bowl, combine crumbs, milk, egg, onion, butter, lemon juice and pepper.
Stir in salmon.
Spoon into greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf dish.
Smooth top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.
Serve with Cucumber Sauce.

title: butterscotch dip
directions: Serve with fruit to dip.

title: thrifty casserole
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add ground beef and brown with onion and bell pepper (chopped).
Turn heat off.
Add milk, soup, salt and macaroni.
Stir up good.
Put in a baking dish, covered.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt
candy
and
stick
butter together; set aside. Cream sugar,
eggs
and
stick
butter; add flour and soda alternately
with milk.
Add melted candy mixture, add pecans. Bake
in
layers or tube pan at 350° for 20 minutes or at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian fruit salad
directions: Combine and chill before serving.

title: stir-fried pork and eggplant
directions: Cut eggplant into 1/2 x 1 x 1/4-inch pieces.
Mix pork and wine.
Refrigerate.
Blend cornstarch, and water; add to soy sauce, sugar and m.s.g.
Set aside.
Heat oil in wok.
Stir-fry garlic, pork and salt for 1 minute.
Add eggplant, chicken broth and pepper.
Stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add cornstarch mixture, stir-fry for 1 minute or until broth thickens.
Remove from wok and serve.

title: canadian short bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter well.
Sift flour and cornstarch in a separate bowl.
Add gradually to the preceding mixture.
Place 1/4-inch thick on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for about 1/2 hour.
While still hot, cut with a small cookie cutter.
Place a silver decor in the middle of each cookie.

title: meat loaf
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix together all ingredients.
Put in meat loaf pans and bake at 250° for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: Combine all of these ingredients.

title: chocolate peanut butter crunch
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions on the box.
Grease two 9 x 13-inch pans. Divide batter into both pans.
Bake at 350° until done, about 15 minutes.
Spread marshmallows evenly on top cake.
Bake 3 minutes more (second layer).

title: baked chicken
directions: Cut chicken up and put in casserole dish.
Mix cranberry sauce and Catalina dressing together and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
This is very good.
I cook rice and serve with it.

title: hurry-up chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Crush the chips slightly in the bottom of a baking dish.
Mix all the other ingredients, except the cheese, in a bowl and pour over the chips.
Top with grated cheese and bake for about 20 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture, alternating with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: grape-nut custard pudding
directions: Soak cereal in warm milk.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Add Grape-Nuts-milk mixture.
Bake in pan or bowl set in pan of water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, stirring at least twice during first 20 minutes.

title: bleu cheese-bacon potatoes
directions: Rub potatoes with shortening.
Bake in 400° oven for 1 hour or until done.
Remove from oven.
Cut a lengthwise slice from top of each potato.
Scoop out insides; mash.
Add sour cream, cheese, milk, butter, salt and pepper.
Beat until fluffy.
Spoon into shells.
Return to oven 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with bacon.

title: alfredo sauce
directions: Melt butter in heavy pan on medium heat. Add cheese and cream to the butter slowly, alternating them until all is mixed in the pan (I use a whisk). When all is mixed, add the package of Knorr; mix slowly. Continue to stir until desired consistency. Serve over fettuccine.

title: seashell macaroni and tomato sauce casserole
directions: Cook meat, add sauce, cooked spinach and shells. Pour in a casserole dish.
Top with shredded sharp Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until dish is bubbly and cheese is melted.

title: pineapple dressing with jello
directions: Prepare jello according to package directions.
Add fruit cocktail. Chill until set.

title: basic stir-fry
directions: In a glass bowl, combine chicken, soy sauce and garlic powder. Stir well and set aside.
Heat 2 teaspoons oil in large skillet or wok.
Stir in all vegetables and stir-fry 3 to 5 minutes until onions are translucent.
Remove vegetables and set aside.
Heat remaining 2 teaspoons oil; add chicken.
Stir-fry until chicken is cooked, about 5 minutes.
Return vegetables to skillet with chicken.
Stir in cornstarch mixture and cook until sauce thickens.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: easy creamy cheesecake
directions: Grease and flour 8-inch square pan.
Mix cream cheese, eggs and 2/3 cup sugar with mixer and spread in prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven for 15 minutes.
Stir together vanilla, 3 tablespoons sugar and sour cream.
Spread on top of cheesecake and bake 10 more minutes.
Cool and chill or freeze.
If desired, top with favorite pie filling.
Can be doubled for 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: 5 hour beef stew
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in covered pan or Dutch oven. Add the tapioca, salt, pepper and sugar, but do not mix, just sprinkle on.
Pour the V-8 juice over mixture.
Cover and bake at 250° for 5 hours.
If you double the recipe, bake for 7 hours.
Do not mix or raise lid.
You can use any large, flat pan and cover with aluminum foil (9 x 13-inch works).

title: cheese 'n wiener crescents
directions: Cut cheese in 6 strips each.
Slit
wieners
to
within one-half
inch of ends.
Insert 3 cheese
strips
in
wieners. Center on dinner roll.
Roll up.
Place on baking sheet cheese side up.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 8.

title: fruit bavarian
directions: Combine jello and boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add ice cream a spoon at a time.
Stir until ice cream melts.
Add fruit and chill.

title: strawberry fruit punch
directions: Boil for 5 minutes.
Cool the syrup.

title: creamed hamburger
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Stir in flour until well mixed. Slowly add milk while stirring.
Cook until thickened, stirring occasionally.
Serve over mashed potatoes.

title: salad dressing(cooked)
directions: Put egg in saucepan and stir to mix white and yolk.
Add rest of ingredients and cook until thick (add milk last and cook, stirring all the time).

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice in boiling water for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
If dry before tender, add more water.
Watch closely.
Rice should be soft and fluffy.
Saute vegetables in butter; add to cooked rice, canned mushrooms and liquid.
Add at least 1/2 teaspoon black pepper and water chestnuts, if you like.
Cover and heat in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and peppers.
Then add all other ingredients.
Cook on top of stove until hot.
Pour into large dish and bake at 350° until thick, stirring often.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix all together and keep in tight closing jar or container until ready for a cup of hot tea.
Add 1 teaspoon or more as desired for cup of hot water.
Great around Christmastime.

title: hot sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; simmer 1 hour.
Store in airtight container and refrigerate.

title: strawberry candy
directions: Mix well.
Set in refrigerator until mixture can be formed into shape of strawberry.
Take coconut and mix green food coloring for stems.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix and form into balls.
Place in skillet on medium heat in 2 tablespoons oil and brown.
Top with Mulneix Meatball Sauce.

title: spinach pie
directions: Cook spinach; drain very well.
Cut Swiss cheese into small pieces.
Mix spinach, egg, sour cream, Swiss cheese and approximately 3/4 can of onion rings.
Save 1/4 can of onion rings for topping.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil macaroni according to package instructions.
When done, rinse really well with hot water.
Add margarine, Cheddar cheese, Kraft singles and milk.
Add enough milk so that the mixture looks soupy.
Then add the Cheddar cheese soup and mix well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours or until the top browns nicely.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together.
Make into balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: peggy's cheese ball
directions: Let all cheese soften in a large ball.
Add onion, horseradish and Worcestershire sauce.
Roll into 1 large ball or 2 smaller balls or 2 logs.
Roll in chopped pecans or chopped parsley.
Chill and serve.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into 3/4-inch cubes and roll in flour that has been seasoned with salt and pepper.
Brown in hot oil.
When meat is browned, add all other ingredients together and pour over meat. Cover and cook on low temperature for 30 to 40 minutes.
Good served over rice or noodles.

title: tuna ball
directions: Drain tuna.
Mix with cream cheese and liquid smoke.
Roll into a ball, then roll tuna into finely chopped celery.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cook beef, onion and garlic until brown.
Drain grease and add seasonings and soup.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add cheese and cook slowly until cheese has melted.
Cut top off pepper, remove seeds and boil for 2-3 minutes.
Cool.
Stuff with mixture. Bake about 50 minutes in 400° oven.

title: fresh fruit glaze
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and pineapple juice in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, for one minute.
Mixture should look clear.
Remove from heat and add remaining juices.

title: buttermilk pie no. 1
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well.
Add beaten eggs, buttermilk, vanilla and nutmeg.
Pour into uncooked pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Heat soups and mushrooms with 1 cup of water.
Set aside 1 cup of mixture.
Mix remainder with 1 1/2 cups uncooked rice and put in bottom of baking pan.
Lay chicken pieces on top.
Cover with the 1 cup of soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: taco shells
directions: It'll help you keep clean,

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Fry sausage and drain off fat.
Butter one side of bread and place in well-greased casserole.
Sprinkle cheese over bread, butter side up.
Combine beaten eggs, milk, salt and mustard. Pour over bread.
Sprinkle sausage on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning bake covered at 325° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: tuna loaf
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Combine all other ingredients, except lemon slices.
Fold into egg whites.
Arrange lemon slices in greased loaf pan.
Pour mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until well set.
Turn out onto a platter.
Serves 6.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Layer in this order:
beef, onions, spaghetti, mushrooms and peas.
Sprinkle well with garlic salt and pepper plus 3 or 4 squirts of Worcestershire sauce.
Put cheese cubes on top and pour tomato juice over all.
Bake at 325° for one hour.
Freezes well.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook frozen spinach in small amount of water with onion until thawed.
Beat eggs and mix rest of ingredients with spinach and onion and bake in greased casserole for 30 minutes in 350° oven or until center is set.
Do not overcook; it will cause casserole to separate.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: prize pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, honey, pumpkin, salt, sugar, cinnamon and vanilla.
Add milk and juice.
Stir well.
Pour into pie crusts.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300°. Bake for 35 minutes longer.

title: the compromise cake
directions: Grease bottom of tube pan; line bottom of pan with wax paper. Grease and flour lining and pan; set aside.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix mashed potatoes, vanilla, sugar, eggs and margarine together and spread in an 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix brown sugar, coconut, chopped nuts, flour and margarine; sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Mix 1/3 cup soup, 1/4 cup water, onion and parsley.
Dip the chicken pieces into soup mixture, then roll the chicken pieces in the crushed stuffing.
Place in a shallow baking dish (12 x 8 x 2-inch).
Drizzle butter on top of chicken.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 1 hour.
Meanwhile, combine remaining soup and water.
Heat, stir now and then.
Serve over the chicken.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cassoleti
directions: Soak beans overnight in water.
Cook in chicken broth until done.
Place duck in baking pan uncovered in 350° oven, until golden brown.
When duck is cooked, cut into bite sized pieces. When beans are done, put into large casserole dish.
Chop onion and garlic.
Place in skillet with small amount of oil.
Saute.
Cut link sausage into bite size pieces.
Add to onions and garlic. Cook about 5 minutes.
Add duck.
Stir all this into beans in casserole dish.
Cover.
Bake about 30 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce made over(lo-fat)
directions: Combine ingredients in a 1-quart saucepan. Simmer slowly, uncovered, for 40 minutes.
Makes 1 2/3 cups.

title: blackened fish
directions: Cover fish with butter.
Sprinkle blackened seasonings on a hot skillet (outside) and sprinkle blackened seasonings on top side.
Flip over when fish is white around edges.
Will cook in 2 to 3 minutes.
Fish should be 1/2 inch to 3/4 inch thick.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except tomato sauce.
Shape into balls.
Place in a casserole dish and cover with tomato sauce. Bake, covered, for 1 1/2 hours in a 350° oven.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into a greased bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: velveeta salsa dip(microwave)
directions: Microwave Velveeta cheese and salsa in 1 1/2-quart microwavable bowl on High for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted, stirring after 3 minutes.
Stir in cilantro.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.
Makes 3 cups.

title: english scones
directions: Butter and flour a cookie sheet.
Mix first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Add oleo and cut in until mixture resembles fine meal.
Add milk and eggs, then raisins.
Mix dough thoroughly. Turn dough on lightly floured surface, roll in flour a couple of times.
Press dough into 1-inch thick round; with cookie cutter (3-inch), cut scones and place on sheet.
Brush on glaze.

title: pink cherry salad
directions: Mix together.
Add miniature marshmallows, if desired.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Wash lettuce and dry thoroughly.
Tear into pieces and put in large salad bowl.
Fry bacon crisp.
Remove from fat and crumble. Add remaining ingredients to fat in pan and heat to boiling.
Pour over lettuce and toss.
Put crumbled bacon on top.
Green onions may be added or hot, sliced, hard-boiled eggs on top.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Place in saucepan with small amount of water.
Cover and cook almost tender.

title: fruit crunch
directions: Mix fruit with sugar and put in bottom of long cake pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix on top and put margarine on top of that. Put 1/4 cup sugar on top of that.
Bake at 350° for at least an hour.

title: apple sweet potatoes
directions: Bake desired number of sweet potatoes until done.
Cut slice off tops of potatoes lengthwise.
Put in pineapple juice and brown sugar.
Broil 3 to 5 minutes to glaze.

title: play dough
directions: Mix ingredients together and knead like dough.
Add food coloring, if desired.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix and boil 2 minutes milk, cocoa, margarine and sugar. Remove from heat and add vanilla, oatmeal and peanut butter.
Stir until stiff and drop by tablespoons on wax paper until cool.

title: mexican mix casserole
directions: Mix chili,
corn,
cheese
and onion in casserole dish. Crumble chips
in
your
hands
over top of other ingredients. Press chips
gently
into
other mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve
casserole with extra whole chips if you like. You may cook in microwave for 4 minutes on High.

title: cajun cabbage
directions: In a large Dutch oven, brown ground beef.
Add onions and green pepper.
Cook until the onions are transparent.
Add rice, tomatoes, tomato sauce, water and seasonings.
Cover and bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes or until the cabbage is tender.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cookies kids love
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Mix in egg, vinegar and molasses. Last, gradually mix in mixture of flour, salt, baking soda and ginger.
Refrigerate about 1/2 hour.
Remove from refrigerator and make small balls from the dough.
Roll them in sugar.
Place balls on cookie sheet and flatten with bottom of a glass.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 9 minutes.

title: chicken and sherry
directions: Fry chicken in oleo until brown.
Mix wine, mushrooms and soup.
Pour mixture over chicken, stirring with butter to mix. Baste over top of chicken and put in oven for about 1 hour at 350°. Remove and baste some more gravy on chicken.
Put remaining gravy in bowl and serve on rice.

title: fruit cobbler(blackberry, peach or cherry)
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Spread fruit over the dough. Roll up like a jelly roll.
Place roll in dish and pour a mixture of sugar and water over roll.
Place in oven and bake one hour at 350°.

title: cheese rice bake
directions: In a glass bowl, combine water, onion, salt and rosemary. Bring just to boiling, just about 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in rice. Cover tightly and let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with a fork.
Stir in cheese, evaporated milk and eggs.
Add vegetables.
Bake, uncovered, in a flat casserole dish for 9 minutes, turning every 3 minutes, or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: spiced fruit compote
directions: Drain fruits.
Reserve syrup.
Arrange fruits in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle sugar, lemon juice and spices over fruits.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: crab casserole
directions: Mix everything together in a bowl; store in refrigerator about 8 hours.
Pour into a casserole dish; bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: 1-2-3 cheese cake
directions: Blend cream cheese, sugar and vanilla on medium speed.
Add eggs; blend until well mixed.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool 3 hours; refrigerate.
Garnish with your choice of fruit.

title: swedish pastry
directions: Combine yeast and water according to directions on package. Meanwhile, combine oil with sugar.
Gradually beat in eggs, softened yeast and milk.
Add flour and salt; beat briskly.
Chill in refrigerator about 2 hours.
Roll out on a floured board into a rectangle about 1/2 inch thick.
Brush with melted butter and divide into 3 equal portions.
Fold one over the other for three layers.

title: ham and broccoli royale
directions: Spoon rice into greased 3-quart casserole dish.
Layer cooked broccoli over rice.
Put 4 tablespoons oleo in pan and melt. Saute onion in oleo.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper; slowly stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add ham and heat through.
Pour mixture over broccoli; layer cheese slices over ham mixture.
Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: cracker spread
directions: Soften cream cheese and beat with a mixer.
Add all other ingredients.
Shape into a ball or place in a serving bowl. Chill and serve with crackers.

title: mabel's iron skillet chocolate pie
directions: Melt margarine in iron skillet. Mix together sugar, cocoa and flour. Separate eggs; beat yolks and milk. Add yolk and milk mixture to sugar, cocoa and flour mixture. Add this to melted margarine in iron skillet. Cook until thick. Add vanilla. Pour into baked pie shell.

title: oreo cookie delight
directions: Crush Oreo cookies and 1/2 stick butter in bottom of pan and put vanilla ice cream (soften) on top and freeze.
Melt 1 stick butter, Eagle Brand milk and syrup.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Cool, then pour on top of Oreos and ice cream mixture.
Freeze.
Put Cool Whip on top; freeze.

title: macaroni and cheese pie
directions: Boil noodles with salt and margarine.
Pour into casserole dish.
Add cheese pack, pepper, eggs and 1/2 block cheese, grated. Mix together; add mix and stir.
Then put other 1/2 of grated block cheese on top.
Add more milk if needed.
The more milk and cheese, the better.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until desired browness.

title: oatmeal carameletas bars
directions: Melt caramels in evaporated milk in heavy saucepan.
Cool slightly.
Combine remaining ingredients, except chocolate chips and pecans, in large mixing bowl.
Press half of the crumbs into the bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and pecans.
Spread carefully with caramels mixture.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes longer until golden brown.
Chill 1 to 2 hours, then cut into bars.

title: no-melt jello
directions: Using the same flavor Jell-O and fruit, add boiling water to Jell-O, then add applesauce and fruit.
Chill to set.
To make serving pieces, use a 13 x 9-inch pan or to be fancy, use a glass bowl.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn bread with baking powder
directions: Combine corn meal, flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Work in cold lard.
Add cold water or milk for a stiff batter.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake for 40 minutes.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat salt and egg whites until thick and foamy. Gradually add sugar.
Beat until stiff.
Carefully fold in nuts and raisins. Carefully add (fold in) nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto brown paper bags.
Place in a preheated oven at 350° and turn off oven.
Leave in closed oven overnight.

title: kathleen's fruit salad
directions: Mix and chill the first 3 items, then about 1 hour before serving, add whole strawberries.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare sweet potatoes per package directions.
Cool.
In a blender or food processor, combine potatoes, sugar, cinnamon, vanilla, ginger and nutmeg.
Cover and blend well. Add milk and eggs.
Pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Pie will be puffy and sink as it cools. Serve with whipped cream. Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Boil chicken and vegetables until done.
Remove chicken from broth, skin, the bone, etc. and cut into bite size pieces.
Return chicken to broth and add bouillon and noodles.
Cook until noodles are done.

title: spaghetti with italian meatballs
directions: In medium bowl, combine ground beef, bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, oregano, garlic, pepper and eggs. Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls. In Dutch oven, brown meatballs in hot oil over high heat. Drain. Combine browned meatballs and spaghetti sauce. Simmer about 30 minutes.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Add enough water to vegetables (potatoes, carrot, onion and parsley) to cook without scorching; do not cover completely (soup will be too thin). Bring to boil, then reduce heat and simmer until potatoes are soft but not mushy. When potatoes are soft, turn heat up and add evaporated milk and Cheez Whiz. Once Cheez Whiz is all melted and just before serving, add butter. Be careful not to boil soup after milk is added! Enjoy!

title: little pizzas for kids
directions: Spread English muffin halves with catsup.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Slice wiener and place slice on top of each English muffin.
Broil or toast until cheese is melted.
Makes 4.

title: onion rings
directions: Separate sliced onions into individual rings.
In med. sauce pan heat oil on med-high setting.
In med size bowl mix all of flour with enough water to make batter consistency thick enough to cling to onions.

Coat a few slices of onions in batter thoroughly coating and place in hot oil until batter is crisp turning to cook both sides (new oil will not allow batter to brown as well). Remove cooked rings from hot oil and drain on paper towels.
Serve hot.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Put raw rice in baking dish; mix mushroom soup, celery soup and milk.
Put about 1/2 of soup mixture over rice and then cover with water.
Arrange pork chops on top of rice, pour the rest of soup mixture over chops and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until pork chops are tender.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken, debone and save chicken stock. In a skillet, saute onions, pepper and celery until tender in butter.
In another saucepan, boil vermicelli in chicken stock, following package directions.
Drain. In a large pan, combine chicken, sauteed onions, pepper and celery with vermicelli. Combine chili powder, parsley, pimento, soup and mushrooms.
Mix thoroughly. Cover and refrigerate 24 hours, if desired.
Place in a large buttered casserole. Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. May be frozen.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in oil until soft.
Add shrimp and stir.
Add mushrooms, salt and pepper and fry over medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add rice and soy sauce and fry 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Diced, cooked chicken, pork or ham may be used instead of shrimp.
One or all of these makes for a fantastic taste.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar 20 minutes.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour and lemon extract; fold in the 7-Up.
Pour into well-greased 12-cup Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: versatile drop cookies
directions: Blend Fluffo, sugar and eggs.
Stir in dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla.
Divide dough into four equal parts.
Leave one part plain or stir in 1 teaspoon nutmeg and 1/2 teaspoon ginger to make spice drops.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Do not salt popped corn.
Melt margarine or butter in saucepan.
Add tiny marshmallows and stir until melted.
Add jello.
Place popcorn in a large dishpan and pour preceding mixture over all.
With buttered hands, form into balls.
Wrap in Saran Wrap.
Great for children's parties.

title: chocolate chip squares
directions: Melt oleo. Add sugars and eggs.
Beat well.
Blend in vanilla and flour.
Stir in pecans, chocolate chips and coconut.
Spread into greased and floured 7 x 12 x 1 1/2-inch Pyrex dish. Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: chicken 'n' dressing casserole
directions: Stew chicken; debone.
Reserve 2 cups of broth.
Place chicken pieces in bottom of large casserole dish.
Mix together soups, melted margarine and sour cream.
Pour over chicken and cover with Stove Top stuffing mix, including seasoning packet.
Pour 2 cups chicken broth over the layered casserole.
Cover; cook 40 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake 20 minutes.

title: cheese stuffed shells with basil(low-fat)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, stir together Ricotta cheese, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, basil and garlic.
Fill each shell with about 2 tablespoons cheese filling.
Place in 12 x 7-inch baking dish sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Pour sauce over filled shells.
Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 8. Total fat 3 grams; saturated fat 1.5 grams.

title: laura ingalls popcorn treats
directions: Put honey, molasses and butter in saucepan. Heat and mix well. Put popcorn, oats, raisins and peanuts in large bowl. Pour honey mixture over popcorn mixture. Stir until popcorn is well coated. Serve right from the bowl.

title: french or jelly pancakes
directions: Separate eggs; beat yolks.
Add salt and 1/2 cup milk.
Stir in flour.
Add rest of milk and oil.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Add sugar.
Fold into flour mixture and fry.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Drain all fruit.
Mix together the night before and refrigerate overnight.

title: vegetable bean salad
directions: Mix all together.
Refrigerate 12 hours before serving.

title: slick dumplings
directions: Roll 1/8-inch thick; cut in 3-inch squares.
Boil about 15 minutes in chicken or meat broth.
Dumplings may be cut in 1/2-inch squares and cooked with English peas, butter beans or vegetable soup.

title: happy day dessert
directions: Mix together and press mixture into a 13 x 9-inch pan and chill.

title: chicken pie with biscuit topping
directions: Heat olive oil in frypan and saute onion, carrots and celery until tender and brown.
Place vegetables in saucepan with chicken stock, thyme and parsley.
Bring to simmer.

title: oven barbecue chicken
directions: Coat chicken pieces with mixture of flour, salt and pepper. Brown in hot oil. Place chicken pieces in one layer in shallow pan. Combine other ingredients and bring to a boil. Pour heated sauce over chicken. Cover the pan. Bake at 325° about 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender.

title: florida bake potatoes
directions: Mix cheese, potatoes, onion
and mayonnaise. Crumble bacon on top along with sliced olives.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: potato deluxe
directions: Thaw potatoes 30 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together; salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in 10 x 13-inch Pyrex dish in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: bean dip
directions: Layer beans, green chilies, salsa, onion, cheese, sour cream and olives.
Put in glass baking dish.
Cook in oven at 350° for about 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve as a hot dip with nacho chips.

title: cajun bayou casserole
directions: Melt cream cheese and 1 block butter and set aside.
(Use microwave oven.)
Saute shrimp and seasonings in 2 Tbsp. butter until shrimp are cooked and seasonings are wilted.
Add cream cheese mixture.
Add soup and season to taste.
Mix in rice and crabmeat and pour into casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350 degrees about 20-30 minutes.
Makes 4-6 servings.

title: easy way chicken pot pie
directions: Put chicken in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour broth over chicken, potatoes and peas with onion.
Pour soup over potatoes and peas.
Add pimiento.
Melt margarine in small pan.
Stir in flour and add milk.
Mix well.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: hot cheeseburger chip dip
directions: Fry hamburger and drain. Add chopped onion. Add sliced black olives and jalapeno peppers. Add melted Velveeta cheese to cover and mix. Serve warm with chips.

title: "apple pie"
directions: Bring water, sugar and cream of tartar to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Add Ritz crackers, one at a time.
Allow to boil 2 minutes after last cracker is dropped in.
Remove from heat. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Dot filling with butter and sprinkle cinnamon over filling.
Bake 20 minutes at 425° (pastry strips can be added across the top before baking, if desired).

title: baked pork tenderloin with vegetables
directions: Place flour, salt and pepper in gallon zippered plastic bag. Shake.
Add tenderloins, trimmed of all fat.
Shake to coat. Melt margarine on medium heat in large skillet.
Brown tenderloins on all sides. Brown potatoes at the same time. Remove to casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Saute onion and celery in pan drippings until just tender. Cut carrots into 2-inch chunks. Add to casserole.
Spoon soup over.
Stir water into onion and celery. Pour over soup.
Bake, tightly covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: southern casserole
directions: Bake chicken breast in 350° oven until done (about 1 hour and can be done the day before).
When cool, remove bones and skin. Leave in large pieces if desired.
Cook rice as directed on box. When finished, add soup, broth, onion and celery to rice.
Arrange pieces of chicken in greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour rice mixture over it.
Bake 3/4 to 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: prairie bread
directions: Add chopped dates, sugar, salt, shortening and boiling water in a bowl.
Let stand until cool.
Add the remaining ingredients; mix well.

title: bisquick banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients for one minute. Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 55-60 minutes.

title: bacon and egg casserole
directions: Coat a 9 x 11 x 12-inch casserole dish with vegetable spray. Place croutons in casserole dish and pour margarine over croutons. Sprinkle grated cheese over margarine and croutons.
Mix milk, eggs and mustard and pour over cheese mixture. Sprinkle bacon crumbs evenly over dish.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Allow casserole to stand for 15 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: cheese cake
directions: Blend together cream cheese, cottage cheese and sour cream. Then add eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
(May be baked on top of graham cracker crust if desired.)

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: In a large bowl mix rice, onion, parsley, celery, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and egg all together.
Then add 1/2 can of V-8 juice and blend well.
Make into balls.
Put meatballs in shallow pan with rest of juice.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: beef and pepper pie casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion (if used) in skillet. Add soups and enchilada sauce.
Crush corn chips and stir into mixture. Place in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish; sprinkle with grated cheese. Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp-crab gumbo
directions: Put bacon pieces in skillet.
Drain off most of the fat.
In the rest, saute onion and celery until soft.
Blend in flour; add salt and pepper to taste.
Slowly add water, tomatoes, shrimp, crabmeat and okra.
Add garlic, pepper and cumin at this time. Cook slowly until okra is cooked.

title: roasted vegetables and kielbasa
directions: Combine potatoes and vegetable oil in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in preheated 450° oven for 20 minutes.
Stir together the chili powder, cumin, salt, thyme and pepper.
Add zucchini to potatoes; toss mixture over both vegetables until evenly distributed.
Bake for 20 minutes at same temperature.
Remove from oven; place kielbasa on top and bake another 15 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients only using 1 cup pecans.
Roll ball in the other cup of pecans.
Wrap in Saran Wrap.
Better if made a day or so before.

title: frozen strawberry daiquiri
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze, stirring 3 or 4 times during the first 6 hours; the mixture will remain slushy. Serve as is or liquify in the microwave.

title: creole style pork
directions: Brown onion and pork; drain fat.
Add spaghetti, tomato, cheese and salt.
Place in greased baking dish.
Cover with crumbs.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: kielbasa surprise
directions: Boil kielbasa; remove, cool and cut up in 1-inch sections. Mix remaining ingredients; set aside.
Put kielbasa in a roasting pan.
Pour over remaining mixture, making sure covered (may add a little water if necessary).
Cover and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Can be served as appetizers.
Serve warm.

title: "easy" barbecue sauce(for stove top or oven)
directions: Mix together catsup and Pepsi.
Pour over beef, chicken or pork.
Cook until tender, turning often.

title: cream of carrot soup
directions: Cut carrots up and boil in broth with onions and garlic until tender.
Put in blender and swoosh until smooth.
Add cream. Puree again.
Return soup to pot and reheat, but do not boil.

title: frosty fruit pie
directions: Bring first ingredient to boil, then stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Mix in sugar.
Cool until almost stiff.
Whip chilled evaporated milk with lemon juice until stiff.
Pour on top of gelatin mixture.
Beat in slowly with rotary beater at low speed. Pour into cooled pie shell.
Chill several hours until firm. Splash with whipped cream.

title: hot pepper rings
directions: Slice peppers in rings.
Let soak in pan with all ingredients overnight.
Next day, place in clean jar and seal with hot lids.

title: peanut butter treats
directions: In bowl, combine egg, honey, oil, water, salt and vanilla. In mixing bowl, stir together oats, flour and wheat germ.
Add liquid mixture to dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in peanut butter pieces and sunflower nuts.
Drop dough from a 1/4 cup measure 2 inches apart onto a greased cookie sheet.
Flatten each mound to 3-inch diameter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until light brown.
Remove; cool on a wire rack.
Makes about 20 cookies.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt margarine.
Add brown sugar.
Beat and stir in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla, flour, salt and baking powder, then stir in chocolate chips.
Bake in a double size sheet cake pan.
Grease pan well.
Bake at 350° until very light brown, about 12 to 20 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: spinach madeliene
directions: Cook spinach according to directions.
Drain, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until well blended, but not brown.
Add onion, cooking only until soft.
Stir in liquid slowly, stirring until smooth. Cook until thick; continue stirring.
Add seasonings and cheese (which has been cut into cubes) and milk, stirring until cheese melts.
Combine with cooked spinach; pour into buttered casserole dish and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Refrigerate overnight before cooking.
For a spicier dish, add a dash of red pepper. This casserole freezes very well.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, salt and cream of tartar in a bowl.
In another bowl, cream together butter, sugar, eggs, vanilla and lemon extracts.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture gradually.
Roll out on lightly floured surface and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake in 425° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: crescent butter rolls
directions: Melt oleo
in milk; cool.
Dissolve yeast with 1 tablespoon sugar
in
warm water.
Beat eggs and add 1/2 cup sugar, milk mixture,
yeast and salt.
Stir in flour.
Put in refrigerator overnight.	Divide into 4 portions.
Taking one portion at a time, roll out each as for a pie crust.
Cut in 8 wedges. Roll each wedge
from
wide end to point.
Place in a greased pan, point down.
Let	rise
hours.
Bake
at
325° for 20 minutes.
Makes 32 rolls.

title: old fashioned dumplings
directions: Remove chicken from broth.
Thicken broth slightly with flour.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Brush chicken with butter and roll in bread crumb mixture. Place in heavy skillet or casserole dish.
Bake at 300° until browned. Cover and continue cooking until done, 2 to 3 hours. Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and spices; set aside.
Cream the sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla together.
Mix flour mixture into creamed mixture.
Add zucchini, applesauce, orange juice and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then remove to wire rack to cool completely.

title: louisiana gumbo
directions: Brown flour and oil in a saucepan until a copper color; add onion, celery, garlic and both peppers.
Cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients except rice.
Cook 2 hours.
Just before serving, add 1/4 teaspoon file.
Serve over rice.

title: burgoo
directions: In a large pot, fill half full with water.
Put in chicken and oxtails.
Boil 6 hours.
Take bones (as many as you can) out.
In a large iron kettle, put meat, diced potatoes, diced carrots, sliced onions, shredded cabbage, spaghetti, beans and noodles.
Stir constantly.
Add pepper and salt.
Add tomatoes and corn.
May have to add water.
Takes approximately 12 to 14 hours to cook.

title: rich and creamy crab salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, blending well. Set aside. In a separate bowl, combine crabmeat, asparagus, green onions and water chestnuts. Pour the dressing over crab salad; toss gently. Chill several hours. Serve on lettuce leaves; garnish with parsley. Great for lunch. Makes 2 1/2 cups or 4 servings.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: In medium saucepan, cook onion in margarine until wilted. Stir in Cheez Whiz.
Gradually stir in soup.
Add broccoli and rice.
Stir gently, but well.
Turn into buttered shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix well and bake 10 to 12 minutes on lightly greased cookie sheets.

title: party apricot kolaches
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix baking mix and sour cream until dough forms; beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Turn dough onto well floured cloth covered board.
Roll in flour; shape into ball.
Knead 20 times.
Divide into halves.
Roll one-half 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with floured 2-inch cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Repeat with other half.
With floured fingers, press a deep indentation in center of each.
Fill with 1 rounded teaspoonful Apricot Filling.
Bake until light brown, 8 to 10 minutes; cool on wire rack.
Dust with powdered sugar.
Makes about 2 dozen kolaches.

title: sand or dirt
directions: Crush cookies in blender; set aside.
Mix pudding with milk. Cream together cream cheese and powdered sugar, then combine with pudding mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer cookies with pudding mixture.
Start and end with crushed cookies.

title: all-bran bread
directions: Combine the cereal, raisins, molasses, margarine and boiling water in a large mixing bowl.
Mix well and let stand until cool. Add eggs and mix well.
Sift the flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon together.
Stir into the egg mixture.
Pour into four 5 x 9 inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 - 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: beef chowder
directions: Brown meat with celery, onion and green pepper. Drain.
Add soup, tomatoes and corn. Simmer, covered, 30 minutes.
Add salt or seasonings to taste.

title: christmas relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions in food processor using fine blade. Cover with boiling water, let stand 5 minutes.
Drain thoroughly. Add salt, sugar, vinegar, and boil 10 minutes.
Seal in hot sterilized jars.
Makes 3 quarts or 6 pints.
Double recipe for larger batch.

title: y. p. s. layered salad(24 hour salad)
directions: If you're prone to bruising, eat more foods rich in Vitamin C. Studies show that Vitamin C helps build collagen tissue (that is, skin tissue) around blood vessels in the skin. Vitamin C rich foods include sweet potatoes, broccoli, cauliflower and citrus fruits.

title: chocolate dream pie
directions: Prepare whipped topping mix as directed on package (using 1 cup milk and vanilla) in a large mixing bowl.
Add remaining milk and pudding mix.
Blend, then beat at high speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Spoon into pie shell.
Chill at least 4 hours.

title: cherry cheesecake in muffin tin
directions: Mix eggs, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Put paper muffin cups in muffin pans.
Place 1 vanilla wafer, flat side down, in muffin cups.
Fill half full with creamed mixture. Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Top with pie filling. Try other pie fillings for variety.

title: chinese butterscotch cookies
directions: Melt butterscotch drops in double boiler or microwave oven. Remove and mix in noodles and peanuts.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Let set until firm.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: artichoke chili dip
directions: Combine and put in a 8-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until hot.
Serve with tortilla chips or Fritos. Can be prepared ahead of time and refrigerated before heating.

title: sour cream raisin bars
directions: Cook raisins and water 10 minutes, covered.
Cool and set aside.

title: spaghetti-crust pie
directions: Cook spaghetti 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain.
Add butter, slightly beaten eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Mix.
Put spaghetti mixture into 9-inch pie plate.
Fry onion and ground beef.
Drain fat.
Add pizza sauce to beef mixture and mix well.
Spoon cottage cheese onto spaghetti crust and then add meat sauce on top of cottage cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over top and bake for another 5 to 10 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients well.
Stir in chips.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine water, oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Add flour mixture to liquids; beat well.
Pour into cupcake molds and top with spoonful of cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 cup chopped nuts (optional).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 18 cupcakes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies; set aside.
(Can use blender or food processor.)
In big bowl, mix 1/4 of Cool Whip, cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
In another bowl, mix remaining Cool Whip, milk and pudding.
Fold the two mixtures together.
Layer in large bowl or flower pot with cookie crumbs on top.
Decorate with flowers or gummy worms.

title: lemon fruit freeze
directions: In medium saucepan, combine oleo, sugar and crumbs, reserving 1/3 cup for garnish.
Pat crumbs firmly on bottom of 13 x 9 inch baking pan.
Bake at 300° for 12 minutes.
Cool.
In a large bowl mix milk, and lemon juice, stir in pie filling and fruit cocktail. Pour over cooled crust.
Top with whipped topping and sprinkle with 1/3 cup crumbs.
Freeze four (4) hours.
Remove from freezer 20 minutes before serving.
If desired garnish with lemon slices.

title: punch for a crowd
directions: Combine ingredients and chill.
Makes 6 gallons.

title: mexican cabbage
directions: Brown meat, onion, pepper and garlic together.
Drain grease. Add soup, Ro-Tel and tomatoes.
Add shredded cabbage.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 45 minutes or until done.

title: buns
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Scald milk with sugar, shortening and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in flour, beat well and then add dissolved yeast, beaten eggs, orange juice and peel.
Use flour and form in soft ball.
Let rise for 10 minutes.
Knead on lightly floured board until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl and let rise until double.
Punch down, cover and let rise for 10 minutes.
Shape for buns.
Let it rise until bun doubles in size.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Excellent bun for Sloppy Joes or as bread, served warm.
Also can be frosted and used at breakfast time.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Heat brown sugar and 1 1/4 cups water to boiling point.
Mix together flour, salt and 1/4 cup water; add to the syrup, stirring constantly.
Cook in a double boiler until thick.
Add beaten egg yolks, butter and vanilla.
Cook 2 minutes longer.
Cool and pour into baked pie shell.

title: roasted fresh tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Use tomatoes held at room temperature until fully ripe. Core tomatoes; cut into halves horizontally. Gently squeeze halves to remove seeds. Place cut side up on rack in broiler pan; set aside.

title: cabbage ground beef casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Place shredded cabbage in pan; sprinkle rice on top.
Saute onions and peppers.
Brown ground beef.
Combine onion, pepper and beef; add tomato sauce and water.
Pour over cabbage.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes or 1 hour.
Remove; sprinkle on cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: burrito casserole
directions: Prepare meat with taco seasoning.
Soften flour tortillas. Add meat and cheeses; roll up and put in greased casserole dish. Mix 2 cans cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Pour over tortillas.
Sprinkle remaining cheeses over top.
Bake until bubbly in a glass pan at 325° or in a metal pan at 350°.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Chop artichoke hearts coarsely, then mix with all other ingredients.
Bake at 375° until brown.
Serve with crackers or tortilla chips.
Garnish with chopped onion.

title: pecan chews
directions: With rolling pin, roll together brown sugar and nuts until they are thoroughly blended.
Beat egg whites until stiff, adding white sugar gradually.
Fold brown sugar mixture into egg whites. Add vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven.

title: chicken pie casserole
directions: Boil chicken in salted water and cook until tender (reserve broth).
Remove meat from bones, chop in chunks and place in a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Pour broth, mixed with soup, over chicken.
Mix together margarine, flour, milk and parsley.
Spoon over other ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: basic yellow cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease and lightly flour bottom only of 13 x 9-inch pan or 2 well-greased and lightly floured 9-inch round pans.
In large bowl, blend all ingredients except vanilla, egg yolks and egg at low speed until moist.
Then beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add egg yolks, eggs and vanilla and beat 2 more minutes at medium speed.
Pour batter into prepared pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Completely cool and frost.

title: dad's favorite casserole
directions: Mix well and bake, covered, for 45 minutes at 350°.
Add grated cheese over top and return to oven for about 10 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Mix ingredients, except chicken and broccoli.
Cut chicken into chunks; add to mixture.
Pour over broccoli.
Top with melted butter and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemonade pie #2
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in lemonade and milk. Fold in Cool Whip.
Put into pie crust and chill 2 hours before serving.

title: fudge
directions: Bring to boil 1 minute in large pan sugar, cocoa, butter, vanilla and milk.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallow and peanut butter.
Stir well. Pour into greased pan.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Cook and drain spinach. Mix cottage cheese, seasonings, raw eggs and melted butter. Grease a large lasagna pan. Place a layer of noodles in pan, followed by a layer of cottage cheese mixture, Monterey Jack cheese, spinach and Parmesan cheese. Repeat layers. Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 40 minutes. Let stand 15 minutes before serving. Reheats in the oven or microwave well.

title: fresh tomato salad
directions: Slice tomatoes 1/4 inch thick.
Alternate with cheese slices on platter.
Sprinkle with shreds of basil and drizzle balsamic vinegar or Italian dressing on top.
Sprinkle with fresh-ground black pepper and garnish with black olives.

title: chocolate syrup brownies
directions: Mix together margarine, sugar, eggs, and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: wiggles
directions: Fry hamburger until brown.
Put in bottom of casserole; add peas, tomatoes or soup and spaghetti.
Pour mushroom soup into hamburger skillet and thin with milk.
Heat this and pour over casserole.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: hamburger chow mein
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and celery; drain and pour into casserole dish.
Pour soup, water, uncooked white rice and soy sauce into hamburger mixture.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Pour over chow mein noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in 6 cups of water until tender.
Do not drain. Melt oleo in a pan.
Stir in flour and blend.
Add to cooked potatoes and stir.
Gradually stir in 1 quart of milk.
Mix well and add Velveeta cheese.
This is best if made the day ahead. Makes 10 servings.

title: delicious cottage cheese salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit (save it for the kids, they will love it).
Sprinkle dry jello over cottage cheese and mix.
Add fruit and Cool Whip.
Serve well chilled.

title: hamburger casserole for one
directions: Cook rice; remove from heat.
Brown beef and onion.
Add onion soup.
Cook bacon crisp.
Mix all together.
Add rice.
Do not cook.
Serve immediately.

title: angel's choice roll or spread
directions: Combine all ingredients, pack into mold and refrigerate overnight.
Can roll into a roll and wrap in Saran Wrap.
This makes 2 quarts.

title: biscuit, beef and cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to
a
large
frying pan, brown ground beef, onions
and
green
pepper, drain, stir in tomato sauce, beans, garlic salt or powder and pinch of sugar and let simmer. Meanwhile, separate biscuit dough in ungreased 9-inch pie pan. Press
over bottom and sides to form crust.
Combine egg and 1 cup cheese.
Bake
at	375° for 25 minutes or until golden brown. Refrigerate any leftover.
Makes 5 servings.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Combine butter, sugar, milk and flour.
Stir as for making cornbread.
Pour into small baking pan.
Pour sweetened fruit (your choice) over batter.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Bake the crescent rolls for 7 to 8 minutes.
Cream the mayonnaise or Miracle Whip, sour cream and cream cheese.
Spread over the top of the cooled rolls.
Sprinkle the dry Ranch dressing over it.
Then add all the vegetables.
Cover with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Use a large cookie sheet.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Grease pan and combine all ingredients.
Bake, covered, about 1 hour at 350°.

title: christmas cream cake
directions: Beat egg whites and set aside.
Cream margarine, oil, sugar, egg yolks and vanilla.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Mix and add coconut and nuts.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour batter into 3 (9-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: Drain sauerkraut.
Brown hamburger and drain off fat.
Combine all ingredients and mix together well.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Makes 5 servings.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla, blend well.
Combine flour, cocoa, salt and baking soda, blend in with mixture.
Stir in nuts and/or chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Prepare in a large Pyrex dish.
Pour oleo over cookies.
Place cookie mixture in bottom of Pyrex dish.
Freeze about 20 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain, reserving drippings.
Cook celery and onion in drippings.
In large pot, add celery, onion, chopped potato, carrot, allspice, bay leaf, salt, pepper and water.
Heat mixture to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer covered about 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Remove bay leaf. Combine sour cream and flour and gradually stir in half and half. Mixture may be lumpy.
Stir in soup until thickened and bubbly. Stir in mashed potatoes and bacon.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mushroom-garlic chicken with artichokes
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
In a large frying pan, melt butter over medium heat.
Add half the garlic and cook 1 minute.
Add chicken and cook until lightly browned, 3 minutes a side.
Remove to a warm serving platter.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Prepare noodles by box directions.
Drain noodles.
Mix noodles, tuna and cheese; put it in the bowls.
It's my favorite.

title: crunchy beef casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and drain.
Brown beef and drain.
Combine all ingredients, except onions.
Pour 1/2 the mixture into a 2-quart, greased casserole.
Add 1/2 the onions on top.
Pour remaining mixture over onions.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat egg with milk, then stir in 1 Tbsp. Crisco Oil or melted Crisco and the corn. Add combined dry ingredients and stir just enough to evenly distribute the ingredients.

title: apricot balls(cookie or snack)
directions: Grind apricots.
Blend coconut and apricots in a mixing bowl. Stir in Eagle Brand milk until well blended.
Shape in small balls with buttered hands.
Roll each ball in sifted powdered sugar. Let stand and roll in powdered sugar again.
Store in a tightly covered container in the refrigerator or a cool place.

title: grilled hamburgers
directions: Make patties out of meat.
Salt and pepper each side.
Put patties on grill.
Cook until done.

title: celia's favorite christmas cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the shortening, sugar, egg, honey and lemon flavoring.
Then sift together and stir in the flour, soda and salt.
Chill dough.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into desired shapes.
Place 1-inch apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake until when touched lightly with fingers, no imprint remains.
When cool, ice and decorate as desired.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°. Makes about 5 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: best ever fruit cake
directions: Stir all together.
Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 hours in tube pan. Brush top while still hot with light corn syrup.

title: dropped tea cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together and set aside.
Cream butter, shortening, sugar and egg.
Add to dry ingredients; mix well.

title: ice cream kolache
directions: When mixing the ingredients, soften the butter and ice cream a bit.
After mixing all the ingredients, put in a bowl and cover with plastic wrap.
Let set in refrigerator for about an hour.
It will be easier to work with the dough.
Roll out about 1/8-inch thick; cut in any shape, or form and fill with desired filling.

title: easy coconut pie
directions: Mix on low speed the eggs, sugar and butter.
Fold in coconut. Pour in pie shell.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° until firm.

title: 24 hour slaw
directions: Use blender or food processor to finely shred vegetables.
Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.
Remains fresh up to 1 week if kept refrigerated in covered bowl.

title: dream whip salad
directions: Mix together ingredients and chill.

title: fruity shakes
directions: Pour water in electric blender container.
Add gelatin dessert mix.
Cover and blend at medium speed for one minute. Scrape sides of container.
With machine running, add ice cream by spoonfuls through hole in lid of blender.
Add milk and ice; blend at medium speed for 30 seconds.
Serve immediately.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Dice fruits and coarsely chop nuts; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs yolks and beat well.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to fruit nut mixture; toss to coat.
Add to butter mixture; blend with wooden spoon.
Gradually stir in vanilla extract and orange juice.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry. Fold into batter.
Turn batter into 2 well-greased 8-inch tube pans, lined on the bottom with waxed or heavy brown paper.
Bake in a preheated very slow oven (275°) for 2 hours and 15 minutes or until a cake tester inserted into center comes out clean.
Place a pan of hot water on rack underneath cake during baking period.
If desired, turn batter into seven well-greased and lined 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Bake in a preheated very slow oven (275°) for 1 hour or until a cake tester inserted into center comes out clean. Cool cakes in pans on rack 1/2 hour.
Remove from pans.
Peel off paper and cool completely.
Yield:
2 (8 inch) cakes or 7 (4-inch) loaves.
Makes 7 1/2 pounds of fruit cake.

title: turtles
directions: Cook and stir constantly and vigorously; it burns easily. Cook until it forms a firm ball in cool water (remove from heat when testing).
Pour into a 4-cup Pyrex cup and pour caramel over nuts already placed on greased cookie sheets.
Spread with chocolate that has been melted.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add margarine and eggs.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Grease pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: oyster spread
directions: Mix all ingredients. Roll into log shape and refrigerate. Serve with crackers.

title: quick beef stew
directions: Combine oil, chuck and onion in large Dutch oven.
Cook over high heat until beef is browned.
Cover, reduce to low heat and cook 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Makes 9 cups.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Mix the soups together in a bowl.
Skin the chicken pieces and trim fat.
Put the chicken pieces in the crock-pot.
Season as desired.
Pour soup mixture over top.
Cover and cook on High for 4 to 5 hours or on low for 6 to 8 hours.
The gravy is great on rice. Yield:
6 servings.

title: angel hair pasta with scallops
directions: If using sea scallops, halve them.
In a large, heavy skillet, heat butter and saute scallops over high heat, shaking pan and tossing scallops often so they don't stick, for 2 minutes or until firm on the outside.
Remove from pan.
Add shallots and wine to pan; bring wine to a boil.
Let bubble vigorously until reduced by half.
Pour cream into pan with salt and pepper and simmer for 2 minutes.
Add scallops and any accumulated liquid.
Turn off heat and set sauce aside.
Bring large saucepan of water to boil.
Drop in pasta.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Dip cup into pasta and remove 1/2 cup of water and set aside.
Drain pasta.
Return to pan.
Add a few tablespoons of cream, salt and pepper and toss.
Cover.
Add pasta cooking liquid to scallop mixture.
Bring just to boil. Divide pasta among 6 pasta bowls.
Spoon sauce and scallops onto each.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat sugar, cream cheese, and margarine until creamy.
Add vanilla and milk until spreading consistency.
Add pecans.
Spread on cooled cake between layers and on top.

title: coconut cream dessert
directions: Mix flour, soft butter and nuts and pour into dish.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and confectioners sugar.
Spread on baked layer.
Mix pudding.
Let thicken and spread over cream layer.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Top with 1/2 cup toasted coconut.
Chill and serve.

title: bubble ring
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Cut cheese in 20 pieces.
Flatten out biscuits.
Place 1 piece of cream cheese and 1 teaspoon of cinnamon-sugar mixture in center of biscuit; pull up edges and press together.
Melt butter in bottom of Bundt pan.
Put remaining sugar and nuts in bottom of pan.
Arrange biscuits around pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Grease large casserole dish.
Line pan with one sheet of beef at a time, bottom and sides.
Wrap bacon around chicken, put in pan.
Mix soup with 1/2 can water and add to casserole.
Put lid on or foil on dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Remove lid.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Delicious over rice.

title: pasta and vodka cream sauce
directions: Melt butter with oil in large heavy saucepan over medium heat. Add onion and saute until translucent, about 8 minutes.
Add tomatoes and cook until almost no liquid remains in pan, stirring frequently, about 25 minutes.
Add cream, vodka and red pepper. Bring to boil and stir until sauce thickens slightly, about 2 minutes.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cook pasta (penne or rigatoni) and pour sauce over.

title: firehouse baked beans for a crowd(50 to 60)
directions: Mix all well, enough for 1 large steam-table pan.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours, stirring every 20 to 30 minutes.
(If you divide into smaller pans such as 13 x 19-inch or medium roaster, baking time will be less.)

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl
beat eggs until foamy; beat in flour, sugar and brown sugar
until well blended.
Blend in melted butter. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: hominy "mexican" dish
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex baking dish.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: pinto bean custard
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into a pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Makes 2 pies.

title: low-fat coconut delight(cindy parkin's favorite!)
directions: Mix well and pat into the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until light brown.
Let cool completely.

title: quick gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add pineapple and cheese.
Mix milk and mayonnaise and stir in jello.
Chill until firm.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add shrimp.
Simmer 3 minutes or until done.
Drain well.
Rinse with cold water.
Chill, peel, devein and chop shrimp.
Set aside.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon, and oil in large mixing bowl. Add eggs, stir in pie filling and mix well. Place into greased and floured tube pan or bunt pan and bake.

title: dana's favorite chicken parmesan
directions: Beat egg and 1 tablespoon water.
Roll chicken in egg mixture, then in crumbs.
In skillet, brown chicken in oil.
Stir in soup, 1/4 cup water, onion and seasonings.
Cover; cook over low heat 45 minutes or until done.
Stir occasionally.
Sprinkle with cheese; heat until cheese melts.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese and additional oregano leaves, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and salt together well.
Add milk, pineapple and crumbs to butter mixture.
Put into casserole.
Bake uncovered 45 minutes at 375.
Can be served as vegetable or dessert.

title: easy crab appetizer
directions: Unwrap cream cheese and place on serving platter.
Drain and flake crabmeat.
Mound crab on cream cheese.
Cover with cocktail sauce.
Surround with crackers of your choice.
Serve with cocktail knives for spreading on crackers.

title: sugar and walnut glazed brie
directions: In a small mixing bowl or wide mouth jar, stir together sugar, nuts and brandy.
Cover; chill up to one week.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Cut fryer into pieces and add salt, pepper and garlic salt. Dip chicken into a batter, then roll in dry bread crumbs, then Parmesan cheese.
Roll again in crumbs, then cheese.
Put in shallow pan and bake, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours at 350° until done and crisp.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Place bread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle sausage and 1 cup cheese over bread.
Mix eggs, milk and mustard and pour in pan.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Stir together first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.

Stir in vanilla, pineapple, bananas, and 1 cup of pecans. Pour batter into 3 greased and flowered 9 inch round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 23-38 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove from pans onto wire racks and cool completely on the wire racks.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Make 3 or 5-inch cookies.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: mommie's okra soup
directions: Braise meat in very little oil.
Add water, cover and bring to a boil; turn down heat and cook slowly for 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients and more water, if needed.
Cover and cook on low heat for 1 hour or until ready to eat.

title: pickled trout
directions: Skin and cut trout in 2-inch pieces.
Place in large pan. Cover with water.
Bring to boil and cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain and pack in wide-mouth pint jar with raw onion.
Combine vinegar and water and spices in pan.
Boil 15 minutes.
Pour hot syrup over fish and seal jars.
Let stand 3 or 4 days before using for best flavor.

title: congo squares
directions: Sift brown sugar, flour, baking powder and salt all together. Melt margarine.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add the flour mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Bake at 325° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: chicken pie
directions: Layer chicken in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
(If using noodles, mix cooked noodles with chicken as first item in pan.) Top with peas and carrots.
Add eggs.
Mix soup and broth; pour over other ingredients.

title: coffee caramels
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, hot water, instant coffee and 3/4 c. sour cream.
Cook over medium heat; stirring constantly until sugar dissolves.
Continue cooking without stirring until candy thermometer reaches 226°, about 15 minutes.
Add remaining 3/4 c. cream, butter and salt.
Cook to hard ball stage (250°).
Remove from heat; cool slightly and carefully stir in vanilla.
Pour into buttered 8 inch square pan; cool.
When firm; cut, wrap if desired.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Boil chicken.
Set aside broth with 1/2 cup noodles.
Combine all else together.
Add broth.
Bake in greased dish 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup noodles on top before baking.
Good potluck dish.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hanky panky
directions: Brown beef; drain and set aside.
Brown sausage, drain.
Add beef to sausage; add cheese in small portions.
Add spices, stir until cheese melts and mixes with meat.

title: old fashion pumpkin bread
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking soda and spices into large bowl.

title: peach preserves cake
directions: Cream butter
and
sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, mixing well after
each
addition.
Sift
flour, cinnamon, cloves and baking soda
together.
Add
dry ingredients to butter mixture gradually with buttermilk, chopped pecans and peach preserves. When mixed, pour into a greased angel food or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for
1 hour.
You may also use 3 small pans and bake at 350° for
45 minutes.
This cake freezes well and stays moist a long time.

title: chocolate peanut butter mix
directions: In a large bowl, put cereal.
Melt together in a pan: chocolate chips, butter and peanut butter. Add vanilla.
Pour this chocolate mixture over cereal and mix well. Pour coated cereal into large sealable plastic bag or large Tupperware with lid along with powdered sugar.
Shake until well coated.
Spread on wax paper to cool.

title: cabbage rolls in a crock-pot
directions: Fry onion in bacon grease until onion is soft.
Mix ground beef, rice, salt, pepper, egg, fried onion and bacon grease.

title: salisbury steak
directions: In separate bowl, mix 1 cup warm water and 1 package brown gravy mix.
Add 1/4 of gravy mixture to first 5 ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Shape into steaks and fry in skillet on low heat until done.
Remove steaks and discard grease.
Pour reserved gravy mixture into skillet; add steaks.
Stir carefully until gravy thickens.
Remove steaks, arrange on platter and pour remaining gravy on steaks.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries, sugar and water 20 minutes
or until done. Add marshmallows to mixture to melt. Mix jello in 1/2 cup water and add to mixture. Let set until half set. Add apples, celery and nuts. Let set until firm.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix rice in a large deep pan with all soups and water.
