Salt and pepper chicken to taste and lay on top of rice mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 1 hour.

title: cheese canapes
directions: Have cheese and margarine at room temperature.
Grate cheese; add margarine and blend mixture with your hands.
Add flour and salt.
Shape into a roll as you would for pinwheel cookies.
Wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate for several hours.
Cut into 1/8 or 1/4-inch slices and place on a salted cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 8 minutes.
May be sliced and placed on a cookie sheet in the refrigerator; ready to bake at time of serving.

title: duck and wild rice
directions: Boil duck for 1 hour in water to cover duck with celery, onion halves, salt and pepper.
Remove and cube meat.
Reserve broth.
Cook the rice according to package directions.
Melt butter. Saute onions in butter. Stir in flour.
Drain mushrooms, reserving broth.
Add mushrooms to onion mixture.
Add enough duck broth to the mushroom broth to make 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Stir this into the onion mixture.
Omitting almonds, add remaining ingredients plus 1 1/2 tsp. salt and 1/4 tsp. pepper.
Put into greased 2 quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake covered at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 5-10 minutes.

title: travel cookies(feed as well as fill)
directions: Add nuts, raisins, dates, coconut, chocolate chips or mini marshmallows, as desired.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Great to pack.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.
Makes a large batch.

title: fresh blueberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in pot.
Add water and 1 cup blueberries.
Bring to boil.
Cook, stirring, until very thick.
Stir in butter and lemon juice.
Cook.
Fold in rest of blueberries.
Chill one hour.
Beat whipped cream.
Add confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Spread whipped cream mixture over top of pie.

title: dinner crepes
directions: Combine and let set in fridge until cool.
Heat nonstick or special crepe pan (8-inch) and using ladle or measuring cup, put enough in pan to just cover bottom; roll around the batter until pan is covered.
Cook until lightly brown on bottom.
Carefully flip and heat a few seconds.
Continue until all batter is used up.
Will store overnight in fridge until ready to use.

title: beef (or pork) barbecue
directions: *For beef, I like bottom round roast or for pork, shoulder butt.
Have butcher "chunk" it for you to about 2 1/2-inch cubes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Arrange the cooked spaghetti in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a separate bowl, combine the cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, egg and oleo.
Spread mixture over spaghetti.
Combine your spaghetti sauce, hamburg, onion and green pepper.
On top, sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: buttermilk waffles
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Makes 4 waffles.
You can use self-rising flour if you don't have all-purpose flour.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
In saucepan, simmer the soups and tomatoes.
Crush Doritos and cover the bottom of a 2-quart baking dish with them.
Place ground beef over chips and cover with soup-tomato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Top with cheese and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: In small mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Beat in chocolate and vanilla until blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating with an electric mixer at medium speed for 5 minutes after each addition.
Turn into baked pastry shell.
Chill.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: spiced grits
directions: Boil enough water for 1 cup of grits.
To hot water, add onion flakes, parsley flakes, butter and soy sauce; cook for 1 minute. Add seasoned salt and grits.
Cook with top on boiler on very low heat, stirring occasionally.
Add more butter, if you desire, before serving.

title: tomatoes rockefeller
directions: Place tomatoes, cut side up, in an oiled baking dish.
Combine onion, parsley, margarine, spinach, pepper and paprika. Spread evenly over the tomatoes. Top with crumbs and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: kid's salad
directions: Dissolve pudding in pineapple juice.
Fold in remaining ingredients until thoroughly mixed.
Chill for several hours.

title: bread in a jar for gift-giving
directions: Cream shortening
and
sugar, beat in eggs, pumpkin and water. Sift
together
flour,
baking
powder, soda, salt and spices. Add
to pumpkin mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour mixture into greased wide-mouth pint jars, filling 1/2 full.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
When
done,
remove
one jar at a time, wipe sealing edge
with paper towel or cloth, and screw cap on tightly.	The heat will vacuum seal the jar and the bread will keep for up to one year.
Makes 8 pints.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Mix in order.
Beat for 12 minutes.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Add milk and flour alternately. Add vanilla last.
Put in cold oven; turn oven to 300° and bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana split brownie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix brownie mix as directed on package. Place parchment paper on 15-inch baking stone.
Pour brownie mixture on paper and spread into 14-inch circle (must use parchment paper!).
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Spread over brownie "crust."
Top with fruit and nuts.
Melt chocolate and butter together, stirring until smooth.
Drizzle over pizza.
Chill.
Cut into wedges with pizza cutter.

title: crab ball
directions: Drain crab meat in a colander and check for shells.
With hands mix crab meat and softened cream cheese and form into a ball.
Chill for several hours, wrapped in foil.
Remove from foil and place on serving dish.
Pour cocktail sauce over crab ball and top with parsley.
Surround ball with crackers.

title: tomato casserole
directions: Toast bread.
Spread with butter.
Put 6 slices, buttered side down, in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix tomatoes, sugar, onion, salt and pepper.
Pour over bread in dish.
Put remaining slices, buttered side up, over mixture.
Top with Mozzarella or Cheddar cheese.
Bake for 1/2 hour in 350° oven.

title: herbed cheese bread
directions: Heat butter, garlic, parsley and poppy seed together.
Cut loaf into squares or diamonds, leaving bottom crust intact.
Insert cheese slices into each cut.
Dribble melted butter mixture into openings.
Wrap in foil.
(Bread may be set aside at this time.) Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Loosen foil to expose top and bake another 15 minutes to brown lightly.
Serve hot.

title: shrimp curry indienne
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, heat 3 inches of water to boiling.
Add shrimp; bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Reduce to low heat and cook 1 minute or until shrimp turns pink.
Drain.

title: oriental pasta salad
directions: Cook linguine according to package. Drain and rinse in cold water; drain.
Add vegetables. Combine remaining ingredients in a jar; cover tightly.
Shake vigorously.
Pour over salad and toss gently to coat. Serve immediately.
Yields 8 servings. Easily doubled.

title: chicken and bacon casserole
directions: Cover bottom of casserole dish	with
dried beef.
Wrap each chicken breast with bacon and place on top of dried beef. Mix soup and sour cream and pour
mixture over chicken.
Cover with foil and cook in 300° oven for
2 hours.
Remove foil and cook another hour.

title: fruit ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, reserving 1 cup of nuts to roll cheese ball in.
Serve with vanilla wafers.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Place chicken in shallow casserole.
Mix sour cream and soup and pour over chicken.
Mix crumbs and poppy seed with butter. Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be prepared and frozen.
Serves 6.
Prepare in 20 minutes.
Bake in 30 minutes.

title: lazy daisy frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread over cake.
Broil until frosting becomes bubbly.

title: fried rice
directions: Rub cooked rice with wet hands so all the grains are separated. Beat eggs. Tilt wok so eggs mixture cover the bottom and part of the sides of the pan. Cook until set then remove. Roll up and slice into thin strips. Heat another Tbsp. of oil in wok and all all other ingredients until warm. Add rice and nuts and let cook for 3 or 4 minutes.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender until smooth.
If orange juice is already made, delete 1 cup of water and use 2/3 cup of orange juice.
Makes approximately two 8-ounce glasses.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Chop vegetable mix in salt, let stand 45 minutes, then put mixture in cheesecloth bag and squeeze dry.
Place in saucepan with sugar and vinegar to cover.
Bring to a boil.
Cook until peppers change color, then jar.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Combine herbs and mix well.
Store in a dry airtight container.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Bake @ 375 degrees for 25-30 minutes.

title: cranberry cheese bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 5 loaf pan.
Sift flour with sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Stir in cranberries, cheese and walnuts.
Beat egg with milk and margarine. Stir into cranberry mixture and pour into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour or until loaf tests done.
Cool in pan at least 10 minutes.

title: matzo brownies
directions: In saucepan, melt chocolate and margarine over low heat.
In a mixing bowl, stir together chocolate mixture and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, with an electric mixer on medium.
Stir in matzo meal, water and salt.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Makes 16 brownies.

title: tropical punch
directions: Combine pineapple, orange and lemon juices, mixing well with sugar in large container.
This can be made ahead.

title: fried cheese sticks
directions: Cut cheese in small thick strips.
Coat with flour.
Dip in beaten egg.
Roll in bread crumbs, coating all sides.
Place on wax paper.
Chill 1 hour.
Fry in 2-inch deep oil until golden brown.
Dip in salsa and enjoy!

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Mix well the juice of the two lemons and two oranges.
Add the sugar and the well-beaten eggs.
Cook in a double boiler until mixture thickens.
Cool.
Add 1 cup of whipped cream just before serving.

title: pineapple-peach upside down cake
directions: Place pineapple and peaches in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread oleo/butter slices evenly over fruit.
Add brown sugar, then dry cake mix.
Cook until done (300° my stove).

title: strawberry romanoff
directions: Sprinkle strawberries with powdered sugar.
Stir gently. Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Just before serving, beat whipping cream in chilled bowl until stiff. Stir in orange juice. Gradually fold in strawberries.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread in lightly greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mom's sandwich spread
directions: Grind and drain first four ingredients.
Add all remaining ingredients except the salad dressing.
Mix together and bring to a boil and cook for fifteen minutes.
Add 1/2 cup of flour, thinned with water, and cook ten minutes longer.
Remove from heat; stir in one quart salad dressing.
Put back on stove on low heat.
Do not bring to a boil.
Can in hot jars and seal.

title: men-love-it salad
directions: Mash cream cheese; blend with pineapple.
Add nuts and celery. Dissolve gelatin in water.
When cool, mix with cheese.
Pour into individual molds; place in refrigerator until congealed. Serve with favorite salad dressing on lettuce leaf.

title: fried potato scramble
directions: Dice potatoes, carrots, pepper and onion.
Fry potatoes and carrots together until almost done.
Add pepper, onion and Bac*Os; cook until done.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Blend salt into flour.
Cut in shortening well.
Combine beaten egg, vinegar and water.
Pour into flour mixture all at once.
Blend by hand or spoon until all dry ingredients are moistened.
Roll out.
Makes 3 singles or 1 double and 1 single crust.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: chex muddy buddies
directions: Pour cereal in large bowl and set aside.
Mix butter, chocolate chips and peanut butter in microwave-safe bowl or in saucepan on stove over low heat.
Melt and pour over cereal, stirring until evenly coated.
Pour into Ziploc bag with powdered sugar.
Seal and shake until all pieces are coated.
Spread on waxed paper until cool.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage into 1-inch chunks and cook until tender.
Drain. Cook diced bacon until crisp; remove from pan and drain.
Saute onion and pepper in same pan.
Mix first 6 ingredients.
Put in casserole dish and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until browned.

title: baked rice pudding
directions: Combine sugar, salt and milk with eggs.
Stir in rice, raisins and vanilla.
Pour into a buttered 1-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake at 350° in a water bath for about 50 minutes.

title: easy cherry cake
directions: Pour pie filling and pineapple (undrained) into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle the cake mix on top.
Pour melted margarine over this.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts on top.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: ranch biscuits
directions: Mix together
the buttermilk, salt, sugar and oil; heat to lukewarm.
Mix
thoroughly the flour, baking powder and dry yeast, then
add
milk mixture; mix.
Let stand until doubled. Heat the oleo in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Knead dough 20 strokes on a floured surface;
roll to
1/2-inch thick.
Cut with a 2 1/2 inch cutter or any size.
Turn
once
in
oleo to grease tops. Let rise until doubled.
Bake
at
350° until lightly browned, 30 minutes.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Prepare corn bread mix as it says on package; allow to cool. Crumble corn bread and add onion, bell pepper and tomatoes.
Toss these ingredients.
Mix mayonnaise and mustard.
Pour over corn bread mixture and stir until mayonnaise is mixed in well. Refrigerate and eat.

title: elaine's fresh salsa
directions: Roast tomato and jalapeno.
(When handling jalapenos, wear rubber gloves.)
Chop all ingredients into small pieces.
When cutting tomatoes, save all juices.
Mix all ingredients together and place into refrigerator before serving.
Make day of serving for best results. For a hotter, spicier salsa, prepare 1 to 3 days ahead of serving.
The longer it sits, the hotter it gets.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in brown sugar, syrup and salt.
Bring to boil and stir constantly, but boil 5 minutes, no stirring.
Remove from heat and stir in soda and vanilla.
Gradually pour over popped corn and mix well.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, turning every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool completely.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together with mixer. Add sugar, a little at a time. Add one egg at a time. Alternately add flour and cream. Add extracts. Reduce speed on mixer to 1. Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: taco ground round dip
directions: Brown ground round and onion in skillet.
Add seasoning mix; blend.
Add water and tomato sauce.
Blend.
Add beans; blend. Add salsa; cook for a few minutes.
Add olives.
Pour mixture into baking dish; sprinkle half of the grated sharp Cheddar cheese over the top.

title: pears and berries soup
directions: Puree the pears, berries and cinnamon in a blender or food processor.
If desired, substitute peaches or nectarine for the pears.
Add the cran-raspberry beverage and blend again.
Chill. When ready to serve, garnish with additional berries and a dollop of yogurt.

title: gran haun's broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes; drain.
Make sauce from other ingredients.
Mix with broccoli.
Put into greased casserole dish. Top with 1/2 cup cheese cracker crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: wassail
directions: Make syrup by boiling sugar and water 10 minutes.
Add cloves, allspice and ginger.
Let syrup stand, covered, in a warm place, for an hour.
(The syrup can be made the day before needed.) Strain.
Add orange juice, lemon juice and cider.
Bring quickly to the boiling point and serve at once, piping hot.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach.
Drain.
Press out as much water as possible. Mix all, refrigerate 24 hours.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crushed corn flakes and melted butter.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Mix corn flakes and melted butter and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: saucy chops
directions: Brown chops; sprinkle with salt, pepper and chili powder. Mix green onions, olives, mushrooms, water and tomato sauce.
Pour over chops and cover pan.
Cook over low heat until chops are tender, approximately 1 hour.

title: frosty fruit pie
directions: Bring pineapple, gelatine and sugar to a boil.
Set aside to cool.
Whip milk and lemon juice until stiff (I chill beaters and bowl first).
Fold into cooled pineapple.
Be sure it's all blended.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Chill until set.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Dissolve soda in persimmon pulp.
Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Add raisins to flour.
Add egg to persimmon pulp.
Add dry and moist ingredients alternately into persimmon pulp.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonful onto greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.
Makes approximately 5 dozen cookies.

title: butterless and eggless cake
directions: Cook raisins with 2 cups cold water for 15 minutes.
Let cool, then add 1 cup cold water, sugar, shortening, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, baking soda, flour and chopped nuts.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: vegetable appetizers
directions: Flatten crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Bake until golden brown.
Mix 3/4 veggies with cream cheese mixed with mayonnaise and Ranch mix.
Spread on baked dough.
Top with remaining veggies.
Garnish with 1 cup shredded Cheddar cheese and diced tomatoes, if desired.
Cut and chill.

title: beef zucchini casserole
directions: Saute ground beef with zucchini and onion in Dutch oven until beef is browned. Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover and cook over low heat for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Uncover and cook 5 minutes longer or until vegetables are tender.

title: almond bark
directions: Cook briskly until almonds pop and candy is light brown, about 10 minutes.
Turn up the burner slightly to get it brown.
Never stop stirring.
Pour on heated cookie sheet.
Spread thin.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Work together until it forms a ball.
Roll out on floured board about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutters or make your own shapes.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cabbage soup
directions: In

a large pot, brown ground chuck and onion. Drain fat and return to pan. Add the cabbage, tomatoes, margarine and water as needed. Cook until tender. Add salt and pepper. Cook 30 to 60 minutes on medium heat. Good with crisp corn bread.

title: saucy noodle skillet
directions: Saute luncheon meat in butter.
Add onions, green pepper and celery; saute lightly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Serves four to six.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until done. Drain macaroni.
Let macaroni stand in cold water while you prepare other ingredients.
Drain macaroni and mix well with other ingredients.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: jello cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to box directions.
Cool cake.
When completely cooled, poke holes with a fork or small handle of a wooden spoon.
Mix lime jello, boiling water and cold water.
Pour jello mixture into the holes of the cake.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: steve's triangle chili
directions: Saute 3 buds garlic in olive oil, brown meat in oil; drain. Slice 3 more garlic buds, put in pot.
Add the meat, canned tomatoes, onion, all the peppers and the beer.
Bring to a boil, add all the spices and stir, reduce heat to low, add 2 bay leaves and the bacon fat.
Simmer 2 hours.
Add beans, simmer another hour.
Use cornmeal to thicken to taste.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add strawberries.
Cool only until syrupy.
Divide int 2/3 and 1/3.
Break up cake in 9
x 13-inch pan.
Spread 2/3 of Jell-O on cakes.
Mix other 1/3 into whip cream.
Spread whipped mixture on top.

title: potatoes and cabbage in tomato sauce(patate e verze al salsa di pomodori)
directions: Clean
and
slice
up cabbage.
Peel and cube potatoes. Place cabbage and potatoes in large saucepan and add the rest of the ingredients.
Bring to a boil; then cook on medium heat until potatoes
are
tender,
about 45 minutes.
Stir mixture occasionally
to make sure it does not stick.
Check to see if there is enough
juice.
If potatoes and cabbage look too dry, add a little more water.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
This makes a great first course dish.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil, eggs and sugar.
Add apples, nuts and coconut. Stir thoroughly.
Add soda, salt, cinnamon and vanilla.
Then stir in flour until batter is very stiff.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hawaiian pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on package
using 2 layer pans, or one 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool completely.

title: spanish noodles
directions: Cook first four ingredients all together.
Cook noodles until tender and drain.
Add cream of mushroom soup, tomato soup and 2 cans water.
Add hamburg mixture, Worcestershire sauce and sugar. Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: salmonettes heloise (long time family favorite)
directions: Open salmon and pour liquid in measuring cup and set aside. Dump salmon in bowl; add egg and mix with fork.
Add flour and stir thoroughly.
Take 1/4 c. salmon liquid and add baking powder. Beat with fork.
After it has foamed, add to salmon mixture.
Mix again with fork.
Drop by small tsp. in hot oil.
Done in a few seconds.

title: coconut pie
directions: Note:
This pie makes its own crust.

title: grape punch
directions: Combine all ingredients except ginger ale.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Fill
pie
tin 3/4 full of strawberries in baked crust. Cook remaining
ingredients
until thick;
cool and pour over strawberries.
Refrigerate.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: full o fruit bars
directions: Stir together flour, salt, nutmeg, baking soda and cinnamon; set aside.
In large bowl, cream margarine.
Gradually add sugar and cream until well blended.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, then add vanilla.
Stir in pineapple and flour mix.
Add apples and raisins until well blended.
Spread evenly in greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.
Remove from oven; cool on rack.
Spread with cream cheese icing.
Cut into 64 bars.
Garnish each with walnut half.

title: baked beans with hamburger meat
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain grease.
Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: simple stroganoff
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic:
drain off fat.
Blend soup and milk: add to meat mixture and heat well.
Reduce heat and carefully blend in sour cream.
Serve over noodles or rice. Serves 4.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Keep in refrigerator.
Let set 5 days before using.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes.
Layer a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle flour, cheese, salt, pepper, seasoned salt and garlic salt.
Cut butter in 1/4-inch pieces.
Sprinkle butter on the potatoes. Repeat the layers, but let the last layer be cheese.
Add milk until halfway full, then fill the rest up with water until water is under cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until cheese is golden brown.

title: cherries jubilee chicken
directions: Drain cherries; sprinkle with brandy and set aside.
Mix cherry juice, sherry, brown sugar, onions, chili sauce and Worcestershire sauce and set aside.
Blend flour, seasoned salt, salt, pepper and paprika.
Dredge chicken in the flour mixture. Place in baking pan and pour melted margarine over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Mix cherry juice mixture and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° until done.
Arrange chicken on platter. Strain liquid from chicken; season to taste.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Add brandied cherries and liquid to sauce.
Heat through.
Pour some over chicken and serve the rest in a sauce boat.
Makes 12 servings.

title: fudgy buttons
directions: In a small saucepan, melt the butter; remove from heat.
Add cocoa and mix well.
Stir in sugar, add milk and stir until smooth.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Flatten tops and shape into 1 inch patties. Yield: about 1 1/2 dozen.

title: my kolaches
directions: Let warm milk, yeast and 2 tablespoons of sugar stand until yeast comes to the top, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Add enough flour (approximately 2 1/2 cups) for not real thin or thick. Let rise until double.
Add egg yolks, whole egg, lemon rind and juice, salt, 3/4 cup sugar and shortening.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix well.
Store in tight container.
To serve, put 2 to 3 teaspoons of mix per cup of hot water.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 13-inch loaf cake pan or skillet by putting in oven.
Mix flour, sugar and milk.
By this time, butter is melted and you pour this dough mixture in pan of butter.
Do not mix.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
You can use canned peaches, cherries or any other fruit.
Right out of the oven with ice cream is our favorite.

title: lemon lime punch
directions: Combine powdered drink mix, water, sugar and pineapple juice. Add ginger ale when ready to serve.
Serve ice cold.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef with onion.
Drain.
Mix all other ingredients. Pour over beef.
Simmer until thick, stirring occasionally.
Serve over buns.

title: linguini salad
directions: Mix the linguini and Italian dressing together.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix, chill and eat.

title: koulourakia (greek butter cookies)
directions: Beat butter well (about 30 minutes) until light and fluffy. Gradually add sugar and beat well.
Add cream, grated orange rind and 5 egg yolks (save 3 whites).
Mix baking powder with some of the flour.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Alternate flour and beaten egg whites and add to the mixture.
Check mixture until you can roll the dough to make cookies.

title: bean casserole
directions: Heat on 350° until done in oven.

title: mile high biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Lightly grease a baking sheet.

title: sausage balls
directions: Blend all the ingredients by hand.
Roll into small balls. Bake at 400° until brown.
Serve hot.
May be frozen until ready to bake or partially bake before freezing.

title: potatoes with cream cheese
directions: Combine cheese and milk; heat until melted, but don't boil. Add other ingredients and pour over potatoes.

title: no-bake crunchies
directions: Slowly melt peanut butter and butterscotch chips in a saucepan. Place crushed cornflakes in a large bowl.
Pour peanut butter mixture over cornflakes and stir until well mixed.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper and let cool.
This makes about 24 pieces.

title: chicken tortillas casserole
directions: I use chicken breast cut into small bite size.
Saute chicken breast, onions and celery.
Add broth, tortillas, green chilies, chicken soup, pepper and 1/2 of cheese. Pour into 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan.
Top with other half cheese and salsa.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: straw hats
directions: Brown
hamburger.
Cook
and drain
dried
beans.
Mix hamburger, beans, sauce, oregano and ketchup.
Rinse spaghetti sauce jars with water
and
add.
Simmer
until hot.
Layer on serving plates the corn chips on bottom, bean mixture, cheese, etc.
Each person makes their
own with what they want and how much.
Some of us like
to put mayonnaise or salad dressing on top.

title: roast potatoes swedish-style
directions: Peel potatoes.
Put in cold water to prevent discoloring.
Put 1 potato in deep spoon. Slice it down to edge of spoon, making slices about 1/8-inch apart.
Spoon will prevent cutting through potato. Return sliced potato to cold water.
Slice others in the same manner. Drain potatoes.
Pat dry.
Put potatoes, cut side up, in a large buttered baking dish.
Baste with some butter. Sprinkle with salt. Cook 30 minutes in preheated 425° oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over each potato.
Baste with remaining butter. Cook 15 minutes or until golden brown and tender. Add cheese 5 minutes before potatoes are done. Yields 6 servings.

title: the colonel's chicken
directions: Combine the flour, tomato soup powder, salt, paprika and Italian dressing.
Shake the chicken in the mixture.
Brown in vegetable oil, then bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: never fail rolls
directions: Stir together flour, sugar and salt.
Mix in warm milk and butter.
Add eggs, yeast and sugar.
Mix with mixer.
Cover bowl and let sit on counter overnight.
Use big bowl!
Roll and cut as desired.
Let rise and bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes good crescent rolls.

title: pepper and tomato stew
directions: Plunge the tomato and pepper into boiling water for a few seconds.
Drain and peel.
Chop the tomatoes, seed and slice the peppers.
Heat the oil in a skillet over medium heat.
Add the garlic and onion; saute until translucent.
Add the peppers (sliced) and salt to taste.
Cook for a few minutes.
Add the tomatoes and oregano.
Cover, reduce heat and cook slowly for 30 minutes, stirring from time to time.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat cooking oil and sugar in mixing bowl.
Add eggs and whip until creamy.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Grease and flour bread pans (2 large loaves or 3 small).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Do not overbake.
Take out of pans in 10 minutes.
Serve warm plain or with whipped cream or cream cheese.

title: charlotte's christmas fudge
directions: Combine chocolate, marshmallow and nuts in large bowl.
Combine sugar, salt, butter and milk in large saucepan.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil 6 minutes.

title: cranberry crumb pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prick bottom and sides of pie crust. Bake 8 minutes. Lower temperature to 350°.

title: berry good muffins
directions: Sprinkle berries with 2 tablespoons of sugar and about 1 tablespoon of flour; set aside.
Combine remaining flour and 1/2 cup of sugar, mixing in a large bowl.
Stir with fork until well blended.
Combine milk, oil and egg in a large measuring cup. Beat mixture lightly with fork until smoothly blended.
Pour into dry mixture until moistened.
Fold in berries.
Pour into greased or paper-lined muffin pans and bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Bake 20 minutes for small muffins.
Freeze leftovers for a quick, easy breakfast.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: apricot salad
directions: Heat nectar and dissolve Jell-O.
Cool and when almost ready to congeal, add celery, pineapple or strawberries, cream cheese and chopped pecans.
Chill.

title: cherry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add pineapple and cherry pie filling and let gel.
For topping, beat together cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over congealed salad. Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.
This can be used for a dessert.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.
Serves 6.

title: good coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on box.
Cool.
Frost with Cool Whip that has powdered sugar and coconut added.
Add coconut flavor if you have it to keep refrigerated.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Bake two 9-inch pie shells (homemade) 3 to 5 minutes at 350°. Fry bacon, drain well on paper towel, then crumble.
Combine eggs and milk and beat well.
Pour into 2 pie shells.
Add bacon and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: buckeyes
directions: Melt oleo; add peanut butter and mix well.
Add powdered sugar.
Mix well until it sticks together.
Roll into small balls. Place on cookie sheet and place a toothpick in each ball.
Chill 15 minutes.

title: aggie mistakes
directions: In a large pan, brown hamburger and sausage, cooking well. Add seasonings. Drain off any excess grease. Add cheese and mix until well blended.

title: brunswick stew #2
directions: Add cayenne pepper if you like a little bite to this recipe and lima beans, if you like them.

title: roasted and stuffed peppers
directions: Roasted peppers:
Broil 2 inches from heat.
Turn as skin blisters and blackens, 15 to 20 minutes.
Put in plastic bag. When cool, cut out cores and remove seeds.

title: carrot cake
directions: Stir, by hand, all ingredients, except the carrots and pecans. Once mixed, add carrots and pecans.
Line bread pan with aluminum foil and pour mixture in pan.
Bake approximately 1 hour at 350° until lightly browned.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: company beef casserole
directions: Cook onions in butter or margarine until transparent. Add chuck and brown. Add celery salt, salt, pepper, uncooked noodles and tomato juice. Simmer until noodles are tender. Do ahead to this point, if desired. Just before serving, stir in sour cream. Serve with green salad and hot breads. Serves 4 to 6.

title: jezebel spread
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over an 8 ounce or larger block of cream cheese.
Serve with Ritz or Wheatsworth crackers.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, flour and milk in top of double boiler. When it begins to thicken, add to beaten egg yolks, then return all to double boiler.
Stir constantly until thick.
Remove from heat and add 2 tablespoons butter.
Stir, cool and add vanilla. Pour into cooked pie shell.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients well.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Grease baking dish.
In mixing bowl, combine sweet potatoes, orange juice, milk, vanilla, sugar, salt, cinnamon and 3 tablespoons of the melted butter.
Beat until fluffy.
Pour into pan; melt remaining butter and add brown sugar, flour and pecans. Sprinkle mixture over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Top with marshmallows and bake until browned.
Serves 6.

title: creamy vegetable dip
directions: In a small bowl, whisk mayonnaise until smooth.
Stir in yogurt, oregano, salt, pepper and garlic.
Cover and chill for 1 hour before serving.
Serve with raw vegetables for dipping. Serves 16.

title: dr. pepper barbecue sauce
directions: Blend together equal parts of catsup and Dr. Pepper, for instance 1 cup each.
Add Tabasco sauce to taste.
